title: sweet and sour broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, raisins, bacon bits and onion in medium-size mixing bowl.
In small bowl, mix together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour on top of broccoli mix.
Toss well.

title: surprised carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
In a large bowl, stir together dry ingredients.
Mix until well blended and then set aside.

title: kolozvar sour cabbage
directions: Heat oven to 350°F.
With 1 tsp butter grease a 13x9x1 inch glass baking dish.
Set aside.
Cook sour cabbage with juices and 1 cup of warm water for about 30 minutes.
When done, strain cabbage.
Meanwhile grind 1 pound cooked smoked ham, add 4 eggs, salt lightly and pepper.
Cut in 1/2 cup fresh parsley, mix well. Put a thin layer of drained cooked sour cabbage on the bottom of baking dish, spread about 1 1/2 cups of ham mixture over the cabbage and repeat the layers.
The last layer has to be sour cabbage.
In a medium mixing bowl mix well 3 eggs with 1 1/2 cups whipping cream.
Pour evenly on top of the last cabbage layer. Bake 1 1/2 hour at 350°F.

title: french frosting
directions: Blend flour and milk.
Cook to thick paste stirring constantly. Cool to luke warm.
Cream butter, sugar and salt.
Add some to cooled paste and beat smooth.
Add all paste mixture and beat until smooth.
Add vanilla.
This frosting is unbelievably smooth if done correctly, almost like whip cream or Cool Whip.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix oleo and milk, then add sugar and coconut.
Knead.
Form into balls. Put into refrigerator to chill.
Melt chips and wax in double boiler.
Dip balls into the melted mixture.
Lay on waxed paper to cool.

title: seaside snack
directions: Pour desired amount of fish crackers (fish), peanuts (rocks), pretzel sticks (fishing poles), oyster crackers (seashells) and chocolate candies (sunken treasure) into large bowl.
Stir. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese (sand) on top.
Spoon into serving dishes.

title: apricot dessert
directions: Mix sugar mixture with some of the cold nectar.
Heat rest of nectar to boiling.
Add lemon juice.
Add boiling nectar to cold mixture.
Cook until clear and thick.
Pour 1/2 of this over 1/2 angel food cake broken into bite-size pieces over bottom of 13 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Cover with rest of angel cake bits and then pour rest of nectar mixture over this.
Chill overnight and serve with whipped cream or substitute.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill approximately 2 hours. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: banana quick bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Place shortening in bowl and beat until glossy.
Gradually add sugar and beat 200 strokes.
Add eggs and beat until pale lemon color.
Add flour mixture alternately with bananas, blending well.
Turn into a greased 4 x 8 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake in a 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool in pan half hour before removing.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, lightly beat eggs.
Add cottage cheese, broccoli, onion, 6 tablespoons oleo and muffin mix.
Beat well. Pour remaining oleo into a 10-inch iron skillet; pour batter into skillet.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden.
Cut into wedges and serve warm.
Yield:
12 to 16 servings.

title: recipe for a happy family
directions: Mix everything together thoroughly and sprinkle with awareness.
Bake in a modern oven of everyday life, using as fuel all the grudges and past unpleasantness.
Cool.
Turn out onto a dish of cheerfulness.
Garnish with tears and laughter and in large helpings serve God, your family and neighbors everywhere.

title: bev perrin's bootlegger beans
directions: Dice bacon.
When bacon is half done, add onion.
Cook until onion is slightly browned.
Pour off most of bacon grease.
Add pork and beans, brown sugar, vinegar and catsup.
Stir well and cover.
Let simmer at least 30 minutes (the longer, the better) or bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Grate German's chocolate.
Set aside 2 tablespoons to sprinkle on top of baked cake while warm.
Mix all ingredients and add the other grated chocolate.
Bake in a 300° oven for 55 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: nangka* salad
directions: Boil nangka until tender. Squeeze liquid off. Cook shrimp and peel. Mix nangka, shrimp, tomatoes, onion and coconut cream. Add vinegar, salt and pepper. Serve as appetizer.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until tender and cool, peel and grate.
Heat 1/4 cup butter with soup; blend in sour cream, onions and cheese.
Stir in potatoes.
Place mixture in buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix corn flakes with 2 tablespoons melted butter and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spread can of cream of celery soup in bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking pan or large casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup rice on this. Lay chicken pieces on rice and sprinkle dry onion soup mix over to taste.
Mix remaining soups with milk and pour over chicken.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 325° (1 1/2 hours covered and 1 hour uncovered).

title: marinated cherry tomatoes
directions: Pour the tomatoes, a few at a time, into a colander or wire strainer and dip into a large pan of rapidly boiling water for about 15 seconds.
Immediately rinse tomatoes with cold water. Slip off the peels and stems and put tomatoes into a refrigerator container or bowl.
Combine the vinegar, onion, basil, oregano, salt, pepper and salad oil; shake or beat until blended, then pour over tomatoes.
Cover and chill for at least 2 hours, or as long as overnight, stirring several times.

title: candy fudge brownies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Combine dry ingredients and stir into sugar mixture.
Fold in Snicker pieces and spoon into lightly greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Hershey pieces.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Mix eggs, brownie mix and oil.
Add morsels and nuts.
Drop onto cookie sheet and cook at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: german cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs; beat well.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla; add nuts.
Bake in a 10-inch pan for 45 minutes at 300°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and bake as you would regular corn bread.

title: penny supper
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine all the dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Add eggs with oil until dry ingredients are moist.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple and nuts; add bananas.
Grease a tube pan with butter. Preheat the oven at 350°.
Bake for 1 hour, then cool and frost.

title: three day coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Let cool. Slice into
layers.
Mix
sour cream, coconut and sugar in bowl.
Set 1 cup of mixture aside for later use as icing.
Mix Cool
Whip and
1 cup of the remaining mixture, being careful not to stir too much.
Spread between each layer of cake.
Ice the
top
with
the 1 cup of mixture prepared previously.
Put cake in refrigerator for 3 days, then eat.

title: giblet mold
directions: Grind together giblets, celery, onion, celery leaves and parsley.
Mash eggs until fine.

title: pizza
directions: Makes sauce for 3 pizzas.
Mix all the ingredients, except bread dough; simmer 1 hour.
For each pizza, spread 1 loaf of thawed dough in pan for crust.
Be sure to bring edges up enough to hold sauce.
Spread 1/3 of sauce over dough.
Top with favorite toppings and 8 ounces shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake approximately 20 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pork tenders with sour cream
directions: Rinse and dry the pork tenders; remove all fat and gristle from the outside.
Slice crosswise about 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Heat oil and butter in a large frying pan and brown pork slices on both sides.
Add onions and cook until transparent.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, tarragon and flour.
Stir in wine, cover and turn heat to low.
Cook until pork is done through (about 12 to 15 minutes). Stir in sour cream and simmer just long enough to heat sour cream. Serve over cooked noodles or rice.
Serves 6.

title: jell-o salad
directions: Dissolve jell-o in boiling water; add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Chill until partially set.
Add remaining ingredients and chill until firm.

title: chili sauce
directions: Saute onion in vegetable oil until tender. Add tomato sauce, 1 can water and ground beef all at once. Cook slowly until beef crumbles. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Turn heat down and let sauce simmer for 1 hour. Add more water to make sauce thinner, if you like.
Delicious used with hot dogs and hamburgers.

title: easy crock-pot mexican chili
directions: Brown meat with chopped onions and drain.
Put meat and onions in a crock-pot.
Open the can of whole tomatoes.
Grab one with your hand and stick your hand deep into an empty bowl.
Smash the tomato with your fingers (fun, but they squirt!).
Smash all the tomatoes and add to crock-pot.
Do not add juice.
Add all other ingredients to crockpot.
Cook on low for 3 to 4 hours or longer. Start it in the morning and eat it when you get home for dinner. Serve with Frito Scoops or saltines.

title: brown bread
directions: Boil the raisins, water and soda 2 minutes and cool.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients.

title: brown sugar confections
directions: Beat egg whites to a stiff froth. Continue beating and adding sugar gradually. When all sugar has been incorporated, sift the flour and salt over egg white mixture and fold in completely. Fold in nuts. Drop by spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet at least 2 inches apart. Bake in a 325° oven about 15 minutes.

title: hot ham
directions: Line pan with foil allowing enough extra to wrap around ham. Cover bottom
of
pan
with
garlic
salt.	Skin ham and insert green
chili
peppers (from pepper sauce bottles) about every 2 to 3-inches
apart all around ham.
Put ham in pan and cover with garlic
salt.
Ham	and
pan
should
be white with salt.
Slice a medium
onion
and place on top of ham.
Cover with foil and bake at 250° for 12 hours.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Add bread and let soak 5 minutes.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Mix butter, salt and sugar.
Pour into eggs and mix. Add vanilla, raisins, bread and milk.
Blend.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Set dish in another pan with 1 to 2 inches water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: fruit delight
directions: Defrost fruit and add brandy.
Marinate for at least 1 hour. Spoon into large glasses.
Pour champagne over fruit at the table. Yields 6 servings.

title: easy brownies
directions: Mix in order as given, mixing by hand thoroughly.
Bake in a 10 x 15-inch oiled jelly roll pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs; add cake mix and beat well.
Add pie filling.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: gazpacho dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate
8 hours before serving.
Serve with tortilla chips, corn chips or crackers.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir in buttermilk; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, cut butter with flour and yeast mixture.
Turn out onto floured board; knead lightly.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter. Place on greased pan; let rise in a warm place about 1 1/2 hours. Bake at 450° for about 10 minutes.

title: taco torte
directions: Spread the bean dip evenly on tray.
Combine the sour cream, mayonnaise, taco seasoning, garlic salt, lemon juice and black pepper.
Stir until mixed and spread on bean dip.
Top with the remaining ingredients.
Serve with tortilla or nacho chips.

title: cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs, cocoa, sugar and butter.
Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crust.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients in order listed; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool completely, cut into bars.

title: crispy potato wedges
directions: Place potatoes in a large bowl;
add cold water to cover. let stand for 15 minutes.

title: alligator cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in double boiler.
Add fruit juice, water and egg.
Place over rapidly boiling water and cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add butter and orange rind.
Cool.
Spread between cake layers.

title: potato deluxe
directions: In a 9 x 13 baking pan, mix thawed hash browns, chopped onion, soup, sour cream, 1 stick melted margarine, cheese, and salt. Top with corn flake crumbs and second stick of melted margarine. Bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: soupette salad(pasta fruit salad)
directions: Cook pasta as directed.
Drain and cool. Drain and cut up the cherries.
Drain and save the juice from the pineapple and oranges.
Mix pineapple and orange juices, sugar, eggs, flour and salt together and cook until thick.
Cool, then add to the pasta. The next day, add fruits and Cool Whip.
Makes a big bowl.

title: sweet potato apple salad
directions: In a large saucepan, cook sweet potatoes in boiling water until just tender, about 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Meanwhile, in a jar with a tight-fitting lid, combine the next nine ingredients; shake well.
Peel potatoes; cut in half lengthwise, then into 1/2-inch slices.
In a 4-quart bowl, layer a fourth of the sweet potatoes, apples and onions; drizzle with a fourth of the salad dressing.
Repeat layers three times.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.
Toss before serving.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: In medium saucepan, stir together rice and water.
Heat to boiling, stirring once or twice.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes without removing cover or stirring.
All water should be absorbed.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: chocolate zucchini pound cake
directions: Mix oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in 3 eggs.
Next add zucchini, peel and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool 15 minutes in pan.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Let cool.
Fold in 2 cups whipped topping. Chill.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: glaze
directions: Stir sugar and cornstarch together.
Gradually add water and berries. Cook over medium heat. Stir constantly until mixture thickens and boils. Boil and stir 1 minute. Cool.

title: earthquake cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer pecans and coconut.
Add cake mix as directed.
In separate bowl, cream together cream cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla.
Drop by spoonful over batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll and cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon.
Add vinegar and sugar to drippings.
Pour over cooked, peeled and sliced potatoes.
Heat in oven until warm, turning gently several times.
Just before serving, crumble cooked bacon over potatoes and heat about 5 minutes.

title: peanut-marshmallow bars
directions: Mix first three ingredients
and press into a 9 x 13 cake pan.
Bake 12 - 18 minutes at 350° or until golden.
Remove from oven and cover with miniature marshmallows.
Return to oven until they puff up. Remove and let cool.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Pour tomato sauce into oblong pan, 13 x 9-inch.
Add water and seasonings.
Mix.
Brown hamburger, onions, green pepper and celery.
Add to sauce.
Add macaroni and cheeses.
Mix well.
Top with pepperoni, ham, olives, whatever you wish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: grape salad
directions: Cut grapes in half.
Mix cream cheese and pineapple juice with mixer until a smooth consistency.
Pour over grapes and add pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: chocolate chip bran cookies
directions: Stir together flour, soda and salt.
In large mixing bowl, beat margarine, shortening, granulated sugar and brown sugar until well combined.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in Bran Flakes and chocolate morsels.
Drop by level measuring tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Bake in oven at 350° about 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Let cool about one minute before removing from baking sheets.
Place on wire racks.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: sandwich boats espanol
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Combine mayo, catsup and spices, stirring well.
Add mayo mixture to bean mixture, stirring to mix.

title: beef patties and gravy
directions: Make
the
ground
meat into small patties.
In a small amount of
Crisco
oil
brown the patties.
Add the gravy mix with
the right amount of water, as to the instructions on the mix package. Add salt, garlic, parsley and black pepper.
Let this
simmer until
a good gravy texture.
Serve over already cooked Water Maid rice.

title: chicken quesadillas(prep time: 15 minutes. cook time: 8 minutes.)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Chop chicken and jalapeno pepper with Food Chopper; set aside.
Combine chicken, pepper, soup and 1/2 cup cheese in Batter Bowl.
Top half of each tortilla with 1/4 cup soup mixture.
Spread to within 1/2-inch of edge with Super Scraper. Moisten edges of tortillas with water using Pastry Brush.
Fold over and press edges together.
Place tortillas on 15-inch Baking Stone.
Bake 8 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cut into wedges using Pizza Cutter.
Garnish serving plate with tomato, jalapeno pepper slices and cilantro.
Serve with salsa and sour cream.
Serve with Mini-Serving Spatula.
Serves 8 quesadillas or 32 appetizers.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Beat egg yolks and water lightly.
Gradually add chocolate, beating rapidly.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not too dry.
Gradually add sugar, beating until glossy.
Fold in chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Pile lightly into small sherbet glasses and chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: no-weep meringue
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until thick.
Beat egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar to a thick froth.
Add cooled mixture.
Beat until thick peaks form.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pasta with tomato and garlic
directions: Saute olive oil and minced garlic over low heat.
Do not brown!
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Lower heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add salt or additional garlic to taste.
Pour over favorite pasta and enjoy!

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Wash eggplant and cut in cubes.
Boil 3 minutes or until tender; drain.
Combine ingredients.
Place in baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbles. Place cheese slices on top.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all together onion soup, beef soup, melted margarine and raw rice and place either meat (chicken or hamburger balls or pork chops) on top.
Bake in oven at about 300° to 350° for 1 hour or little more until done.

title: italian meat balls
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
With wet hands, form into about 16 balls (mixture will be quite soft).
Brown slowly in hot oil, shaking pan frequently to keep balls round.
Blend tomato paste with remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat balls.
Cover and simmer one hour.
Serves 4.

title: rev. kalb's salad dressing
directions: Add milk to Miracle Whip to consistency wanted.
Add sweet pickle juice to taste.
Add sugar to taste.
Serve over any lettuce salad.

title: applesauce cake 2
directions: Mix chopped nuts and raisins with one cup of flour.
Mix all other ingredients with remaining 2 cups of flour, then fold in nuts and raisins.
Cook at 350° to 375° about 45 minutes.

title: chicken continental
directions: Dredge chicken in flour.
Saute in butter until golden brown. Mix soup, onion, parsley, salt, thyme and celery flakes in saucepan.
Stir in water.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly. Pour into a shallow, 2-quart casserole.
Reserve 1/3 cup of the soup mixture.
Pour remaining mixture into rice.
Top with chicken.
Pour remaining soup mixture over chicken.
Cover.

title: 4 layer torte
directions: Mix oleo, flour and nuts.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 13 minutes.
Cool well.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar until fluffy; fold in 2 cups Cool Whip and spread on cooled crust.
Beat milk and pudding mix together (about 3 minutes).
Spread on cream cheese layer.
Spread with additional Cool Whip and chill well before serving.
(Use fat-free cream cheese and lite Cool Whip to save fat grams!)

title: black forest dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple in
greased
9 x 13-inch cake pan; add pie filling and
sprinkle
cake
mix
over
top.
Add
pecans. Combine melted butter and juice; drizzle over mix.	Bake 35 to 40 minutes. Serve with topping.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken pieces with salt, pepper and garlic.
Place in baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients in bowl.
Pour over chicken and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
(This can be grilled.)

title: zucchini bread
directions: In blender, mix zucchini, oil and eggs.
Sift flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir in zucchini mixture. Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in two greased and floured loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour.

title: crunchy chicken salad
directions: Chop up vegetables and add water chestnuts.
Add chicken, vinegar and spices to taste.
Mix all together.
Makes a great lunch.

title: chicken-potato balls
directions: Mix together chicken, potatoes, milk, 1/3 cup of crumbs, 1/4 cup margarine, onion salt, pepper and rosemary.
Roll mixture by teaspoonfuls into balls.
Dip balls in remaining margarine.
Coat with remaining bread crumbs.
Place balls on baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes or until hot.

title: south of the border slaw
directions: In small skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add cumin seed and cook, stirring constantly, until lightly toasted and fragrant, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add lime juice, vinegar, sugar and salt.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Place sherbet in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale.
Yields 48 (4 ounce) cups.

title: hamburg and rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and onions.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil on High heat for 2 minutes.
Add soda; pour over popped popcorn.
Shake well in a brown paper bag.
Microwave on High at 1 minute intervals for a total of 3 minutes, shaking between minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Put in meat loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Can be made ahead and frozen until ready to bake.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix top 5 ingredients at high speed.
Mix in remaining ingredients on low speed.
Cook 70 to 80 minutes.

title: cheese ball or log
directions: Take cheese out of fridge; let stand to room temperature. Shape into log or ball as desired.
Mix together nuts, chili powder and garlic salt.
Sprinkle all of this on sheet of foil. Roll cheese (ball or log) in this back and forth until completely covered.
Place on plate; cover with plastic wrap or foil and refrigerate.
Slice when ready to serve.
Good with Hi Ho crackers or for less calories, use wheat crackers.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Slice apples and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Mix batter thoroughly and pour over apples.
Pour over the batter 3/4 cup sugar mixed with 1/2 cup water.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: indian bannock bread
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder; stir well.
Add oil/lard and water/milk to dry ingredients; stir well.
When dough becomes too stiff to stir, mix with hands.
Sprinkle flour on counter; knead until dough is smooth.
Shape dough into a flat, round cake about 1-inch thick.
Prick with fork 25 times.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake bannock for 20 minutes until golden brown.
Eat warm.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, and refrigerate overnight in an extra large salad or tupperware bowl.
Add shredded lettuce, olives, tomato and cheese. Before serving, add dressing and mix; then add Doritos and mix.
Great for carry-in lunches or dinners.

title: georgia bell peach salad
directions: Drain all fruit and use juice for liquid.
With a fork, mix cream cheese with dry gelatin until it is a smooth paste.
Then slowly add 1 cup boiling juice.
Gradually add rest of juice (or water if not enough juice). Mix well.
Let stay in refrigerator until it begins to thicken.
Cut up peaches and mandarin oranges into small pieces.
Add fruit to thickened jello.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in mold.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill 30 minutes or more.
Drop by heaping tablespoon onto hot skillet.
Fry until golden brown. Serve on hamburger buns with lettuce and tomato.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Heat crushed pineapple to boiling.
Add Jell-O; stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add cottage cheese and nuts.
Pour into bowl. Refrigerate until set.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients thoroughly.
Place in a bowl in the refrigerator to chill.
When chilled, form in desired shape and roll in 3/4 cup chopped nuts.

title: apple salad
directions: Stir cooled dressing into apple mixture.
Add some whole nuts over top.
Red or Yellow Delicious or Grime's Golden apples are best.

title: leeks and bacon
directions: Clean the leeks thoroughly as they can be gritty.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and drain.
Wrap a rasher of bacon round each leek.
Cook slowly in a buttered dish until done.
Cover with cheese sauce; sprinkle with grated cheese on top and brown under grill.
Serve with jacket potatoes.

title: puffatjes
directions: Drop by tablespoons into deep fat fryer and fry until brown.

title: chess bars
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg and butter. Pat into a 9 X 13 inch pan.
Mix cream cheese until creamy.
Add 2 eggs until well mixed and add powder sugar.

title: easy cheese potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except 1/2 cup Colby cheese; mix well.
Turn into buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Top with remaining cheese; bake 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: cheesy cheddar potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients, breaking up potatoes with spoon if necessary.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Bake for 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: blueberry yum-yum
directions: Mix Dream Whip by package directions. Mix cream cheese and sugar together.
Fold into Dream Whip mixture.
Put 1/2 mixture into crust.
Spread blueberries on top of this.
Put rest of cream mixture on top of blueberries.

title: old fashioned cake donuts
directions: Mix sugar, egg, milk and vanilla; add enough self-rising flour to make a stiff dough.
Roll out and cut.
Drop into hot oil, fry until golden brown.
Drop into paper bag with powdered sugar or top with icing or fruit.

title: spanish corn pie
directions: Drain tamales, reserve liquid.
Mash tamales and combine with drained corn.
Saute meat, onion and celery until meat is crumbly; stir in tomato paste.
Add enough water to tamale liquid to make 2/3 cup, pour in, season.
In a greased 1 1/2 quart casserole, arrange alternate layers of tomato and corn mixture and meat mixture.
Pitted black olives may be added.
Insert tip of bay leaf in each end of casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaves before serving.
Serves 6.

title: creek bank potatoes
directions: Put 1 pound bacon in
bottom
of
12-inch
Dutch
oven. Cover bacon with potato slices.
Place
cheese
to cover potatoes. Layer onion on cheese.
Cover with last pound of bacon. Cook 45 minutes with 12 coals on
top
and 10 coals on bottom. Drain off grease and serve.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cookie mix according to package directions.
Spread mix in pizza pan.
Bake according to package; let cool.
Mix the cream cheese, whipped topping and sugar; spread over cookie pizza. Arrange fruit on top.
Makes 8 servings.

title: granny cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; set aside.
Beat eggs; add pineapple, then dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan which has been greased and floured.
Mix brown sugar and nutmeats together; sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: kathy's frozen delight
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar and set aside. Mix remaining ingredients together, then
stir in the cream cheese and sugar mixture. Spread into a long Tupperware container and freeze. Remove from freezer a few minutes before serving.

title: cubed steak deluxe
directions: Coat steaks with flour, seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown in oil, then remove from pan.
Mix 1 to 2 tablespoons of flour with drippings.
Dissolve bouillon in cup of water and add to flour mixture in pan.
Add enough milk to make a thin gravy.
Add cooking sherry and stir well.
Return steak to gravy.
Top with slices of onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Cover tightly and simmer approximately 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: bigos (hunter's stew)
directions: In Dutch oven, cook salt pork.
Remove cracklings and set aside.
Add kielbasi; brown and set aside.

title: caramel pull-aparts
directions: Arrange frozen rolls in a single layer in an angel food pan. Mix brown sugar and dry pudding mix together.
Pour melted butter over rolls and sprinkle with pudding/sugar mixture.
Top with nuts.
Cover and let rise at room temperature 10 to 12 hours, or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
To serve, slice or pull apart.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine pork and beans, brown sugar, mustard, catsup, onion and Worcestershire and mix well.
Pour into 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with bacon pieces.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken chop suey
directions: Brown chicken in melted fat in a large frying pan, stirring constantly 5 or 6 minutes.
Add celery and onion in water or broth.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add mushroom soup; cover and let simmer.
Blend cornstarch with cold water to make a paste and stir into the cooking mixture.
Continue to cook and stir 10 minutes.
Add salt, sugar, soy sauce, pepper and paprika.
Heat for 3 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Add milk gradually to cream cheese
until
smooth.
Add dry pudding mix.
When it starts to thicken,
pour
into
pie shell. Combine sugar, butter and crumbs and
sprinkle
on top or top with Cool Whip or whipped cream. Refrigerate.

title: andy's wild game meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the first 7 ingredients and knead to ensure that they are evenly mixed.
At this point the mixture should be somewhat sticky.
Add barbeque sauce last, a little at a time, to moisten the meatloaf.
Grease a loaf pan and spread the meatloaf evenly.
Sprinkle with parsley.
After the meatloaf bakes about 35 minutes, check to see if it is cooked to your liking.
Do not overcook.
Good with Beaujolais or Cabernet wine.

title: peach crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease baking dish.
Mix flour and sugar together.
Add the butter or margarine.
Mix together with a fork or pastry blender until mixture looks crumbly.
Open the peaches; drain off all the liquid.
Spread drained fruit evenly in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle the crumb mixture evenly on top of the fruit.
Bake for about 30 to 40 minutes.
The topping should be golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Grease pan with butter. Bake at 350° for approximately 2 hours or until fully cooked. Don't forget the gravy!

title: enchilada pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice onions and peppers.

Drain tomatoes. Cook beef in a large frying pan. Remove with a slotted spoon. Add onions, peppers, garlic, salt and pepper to the same pan you cooked the meat in and cook until soft, about 15 minutes. Remove vegetables with a slotted spoon and return meat to pan. Drain tomatoes and add vinegar, cumin, oregano, salt and pepper. Break up tomatoes before adding to pan. Simmer for 10 minutes. Line bottom and sides of a 2-quart baking dish with 4 tortillas. Put in half of the meat mixture and layer it with the onion mixture. Cover with 2 tortillas and repeat layers of meat and onion mixtures.
Top with cheeses and sprinkle with jalapeno peppers (if desired). Cover loosely with foil and bake 20 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.
Serve.

title: cocktail cake
directions: Combine sugar, milk and oleo.
Boil icing mixture 2 minutes. Add coconut.
Pour over cake while hot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Drain fruit cocktail well.
Put in food processor with cream cheese and instant pudding.
Mix well.
Dump out in bowl of chopped pecans and roll.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Wash strawberries and remove stems, then cut in half and crush in small amounts.
Place berries in pan, then add pectin and butter.
Bring to a rolling boil over high heat, while stirring constantly.
Quickly, add sugar and bring to boil again.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and skim off foam with a large metal spoon.
Fill jar to 1/4-inch from top of jar.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together well the shortening, eggs and sugar.
Add soda, flour, cream of tartar and salt.
Mix together well.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Roll into balls the size of walnut or larger if desired. Then roll balls into a mixture of equal parts sugar and cinnamon. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 400° oven.
Bake until brown but still soft.
These cookies puff up first, but flatten out with crinkled tops.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover and freeze in squares.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.
Keeps for 2 to 3 months. May be frozen in paper cups in muffin tin.
Great for a luncheon served with chicken salad, date-nut cream cheese sandwich and cheese straws.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix all except carrots.
Put carrots in mixture.
Marinate in refrigerator for 12 hours.

title: chicken scampi
directions: Stir-fry chicken pieces in 2 tablespoons oil. Remove from pan. Add broccoli and stir-fry for 4 minutes. Add onion and green pepper; stir-fry 5 additional minutes.
Return chicken to pan and cook 5 minutes more. Sprinkle with lemon juice, salt and pepper. Cook linguine according to package directions. Drain.
Place on serving dish. Top with chicken and vegetables.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: infallible rice
directions: Saute	onion
in
butter
until
transparent.	Combine onion, rice and broth.
Bring to a boil on top of range.
Pour into casserole and cover.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: el postre de pan y vino(from honduras)
directions: In shallow dish, combine eggs and 1/4 cup wine.
Dip bread slices in egg mixture.
In a 10-inch skillet cook bread in hot butter on both sides until golden brown.
Remove bread and set aside.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Mix together in a small heated saucepan the margarine, mustard, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce and onion. Brush this mixture on bottom half of the rolls.
Sprinkle the ham and cheese over mixture. Add the top half of the rolls.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted (20 to 25 minutes) with foil on top.

title: venison
directions: Marinate meat 12 hours in Coke, pour off.
Place bacon in roaster.
Add meat, onions and other ingredients.
Cook 2 to 3 hours in 350° oven.

title: breakfast or brunch casserole
directions: Brown the sausage and drain. Place in casserole dish and spread sour cream on top.
Prepare eggs as if to scramble.
Pour on top of sour cream. Top entire casserole with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until eggs are cooked.

title: baked beans
directions: Put all ingredients but bacon in big baking pan. Stir, then adjust sorghum, Worcestershire and mustard to taste.
Add bacon pieces. Stir them in. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until cooked down but not dry.

title: holly cookies
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows in a large saucepan.
Add food coloring.
Stir in cornflakes.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper. Put 2 or 3 red hots in the middle to look like berries.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Core, rinse and drain lettuce.
In a bowl toss apple with lemon juice.
Stir in celery, nuts, raisins, grapes and kiwi fruit.

title: buttermilk spice cake
directions: Heat oven
to
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan. Measure
all
ingredients
into
large mixing bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed.
Pour into pan (or pans).	May
use
round
cake
pans.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until
wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes.
Cut
cake
in
diamond
shapes.
Mix 1/3 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon and sprinkle over cake.
Heat 1 cup maple flavored syrup and pour over cake.	Let stand a few minutes. Serve warm or cold.

title: play dough
directions: In a large bowl, mix the ingredients (except food colorings) .
Knead until a large ball is formed with hands.
Separate and add a lot of food coloring. Store in Ziploc or Tupperware.

title: oriental green beans
directions: In a large pot of rapidly boiling water, cook green beans until just tender, 4-5 minutes.
While beans are cooking, in a small bowl combine soy sauce, oil, and sugar; set aside.
Drain beans; set aside.
Spray wok or 10 inch skillet with nonstick cooking spray; place over medium-high heat.
Add garlic; cook, stirring constantly, until softened, 20-30 seconds.
Add green beans; cook, stirring and turning constantly, until well coated, about 2 minutes.
Add soy sauce mixture; continue to stir and turn until most of the liquid is absorbed, 1-2 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in greased casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake 15 more minutes. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: marinated green beans
directions: Wash beans.
Remove ends and strings.
Cook whole beans covered in a small amount of boiling water for 20 to 30 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain well.
Mix together all other ingredients except onion.
Combine beans and onion together.
Pour marinade over vegetables.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: grandma bickhart's peanut butter fudge
directions: Put jar of peanut butter and pint of Marshmallow Creme in a bowl.
Set aside.
Put sugar with milk in saucepan and boil 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and pour into peanut butter and marshmallow.
Mix well and pour into well-buttered pan.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening. Add milk and knead until dough is soft.
Bake in ungreased pan for 12 - 15 minutes at 450 degrees.

title: red beet and horseradish relish
directions: Chop drained red beets in blender.
Add remaining ingredients. Blend. Chill until next day.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in whole egg and egg yolk.
Sift flour and soda with 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg.
Mix into batter.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Drop from a teaspoon 2-inches apart onto a buttered cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
This recipe makes 5 dozen great Christmas cookies.

title: banana-walnut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Blend in bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Stir this into banana mixture.
Alternate with buttermilk.
Add nuts and mix well. Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: ham and egg shortcake
directions: Mix soup and milk and heat.
Add ham and eggs.
Pour this mixture over biscuits.

title: chicken pie
directions: Steam
chicken	until tender.
Steam potatoes, peas and carrots.
Mix
all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly and golden.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix cooked, cubed chicken with soup and sour cream.
Cover with crushed crackers.
Pour melted butter over the top.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: graham cracker pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a small mixing bowl.
Press into an 8-inch pie plate and bake in a preheated 375° oven for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add chopped nuts and mix.
Cream butter; add sugar gradually and continue creaming until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well after each addition.
Add flour mixture and blend lightly.
Pour batter into a greased pan (10 x 3 1/2 x 2 3/4-inch) and allow to stand 20 minutes.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for about 70 minutes. Yield:
1 loaf.

title: "philly" cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing, mixing until well blended.
Add rest of ingredients and shape into a ball.
Chill well before serving.
Pimento pepper pieces, parsley or paprika can be put on top of cheese ball for added color.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: frito salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat, drain grease.
Let cool while chopping onion, lettuce, radishes, pickles and tomatoes.
Drain kidney beans.
Add all ingredients except Fritos and dressing.
Mix well. Top over Fritos and add dressing on top.
You can add or subtract vegetables to taste.
You can also substitute Ranch dressing or any kind of salad dressing.

title: butterscotch morsels
directions: Melt morsels over water or very low heat. Stir until smooth. Add noodles and nuts.
Mix to coat.
Spoon onto waxed paper and let cool. Store in tight container.

title: tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add onion, can of mushrooms, Worcestershire sauce and seasoning salt.
Cook until done.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, can of Cheddar cheese and water together, then add to hamburger mixture.
Place in long pan or glass dish. Add grated cheese on top, then layer the top with potato tots. Cook on 350° until potatoes are done, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: grandma's fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix together. Serve with fresh fruit.
Especially good with strawberries, watermelon, pineapple and grapes!!

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Mix ground beef and pepper 6 to 8 minutes.
Drain.
Mix in soup mix, chili powder, tomato sauce, tomato paste, olives and water.
Microwave 5 minutes.
Place 2 tortillas in 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Top with half meat mix and half both cheeses. Repeat.
Microwave 5 minutes.
Rotate.
Microwave 5 minutes.
Top with shredded lettuce, sour cream and tomato.

title: bread
directions: Scald milk with butter, salt and sugar.
Add warm water and softened yeast.
Mix with flour and knead for ten minutes on floured board.
Kneading is the secret of good bread.
Replace in bowl, cover and allow to rise for two hours in a warm place.
Turn the dough over and punch down.
Let rise one hour and shape into loaves.
Place in greased loaf pan and allow to rise double in size.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chow chow pancakes
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together the eggs, potatoes, zucchini, carrots, onion, peppers, flour, poultry seasoning and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Spoon 1/4 cup of mixture onto a hot, oiled griddle; flatten with a spatula.
Repeat with remaining batter.
(Good for when the zucchini takes over the garden.)

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and chill at least one hour before serving.
Use as dip or use for ham rolls.

title: chocolate iced brownies
directions: Mix the butter, cocoa, eggs and sugar.
Add flour, salt, pecans and vanilla.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
While hot, put marshmallows on top.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix all together and put in ice cream freezer.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, powdered sugar and butter.
Press in bottom and on sides of 9-inch plate to make a crumb crust.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all and place in casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soup.
Form into balls; place in casserole.
Cover with soup.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes, then cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sausage, chili and cheese tartlets(makes 24)
directions: Cook sausage in heavy large skillet over medium-high heat until no longer pink, breaking up with fork.
Drain off fat.
Add salsa, cheeses and green chilies to skillet; simmer until mixture thickens, about 5 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: cooking of rhubarb
directions: Rhubarb should not be boiled!
Dice in 1/4 inch lengths.
Add 1 cup sugar for tart taste or 2 cups for sweet taste.
Let stand overnight.
Bring to boil, remove from heat and cover.
When cool, drain off excess juice.
(This juice may be mixed with equal parts of orange juice, delicious!)

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Stir in zucchini, pineapple, flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, nuts and raisins.
Blend well.
Pour into two greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening or margarine, sugar and vanilla. Add egg and milk; beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients; blend into creamed mixture.
Divide dough in half. Cover and chill at least 1 hour.

title: chocolate covered coconut balls
directions: Blend with mixer first two ingredients slowly until well blended.
Separately, mix together next 3 ingredients and then mix together with first two.
Form into small balls.
Makes 140 to 150.

title: chocolate mint flip
directions: Add cocoa malt to hot milk; stir until dissolved.
Add cold milk, salt and extracts.
Chill.
Just before serving, pour into shaker; add ice cream.
Shake until smooth and blended.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients to creamy; add rest (except kisses) and mix.
Roll into small ball and coat with sugar in bowl.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes, then place chocolate kisses on each.
Bake for another 2 minutes.

title: snapper smoothies
directions: Sprinkle fish in baking pan with onion salt, paprika and garlic salt.
Combine tomato juice, basil, parsley and lemon juice.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes.
Slowly pour over fish in pan.
Bake at 375° (medium oven) for 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Makes 2 servings.
This is a great favorite with our family.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions until tender.
Add cooked beans (pink or red), onion, soy sauce and sherry; mix gently.
Simmer, covered, 5 minutes or until all moisture is absorbed.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix all ingredients. Spread in dish.
Bake about 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch pieces.
Makes about 48 appetizers.

title: broccoli hot dish
directions: Mix together oil, soup, garlic salt, milk, eggs and onion. Cook rice and broccoli and mix together.
Add rest of the ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until brown.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients except chipped ham into saucepan. Bring to boil.
Continue boiling for 5 minutes.
Add 1 pound chipped ham and heat through.
Will keep well for a week in refrigerator.
Can also be frozen for later use.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add vanilla and beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour and the rest of the ingredients.
Make small balls and bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: beef 'n noodles
directions: Take 2 sirloin steaks, cut into chunks, put in pressure cooker with water.
Cook 25 minutes.
Cook 1 pack of egg noodles in with beef until noodles are done.
Take 3 packs of brown gravy mix and mix with beef and noodles just before noodles are done.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: stir-fry(pork or chicken)
directions: Heat wok or skillet over high heat.
Add oil, then add chicken or pork.
Stir-fry about 3 to 4 minutes or until no pink remains in center.
Stir in half of soy sauce.
Add all vegetables. Stir-fry until vegetables are crisp-tender, then add the rest of the soy sauce over vegetables and add oyster flavored sauce if you want to add more oyster flavor.
Have rice ready before vegetables are done.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven at 325° to 350°.
Cream sugars and butter and remainder of ingredients.
Bake 25 minutes (a little less if you like them gooey!).
Dress them up by using an icing decorator with peanut butter or chocolate icing.

title: oven herb chicken
directions: Dip pieces of chicken in butter mixture. Then dip in crushed cornflakes. Place in greased pan or dish.
Bake at 375° about 1 1/2 hours.
Don't turn.

title: nanci's salad
directions: Use a cold beater and bowl and whip cream to stiff peaks. Place in refrigerator.
Make jello with 1 cup boiling water only and cool to room temperature.
Drain pineapple with juice; add water to make 1 cup of juice.
Beat cream cheese until smooth. Add cooled jello slowly and pineapple juice.
Fold in pineapple chunks and cranberry sauce.
Lastly add and fold in whipped cream and walnuts.
Grease a jello mold and pour contents.
If extra, make a smaller mold.
Best when made 24 hours ahead.
May be used as a dessert or with chicken or turkey.

title: shrimp and corn soup
directions: Make a roux with oil and flour.
When roux is golden brown, add onions.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add bell pepper, shrimp, parsley, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add whole tomatoes, Ro-Tel, corn and 1 cup of water.
Simmer at least 1 hour, adding water gradually until desired consistency.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients, then pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cheddar chowder
directions: In a saucepan, combine milk and soup.
Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat, about 30 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Mix all together cake mix, pudding, eggs, milk and oil. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Makes 3 layers.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix cornstarch and seasonings.
Blend beet juice and vinegar into cornstarch mixture.
Bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Add beets.
Heat.

title: sweet and saucy chicken
directions: Mix salad dressing, soup mix and preserves.
Arrange chicken, which has been skinned and patted dry, in a large Pyrex dish or baking pan.
Spoon sauce over chicken and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pluckets(amish rolls)
directions: Add 1/3 cup sugar, butter and salt to scalded milk when lukewarm. Add dissolved yeast, eggs and flour.
Beat thoroughly. Cover and let rise until double. Stir down and let rise again until double.
Take 1 teaspoon of dough and dip in butter (melted).
Roll in mixture of the 1 cup sugar, nuts and cinnamon. Pile balls loosely in ungreased angel food pan.
Let rise 30 minutes. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and then at 350° for 30 minutes.
When baked, turn the pan upside down immediately. Serve warm.
The rolls will be stuck together and that's the way you serve them.
Everyone plucks his roll from the central supply. These can be reheated in the oven if wrapped in foil. They are also good when served cold. These are very good and different.

title: crispy caramel corn
directions: Boil together
brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt for 5 minutes, stirring
constantly.
Remove
from
heat
and add vanilla and soda.
Pour over
popcorn.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour. Stir evenly every 15 minutes.

title: tandori turkey
directions: Blend all ingredients, except turkey or chicken, well.
Pour over turkey breasts.
Cover both sides.
Cover; refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Grill until done.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on a large cookie sheet and pat together.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.

title: tomato with pasta
directions: Heat oil; add and saute all ingredients except the tomatoes and pasta.
Peel and chop tomatoes and add to the sauteed mixture. Cook pasta (amount desired) and serve with the sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese, if desired.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: flounder fillet in sauce
directions: Broil fish for about 3 minutes with lemon juice.
Combine all ingredients (soften margarine into liquid).
Spread all well mixed ingredients over fish and return to broiler 6 minutes.
Marinade should be golden.
Watch carefully.

title: cheese rounds
directions: Blend ingredients.
Divide into 2 balls.
Roll each ball into a long roll about 1-inch thick.
Wrap in wax paper and chill. Slice very thin.
Put pecan half on top, and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 100 rounds.

title: working mom's chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400° and spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam.
Place chicken, veggies, mushrooms and onion in dish.
In blender, mix remaining ingredients and pour over the chicken and vegetables.
Bake until knife in the center comes out clean, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: french onion soup(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Saute onions in butter until brown.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of flour and cook for 1 minute. Add 2 cans beef broth, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.

title: herbed chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Mix butter and seasonings; spread on chicken pieces.
Put in casserole.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine, mix with stuffing.
Grease casserole dish, 9 x 13-inches.
Place layer of stuffing and some turkey in bottom of dish.
Add 1 can cream of chicken soup and 1 can broth.
Add another layer of stuffing and layer of turkey.
Add 1 can cream of celery soup and 1 can broth.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: new orleans shrimp dip
directions: Stir all ingredients together; chill 1 hour.

title: beef and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Slice sirloin into thin strips.
Combine cornstarch and soy sauce in bowl; mix well.
Stir-fry garlic with salt in oil in skillet or wok.
Add beef.
Stir-fry for several minutes.
Remove beef; set aside.
Add broccoli, (undrained) mushrooms and broth. Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cook, covered for 2 minutes.
Add beef.
Heat to serving temperature.
Serve immediately with rice. Yield:
4 servings.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Simmer chicken breasts 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain, remove skin and bones, and cut chicken into 12 long strips.
Saute onion and garlic in margarine until tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, chilies, sugar, cumin, salt, oregano and basil.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, covered, 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Dip each tortilla into sauce to soften.
Place a strip of chicken and 2 tablespoons shredded cheese on each tortilla.
Roll up and place seam side down in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Blend sour cream into remaining sauce.
Pour over tortillas.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot sauce for wings
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat to a boil and simmer 15 minutes.
Baste wings or chicken as it cooks on the grill.

title: rex jelly
directions: Mix ingredients together and boil 6 to 8 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
Makes 5 pints.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute oleo, celery and onion.
Add 1/2 bread.
Saute until crisp.
Mix remainder of bread, soup and chicken.
Add sauteed ingredients.
Put into well-greased casserole.
Add 3/4 of can of evaporated milk over top.
(Don't mix.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop dried beef.
Add to soft cream cheese along with other ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Combine cake mix and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add vegetable oil and next 4 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed with an electric mixer for 6 minutes.
Stir in poppy seed.
Pour batter into a 10-cup Bundt pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Drizzle with Lemon Glaze and cool completely on wire rack.
Makes 24 servings.

title: ponsit
directions: Brown pork, onions, celery and garlic in oil.
Add chicken and shrimp.
Stir-fry for a few minutes.
Add cabbage, carrots and about 1/4 cup soy sauce.
Stir-fry until crisp tender.
While this is cooking soak thin rice sticks in warm water to cover.
Drain and combine with meat mixture, along with 1/2 to 1 cup hot chicken broth.
Let set covered for 30 minutes.
To reheat, stir-fry in a little oil.

title: cranberry meatballs(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine beef, corn flake crumbs, parsley, eggs, soy sauce, pepper, garlic powder, catsup and onion.
Blend well.
Form mixture into walnut-size balls.
Arrange in 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.

title: potatoes cooked with butter and cream
directions: Add just enough water to potatoes so you can see it.
Add butter; cook until tender, then add thickening made by combining flour with milk and cream.
Cook until thickened, then add salt and pepper to taste.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix orange juice according to directions on can.
Pour 1/3 of mixed juice into blender.
Add dry ingredients until mixed.
Pour in remaining juice.
Pour over ice cubes or crushed ice in parfait or iced tea glasses.

title: mushrooms with parsley and garlic(funghi triffolati)
directions: Clean,
wash
and
dry
mushrooms thoroughly.
Cut each mushroom
in
half and parboil for 2 minutes in boiling water. Drain
well.
Heat oil in large skillet and add garlic.
Saute garlic until very brown, discard garlic and add mushrooms, hot pepper,
salt
and
parsley.
Cook
over
high
heat
browning mushrooms
slightly, about 10 minutes.
Lower heat and cook an additional 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: weight watchers' strawberry milk shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and process until thick. Yields one (8 ounce) drink.

title: vegetable and cheese salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, parsley, basil and garlic.
Mix well. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly.

title: zucchini cakes(mock crab cakes)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into cakes.
Pat with plain bread crumbs or Italian and fry in skillet until brown on both sides. 1/4 cup Parmesan may be added also.

title: quick beef-and-vegetable soup
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven, over high heat, cook ground beef and onion until all pan juices evaporate and meat is well browned, stirring frequently.
Add stewed tomatoes and next 6 ingredients. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add frozen mixed vegetables; over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 10 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 12 cups or 6 main dish servings.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Separate the eggs.
Beat the whites.
To the beaten egg yolks, add sugar, condensed milk, evaporated milk, salt, vanilla and bananas.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour in freezer and add the whole milk to finish filling the freezer.
This makes 1 1/2 gallons of ice cream.

title: hopping john
directions: Dice the bacon and fry with the chopped onion.
Add to the peas, rice and water.
Cover and cook at low heat until the peas and rice are done.
Add seasoning.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery until clear in butter.
Mix together with remaining ingredients and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: magic french fudge
directions: In top of double boiler, melt chocolate chips over hot water; remove from heat.
Add milk, vanilla, salt and nuts.
Stir until smooth.
Turn out into waxed paper on cookie sheet.
Chill.
Cut in pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken in skim milk.
Put all dry ingredients in plastic bag.
Mix. Add chicken, 2 or 3 pieces at a time.
Shake to coat. Place on cookie sheet sprayed with oil and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: southern corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, eggs, sugar, butter, salt and pepper.
Put in a baking dish.
Pour milk over corn.
Place dish in a pan with an inch of water.
Bake at 325° about 45 minutes or until firm. Serves 4 to 6.

title: dad's drink
directions: Add ingredients in 8-ounce glass and stir vigorously.
Great for that morning after feeling before coffee.

title: hot pineapple
directions: Place pineapple in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar and flour together and sprinkle over pineapple.
Then, sprinkle the cheese over it and top with crushed crackers.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Put soup, sour cream, chicken and chillies together and mix well.
Use 9 x 13-inch dish or larger dish.
Layer chicken mixture with tortillas, starting with mixture.
(Tearing the tortillas in smaller pieces makes serving easier.)
Top with grated cheese, enough to cover top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for about twenty minutes.

title: nabisco strawberry delight
directions: Roll out wafers and line buttered 8-inch square pan with 1/2 of the crumbs.
Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat mixture until fluffy.
Spread mixture over crumbs.
Add layer of berries.
Spread whipping cream over berries and top with remaining crumbs.
Chill thoroughly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and save 3 cups of the broth.
Pull chicken off bone and mix with broth, stuffing and soup.
Put in a casserole dish with lid or cover it.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncover. Bake for 20 minutes or until top is brown.

title: lasagna(serves 8)
directions: Cook meat in 5-quart pan over medium heat.
Saute sausage, beef, onion and garlic, stirring frequently, until browned.
Add sugar, 1 tablespoon salt, basil, fennel, pepper and half of the parsley.
Mix. Add tomatoes, paste and 1/2 cup water, mashing tomatoes.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, until thick (1 1/2 hours).

title: date nut balls
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and cook until dates dissolve. Mix the pecans, Rice Krispies and vanilla; add to the other ingredients.
Roll into balls in xxxx sugar.
Ready to eat.

title: sherry pie
directions: Soak marshmallows in wine until they melt.
Beat.
Beat Dream whip as directed.
omit vanilla.
Add to marshmallow mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into pie shell and chill.
You may want to add a few drops of red food coloring.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix together half can milk, 3/4 cup butter and cake mix. Pour half the mixture into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
In a pot, melt caramels and rest of milk.
Spread over cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans.
Spoon rest of batter over top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tofu pie
directions: Drain tofu and squeeze out water.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Blend dissolved jello and tofu in blender.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate until firm.
Top with Cool Whip.
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix filling ingredients in order given. Pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool; serve garnished with whipped topping.

title: icebox cucumbers
directions: In saucepan, bring vinegar, sugar and salt to rolling boil. Place cucumbers and onions in large bowl.
Pour liquid over cucumber mixture.
Cool in icebox.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook all ingredients except soda for 5 minutes on top of stove.
Add soda.
Pour over popped popcorn and mix.
Put in large flat pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on pizza pan; cook as directed.
Mix cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Spread over cooked cookies. Slice and arrange fruit on top.
Mix orange juice, sugar, water and cornstarch.
Cook until thick and pour over fruit.
Let cool and slice.

title: coconut pie
directions: Remove 3 oz of frozen coconut from freezer. Bake pie crust according to directions on pkg. Let cool. Pour 2 c of milk in pot. Place on low heat. Separate 3 eggs. Place whites in a bowl. Beat egg yolks. Add sugar and flour. Mix. Add egg yolk mixture to warm milk. Cook on medium heat until it thickens. Add coconut. Cook on low heat until coconut has thawed. Remove from heat. Add vanilla. Pour into baked pie crust. Beat egg whites until fluffy. Add 1/4 cup of sugar and a sprinkle of cream of tartar. Beat about 30 seconds. Pour on top of pie. Bake at 400 degrees until meringue is brown.

title: bad jack's pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk in large microwavable bowl.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes or until mixture comes to full boil, stirring after every 2 minutes.
Cooking time is approximate.
Let cool about 5 minutes.

title: pecan sticky buns(microwave)
directions: In a small bowl, combine sugar, pecans, and cinnamon.
Unroll the 2 sections of dough, but do not separate.
On each long rectangle, spoon 1 teaspoon margarine and 1 tablespoon pecan mixture; re-roll. cut each into quarters, forming 8 buns.
Dip each bun into butter and then into pecan mixture.
In 8-inch round baking dish, arrange biscuits in ring.
Sprinkle with remaining pecan mixture.
Heat at Medium in microwave oven for 4 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes.
Yields 8 buns.

title: chicken pie
directions: Spray dish with Pam.
Crumble chicken into bottom of dish. Add drained vegetables and sliced egg.
Mix soups and chicken broth and pour over chicken and vegetables.
Melt butter and into separate bowl mix butter and flour together to make a paste.
Add milk and stir with wire whisk.
Pour over vegetables and broth. Do not stir.
Bake at 375° until crust is golden brown.

title: open crab sandwiches
directions: Let the butter and cheese soften to room temperature.
Mix together with mayonnaise, garlic, seasoned salt and crabmeat. Spread on buns.
Freeze after wrapping in Saran Wrap separately, then place in tight container.
When ready to use, remove from freezer and let set about 10 minutes.
Then place under broiler 3 or 4 minutes or until bubbly.

title: fresh vegetable marinade
directions: Remove flowerets from broccoli and cut into bite size pieces (reserve stalks for another use).
Combine all vegetables.
Toss lightly to mix.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well and pour over vegetables.
Chill at least 3 hours or overnight.
Yields 16 servings.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Save 1/4 cup of crumbs.
Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add Ritz cracker crumbs and pat to form a crust.
Mix ice cream until softened.
Add milk and pudding and beat only two minutes.
Pour over crust.
Refrigerate until firm; top with Cool Whip and remaining 1/4 cup of Ritz cracker crumbs.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine in a casserole; bake and serve.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Drain and cool macaroni.
Combine macaroni with all other ingredients.
For extra flavor, try adding 1/4 cup French dressing.
Serves 6.

title: beef stew
directions: Simmer meat in stock until tender.
Add vegetables and spices. Cook until done.
Mix some broth and flour to thicken.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sugar, then sprinkle sugar over top of mixture.
Cover; refrigerate overnight for best flavor, but may be served sooner.
Mix well before serving.

title: yellow cake
directions: Stir flour, sugar and shortening together.
Add milk and vanilla; beat vigorously for 3 minutes, scraping bowl frequently. Add unbeaten eggs; continue beating 2 minutes.
Bake in 2 (8 or 9-inch) greased and floured baking pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: squash dressing
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar (1 cup), flour and salt well.
Add milk; add beaten egg yolks.
Add chocolate syrup.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell. Top with meringue.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add 1/4 cup sugar.

title: apple butter (spiced)
directions: Core and slice apple, but do not peel.
Add only enough water to cook apples until soft.
Press through fine sieve and measure. Combine all ingredients.
Cook until mixture remains in a smooth mass when a little is cooled (about 1 1/2 hours, boiling).
During cooking, stir frequently to prevent burning.
Pour into sterilized jar and seal while hot.

title: tim's marinating magic
directions: Mix ingredients. Pour over beef or steaks and let marinate 2 to 3 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: mom's pecan snowballs
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except confectioners sugar.
With hands, mix until thoroughly blended. Refrigerate dough 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Form dough into 1/4-inch balls.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until set but not brown.
Let stand 1 minute. Remove to wire rack. Cool partially.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm. Cool completely.
Just before serving, re-roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes about 20.
May double recipe; dough keeps in refrigerator for up to a week.

title: roman holiday bake
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Cook sausage and onion with oregano until done.
Pour off fat.
Add soups and water.
Chill overnight.

title: picadillo
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add garlic, onion, cumin, oregano and bell pepper.
Drain fat.
Add tomato sauce and two cans.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add bay leaf and dash of sherry.
Simmer an additional half hour.
Add olives last 15 minutes.
Serve with warmed corn tortilla chips, homemade black beans and white rice.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: In a covered saucepan, cook potatoes in boiling water for 20 to 25 minutes or until just tender; drain well.
Peel and cube potatoes.

title: banana salad
directions: Combine egg, sugar, and juice in a saucepan.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cut bananas into medium slices.
Pour dressing over bananas; add nuts.
Mix well and chill before serving.

title: quick nut fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients in top pan of double boiler.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: wonder fudge
directions: Measure margarine or butter, chocolate morsels, corn syrup and vanilla into saucepan.
Cook over very low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Mix in sugar.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir. Pour into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm. Makes 25 (1 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch) squares.

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Brown meat.
Saute onions and celery.
Add mushrooms and both soups.
Mix well.
Add milk if more moisture is needed.
Fold in noodles and nuts.
Place in casserole dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese spread for crackers
directions: Mix together with hands.
Form into shape and chill.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese with 1 package taco mix.
Spread on 2 round pizza pans as you would crust for pizza.
Brown hamburger and mix with taco mix to taste.
Layer with grated cheese on top of cream cheese mixture.
Cover with tomatoes, onions, lettuce, olives; any of the above or anything else you can think of.
Serve with taco chips.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease (spray Pam) pie plate.
Place ingredients into blender.
Beat until smooth, 1 minute in blender on high or 2 minutes by hand beater.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until knife in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together into skillet or baking dish and make three holes.
In small hole, put vanilla.
In medium hole, put vinegar and in large hole put melted butter.
Pour cold water over and stir with fork.
Bake for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Add milk; mix well.
Knead on lightly floured surface.
Divide into 3 portions.
Roll each into circle; punch hole in center.
Fry in hot oil in skillet until golden brown.
Serve with honey or chili sauce.
Yield:
3 servings.

title: holiday nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
In large bowl, beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Add milk and flour mixture, alternately mixing well.
Stir in mincemeat and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes or until test for doneness.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Turn tomato stem side down.
Cut off top, scoop out and save for soup, etc.
Fill with frozen, thawed corn souffle or broccoli souffle.
Top with cheese and bacon.
Bake or microwave.

title: lovely lemon cheesecake
directions: Spray 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan or 9-inch pie plate lightly with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle side with half the graham cracker crumbs.
If desired, omit graham cracker crumb garnish. Sprinkle bottom of pan with remaining crumbs.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Soak chicken in buttermilk for at least 1 hour.
Dip chicken in flour mixture and fry.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix very well and roll into ball.
Roll ball of cheese in grated pecans.
Let stand in refrigerator for 1 hour, then serve with crackers.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate 12 hours before eating.

title: snowflake cookies
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Chill 2 hours or overnight. Roll into small balls, then into powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on a cookie sheet sprayed with cooking spray.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Remove from heat; blend in flour and salt.
Add milk and heat, stirring constantly until it thickens.
Add 1 1/2 cups of cheese; melt. Combine with macaroni in casserole and top with remaining 1/2 cup of shredded cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ice mocha
directions: Add coffee, milk, sugar and cocoa to blender. Process until smooth. Place over ice and immediately over ice or refrigerate. Stir well and serve. Makes 2 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs well, then add the other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in moderate oven about 45 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: shasta-orange ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: cherry salad
directions: Add Jell-O to hot water.
Mix pineapple in Jell-O.
Let cool. Add Coke.
Mix cheese and nuts.
Fill cherries with cheese/nuts mixture.
Drop cherries into setting Jell-O mixture.
Whip remaining cream cheese and nuts with small amount of mayonnaise for topping.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Wash and chop broccoli into bite size cubes.
Boil until partially done.
Boil one bag of Success rice.
Add broccoli, rice, soup and 2 well beaten eggs into casserole dish.
Top with shredded cheese and bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Cut steak into small pieces.
Salt, pepper, and flour all pieces.
Brown steak in frying pan with small amount of oil. Brown on both sides.
Place steak in baking dish.
Saute onion in meat drippings and place over meat.

title: pineapple orange punch
directions: Mix well and chill.
Serves 50 people.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package; drain and put aside.
In saucepan, cook green pepper and onion in butter until tender. Blend in flour and thyme.
Stir in soup and milk.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Fold in chicken, mushrooms, pimientos and noodles.
Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until heated through.
Very good!

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix together sugar, butter and corn syrup.
Fold in eggs; add vanilla and stir in oatmeal.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.
Serve hot.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream the butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
In a large bowl, combine milk, pudding mix and whipped topping.
Combine with butter mixture. Spread some crushed cookies in the bottom of bowl. Cover with some pudding mixture. Add more cookies and another layer of pudding. End with final layer of cookies.
Chill and serve.

title: dill beans
directions: Cover green or yellow (or mixed) fresh beans with water and boil 3 minutes.
(They should be crisp.)
Drain and pack into hot canning jars (pints or quarts).
To each jar add a head of dill and a clove of garlic.
Cover with the following solution and seal: 2 cups vinegar, 2 cups water and 1/4 cup salt.
Bring to a boil. This solution will make about 3 pints.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine; add rest of ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Use casserole dish with cover.

title: danish kringle
directions: Mix flour, sugar and lard like pie crust. Add eggs gradually, add milk. Let rise until double in size then roll out like pie crust.

title: pumpkin ring
directions: Beat all ingredients on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on medium speed 3 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Spread in greased and floured 12 cup Bundt pan or 10-inch angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Drizzle with glaze.

title: scott's oatmeal delight cookie
directions: In each individual foil, place 2 to 3 doves. Slice 2 potatoes. Place potatoes first, then doves, breast side down.
Next slice 3 pads of butter, then salt and pepper.
Close foil tightly. Wrap a second time.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes until doves and potatoes stick easy. Serve with cooked carrots and cole slaw.

title: crab quiche lorraine
directions: Place crabmeat, Swiss and onions in pie shell.
Beat eggs slightly.
Beat in milk.
Add seasonings.
Bake in 350° oven 50 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Bring ketchup, sugar and Coke to a boil.
Skin chicken; add salt and pepper.
Place chicken in mixture; cook until chicken is done over medium heat.

title: lindsey's lemon cookies(club member: amanda speed)
directions: Mix ingredients by hand; chill dough. Drop spoonfuls of dough into powdered sugar. Roll into marble-size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Heat together the butter, milk, flour and salt until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
