A wire whisk works well. Add the cheese and stir until melted.
Add the hash browns.
Stir and break up patties as they melt.
Pour in buttered 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave pecan and pineapple cream cheese pie
directions: Blend cream cheese with sugar until smooth and creamy (and no longer grainy).
Add pecans and pineapple to cream cheese mix and blend together.
Spoon mixture into pie shell.
Cook in microwave on Medium for 8 minutes, rotating after 4 minutes.
Cook until set.
Chill before serving.

title: pistachio fluff
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding together. Add crushed pineapple and maraschino cherries. Fold in miniature marshmallows. Chill and serve.

title: can can casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken and paprika in a large casserole dish.
Place chicken on top of mixture and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with steamed broccoli and crusty rolls.

title: super chicken curry(india)
directions: Heat grease in skillet.
Add onion and brown in hot grease. Add curry powder and garlic.
Cook mixture until slightly browned. Add meat and brown.
Add salt and cayenne pepper to taste.
Add enough water to keep from burning.
Cook until almost tender.
Add potatoes and cook about 30 minutes.
May add other vegetables, if desired.

title: chocolate pies(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix well sugar, flour, salt and cocoa.
Beat
egg yolks well and add to milk.
Stir into sugar mixture,
a little at a time. Cook over medium heat until
thick, stirring constantly. Add vanilla and margarine.
Bake pie shell
until almost done, add filling
and
return to oven and bake
until
crusts
are brown. Beat egg yolks until stiff.
Add 2 teaspoons sugar and beat again. Spread on pie and brown.

title: german pancakes(makes 10 servings)
directions: Mix flour, salt, vanilla pudding, baking powder and sugar together in a big bowl.
Slowly add milk while mixing with a mixer.
Separate egg whites and yolks.
Add yolks to batter and put whites in a second bowl.
Mix yolk batter well.
Beat egg whites until firm, then fold into batter with a wooden spoon.

title: peanut butter crunch cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cake mix (dry), brown sugar and peanut butter on low speed until crumbly.
Reserve 2/3 cup of crumbly mixture.
Beat remaining crumbly mixture, water, oil and eggs on low speed.
Beat on medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour batter into pan.
Stir nuts into reserved crumbly mixture.
Sprinkle over batter.
Sprinkle chips.
Bake about 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Melt margarine, water and cocoa and boil for one minute. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° in greased jelly roll pan or cookie sheet.

title: raleigh rolled dumplings
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour, baking soda and salt.
Cut in the shortening until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add the buttermilk, stirring with a fork until the dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn the dough onto a well floured surface and knead lightly
4 or 5 times.
Roll the dough to 1/8-inch thickness and cut into strips or small squares.
Slowly drop the dumplings into boiling broth.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil and sugar in large mixing bowl; blend well.
Add eggs, beat well.
Stir dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture alternately with zucchini, beating well after each addition.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Pour into 2 greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread refried beans in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish. Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco sauce in a separate bowl. Mix until well blended. Spread mixture over beans. Top this mixture with shredded Cheddar cheese. Garnish with black olives, tomatoes and scallions. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: make ahead oriental salad
directions: Combine vegetables in large bowl.
Stir gently.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Chill 24 hours before serving.

title: sweet n sour pork chops
directions: Brown apples and onion in margarine.
Drain kraut in a small bowl; stir in sugar.
Lightly brown chops in large skillet, using garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Pour in apples and onion mixture and sugar, kraut mixture; simmer, covered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: dirt
directions: Mix pudding and milk together; set aside.
Cream the margarine and cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar and mix.
Add pudding and mix.
Add Cool Whip and mix.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients and spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat eggs, powdered sugar and butter or margarine at high speed for 5 minutes.
Spread on crust.
Slice a layer of bananas over filling and then spread whipped cream over bananas.
Garnish with nuts, chocolate chips and cut up maraschino cherries. Refrigerate.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve dry yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
In mixing bowl add milk, sugar, salt, shortening and dissolved yeast.
Add flour a little at a time.
Knead and let rise. Turn onto floured board. Shape into rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut crumb coffee cake
directions: In a large mixer bowl, stir together flour, brown sugar, coconut, baking powder and soda.
Add peanut butter and softened margarine.
Beat on low speed of electric mixer just until crumbly.
Set aside 1/2 cup of mixture.

title: cooked fudge frosting
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk, butter and salt; bring to boil. Cook until soft ball stage.
Beat with mixer until cooked.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.

title: chocolate candy bar cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan. Combine all ingredients in large bowl and beat at medium speed until just mixed and no lumps remain.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Do not overbake.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream and Hot Chocolate Sauce.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast on warm water; stir to dissolve.
Heat cottage cheese in saucepan until lukewarm.
Combine cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill, salt, soda, egg and yeast in bowl.
Add flour, a little at a time, to make a stiff batter; beat well after each addition.
Cover and let rise in greased ovenproof bowl until doubled, 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Makes one loaf.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Cream Sauce:
Melt butter and add flour.
Cook 2 minutes. Slowly add milk and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Cool to room temperature.
Add sour cream.
Slice eggs and layer with cream sauce, mushrooms and bacon in large casserole. Repeat layers, ending with bacon.
Bake at 350° until bubbly. Serve over English muffins.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil water and pour over cleaned berries. Let stand 2 minutes; pour off liquid and save. Sprinkle berries with lemon juice and place in refrigerator. Combine liquid, sugar, cornstarch, salt and food coloring. Cook until very thick. Cool. Gently add berries and place in pie shell. Refrigerate. When ready to serve, cover with whipped cream.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Bake cake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread cubes.
Cook slow over low heat until cheese is melted.

title: gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt molasses and butter together; stir in sugar until dissolved.
Cool.
Mix with a wooden spoon flour, baking powder, spices and eggs.
Add to cooled mixture, beating well.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan and bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: s'mores snack treats
directions: Melt butter in saucepan on medium heat.
Add marshmallows, stirring constantly, until melted.
Stir in graham cracker pieces. Put in a 13 x 9-inch buttered dish and sprinkle on chocolate chips.
Press down with waxed paper.
Refrigerate 20 minutes before cutting (any size pieces you want).

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and oregano together.
Boil the noodles according to package.
Drain meat off.
Add sauces and catsup.
In a baking pan, put 1/2 of noodles (layer), 1/2 sauce and 1/2 cheese.
Add another layer of same.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°. Let rest for 10 minutes before serving.

title: honey-pecan butter spread
directions: Toast pecans in a 350 oven for about 8 minutes; cool.
Chop toasted pecans finely.
In a medium bowl, beat butter until fluffy.
Beat in honey until well combined.
Mix in chopped pecans.
Cover and refrigerate.
Let stand at room temperature to soften before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter, add syrup and salt; beat well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add pecans.
Pour into pastry shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: speedy ground beef casserole
directions: Brown onion and beef in pan. Add chili soup and tomato soup. Bring to a simmer. Add salt. Line casserole dish with Fritos. On top, sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° until cheese is melted.

title: don't last long cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Mix other ingredients in bowl.
Mix with spoon.
Then combine both bowls together and put in tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecued chicken(with homemade sauce)
directions: Cook onion, butter and green pepper until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook together for 15 minutes.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Cut in shortening with knives or pastry blender until uniform.
Add water; mix and knead.
Roll out balls of dough to flat tortillas and cook on a griddle (size of dough balls depends on desired size and thickness of tortilla).

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, salt, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can fried onions.
Place in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Cover and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Unwrap rolls and separate into two rectangles.
Press together perforations. Cut each rectangle lengthwise into 3 strips.
Place strips on top of dish. Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Put remaining cheese and onions over top. Bake remaining 3 minutes until melted.

title: green bean and bacon casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients (using only half of the onion rings and bacon or bacon bits) and mix; pour into casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining onion rings and crumbled bacon, or bacon bits.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: corned beef in beer
directions: Place onion in bottom of cooker.
Place corned beef in pot. Combine sugar, thyme and beer.
Pour over beef.
Cook low for 10 hours.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 40 minutes.

title: ham 'n cheese pinwheels
directions: Cut Cheddar cheese into 1/4 x 1/4 x 4-inch sticks.
Spread each ham slice with a thin layer of cream cheese.
Place Cheddar cheese at one edge of ham; roll up.
Chill.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices just before serving.
Serve on cucumber slices or crackers, if desired.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours.
Top with strawberries and desired amount of glaze.

title: cake frosting(for any type cake)
directions: Beat all ingredients together for 7 minutes.

title: ginger beef with soy sauce
directions: Cut beef into 1 1/2-inch slices.
Place beef and ginger in saucepan.
Add enough water to cover, about 1 cup.
Add sugar, Japanese rice wine and soy sauce.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, until scarcely any water is left.
Serves 4.

title: cherry pie filling salad
directions: Mix with mixer the Cool Whip, pudding mix and milk.
Line pan with graham crackers (9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish).
Pour half of mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers over mixture.
Add rest of mixture, then add a can of cherry pie filling on top.

title: angel food strudel
directions: Mix together by hand flour and butter.
Add beaten yolks and water.
Add vinegar last.
Divide into 7 balls.
Refrigerate at least 3 or 4 hours or overnight.

title: sweet potato fries
directions: Cut yams into long strips, leaving skin on.
Heat oil until sizzling.
(It is ready when a square of bread cooks quickly.) Fry yams in a large frying pan until brown on each side.
Drain on paper towels and blot off the extra fat.
Sprinkle with salt before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt in bowl. Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Add nuts.
Heat 3 minutes, stirring after each minute.
Add soda and vanilla; stir. Put popped popcorn inside 2 brown paper bags.
Pour mixture over corn.
Close and shake.
Heat 1 minute and shake.
Heat 1 minute and shake.
Heat 1 minute and shake.
Heat 30 seconds and shake. Heat 30 seconds and shake.
Cool and eat.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef with onion; drain.
Place beef and onion in large pot.
Add all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients thoroughly.
Stir in 1/2 cup buttermilk or water.
Sift together and stir in the last ingredients.
Chill at least an hour.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake until set, just until when touched lightly with finger, almost no imprint remains.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt
butter
or
margarine
in pan.
Mix in flour; add milk slowly, stirring until smooth.
Cook and stir until sauce thickens.
Add
mustard
and cheese;
stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Makes 2 2/3 cups of sauce.
Use cheese sauce to pour
over	cooked	vegetables or to mix with cooked potatoes, rice, macaroni or noodles.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together, sugar, syrup and salt in microwave safe dish (sprayed with PAM).
Place in microwave oven and cook on high 4 minutes.
Remove from microwave and stir in peanuts.
Cook another 3 1/2 minutes, then add butter and vanilla to mixture, stirring well.
Return to oven and cook 1 to 2 minutes more.
Peanuts will be slightly brown and syrup VERY HOT.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let cool 30 minutes to 1 hour.
When cool, break into small pieces and store in airtight container.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding
and milk.	Mix sour cream and Cool Whip in a large
bowl.
Fold	in
pudding.
Layer
vanilla wafers and banana slices with mixture.
Top with crushed vanilla wafers.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Grease a 10x15 cookie sheet and line with waxed paper.
Mix first six ingredients together in medium bowl.
Pour mixture in cookie sheet and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 min.
Turn onto a towel sprinkled with powdered sugar and roll it up in the towel a few times while warm (for flexibility).
Let cool, remove waxed paper and cover with filling.
For filling, mix butter, cream cheese powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Spread over pumpkin mixture after cool.
Roll up like a jelly roll and wrap in foil.
Keep refrigerated.
Will keep for weeks.
Can be frozen.
Delicious!!

title: bread
directions: Soften active dry yeast in warm water.
Combine hot milk, sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in 2 cups of the flour, beat well.
Add the softened yeast mix.
Add enough of the remaining flour to make moderately stiff dough.
Turn on lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth and satiny.
Shape in ball.
Place in lightly greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover, let double.
Punch down, let rise again until double.
Cut in 2 parts.
Let rest a few minutes.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Place in greased loaf pans.
Let rise until double.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch coffeecake
directions: The night before baking, place individual rolls (still frozen) in well-greased tube pan.
Mix sugars, pudding mix and cinnamon and sprinkle over rolls.
Pour melted margarine over top of dry mixture.
Leave on counter, uncovered, all night.

title: graham cracker crust(chocolate cheese pie crust)
directions: Place butter in 9-inch pie plate.
Microwave at High for 45 seconds or 1 1/2 minutes or until butter melts.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs and sugar.
Press mixture evenly on bottom and side of pie plate.
Microwave at High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until set, rotating pie plate once.
Cool.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut beef across the grain into thin strips.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef; toss and set aside, preparing vegetables.
Heat oil; add beef and toss over high heat until browned.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes over low heat. Turn heat up and add vegetables.
Toss until vegetables are tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water; add to pan.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat through.

title: oriental salad
directions: Mix together cabbage, carrots, onions and broken Ramen noodles.

title: shake and bake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until crumbly. Original recipe is spicy, cut down on paprika and red pepper. This is a good coating for chicken, fish or pork chops.

title: apricot spice cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients (sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg).
Mix eggs, oil and baby food.
Mix all ingredients; do not beat.
Cook in Bundt pan for 55 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: "hobo dinner"
directions: Cut 4 square pieces of foil and place patties.
Layer the following:
1 slice onion, 5 to 6 slices of potatoes, spoonfuls of corn and peas and a pat of butter.
Twist shut tight.
Make all 4 foil packages and bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: venison steaks
directions: Sprinkle steaks with seasoned salt.
Fry steaks in oil until brown.
Cover with onion and tomatoes.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Add extra liquid if needed.

title: microwave candy
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk.
Stir 2 times during 11 minutes in a microwave.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well. Pour into greased pan.

title: festive pumpkins and striped green snakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly grease baking sheet. In bowl, mix flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. In a medium bowl, combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla. Slowly add flour mixture, mixing well, forming a stiff dough. May divide dough into 2 balls to make both cookies.

title: cheerios treat(microwave)
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch microwave pan.
Microwave margarine in pan on High for 45 seconds or until melted.
Add marshmallows; toss to coat with margarine or spread.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 45 seconds.
Stir in peanut butter.
Immediately add cereal.
Mix lightly until well coated.
Using greased spatula or wax paper, press mixture into prepared pan.
Cool; cut into squares.
Makes 24.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil and debone chicken; salt to taste.
Reserve stock; saute onion, pepper and celery in oleo until translucent.
Add mushroom soup, cream of
chicken
soup,
pimento
and 1 can of chicken stock.
Cook
spaghetti
in
remaining stock.
Combine soup mixture, deboned
chicken, spaghetti and cheese in casserole. Bake at
until
cheese
is
melted.
Garnish with extra cheese on top.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes; mash.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, onion salt, salt, pepper and butter.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover.
Refrigerate for at least 2 days.
(Can store up to two weeks.)
When ready to use, top with Cheddar cheese (lots) and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: banana pie
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover with miniature marshmallows.
Put under broiler until marshmallows are browned.

title: chocolate meringue kisses
directions: Beat 2 egg whites stiff and add 1/8 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar.
Fold in 6 ounce package chocolate chips and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 300°.
I usually double the recipe.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cut buttered bread in 2-inch strips and put in buttered pan. Blend sugar, vanilla, salt and beaten eggs.
Add scalded milk and pour over bread.
Sprinkle with raisins.
Bake in 325° oven for about 45 minutes.
Pudding is done if knife comes out clean.

title: school party punch
directions: Make Kool-Aid according to package directions.
Add juice and store in a gallon container.
Chill.
When ready to serve, finish filling the container with chilled Sprite.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Cut shortening into flour, add milk and stir to make a soft dough.
Roll out on floured board to make a rectangle.
Spread sausage on top.
Roll from side to make a long roll.
Cut into slices and place, cut side down, onto ungreased cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush
cookies
in
blender
or
food processor and set aside. In
a
medium
bowl,
cream
butter,
cream cheese and powdered sugar.
In a large bowl, mix milk and pudding.
When pudding
is set, fold in Cool Whip, then cream cheese mixture. Layer
cookies and mixture, beginning and ending with cookies. Put
cake
in
a lined flower pot and plant artificial flowers and use
as
a centerpiece or for a child's party place gummy worms on
top or put cake in a sand pail and serve with a sand shovel.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Mix half margarine with corn flakes; set aside.
Put potatoes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour rest of ingredients over potatoes.
Put rest of corn flakes on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: peppered steak
directions: Cut steak into bite-sized pieces.
Salt and pepper and roll in flour.
Brown in skillet.
Pour into baking dish and add other ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: gingerbread
directions: Beat egg until fluffy, add molasses.
Blend in flour 1 cup at a time.
Add oil, then sugar, followed by spices and baking soda. Add 1 cup hot water last and mix well on low speed.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan and bake 30-40 minutes.
Cool slightly and serve lukewarm with whip cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour half into a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
While the cake is baking, melt caramels and margarine over low fire.
Add condensed milk slowly until it's all absorbed.
Pour this over baked cake. Add remaining cake batter.
Sprinkle with nuts and chips.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes longer.

title: onion soup
directions: Melt butter in pot which you will use for the soup, but do not brown.
Add the sliced onions and cook over low heat stirring occasionally until onions are soft and light brown.
Sprinkle the flour on top of onions.
Dissolve 4 bouillon cubes in 4 cups of boiling water, add to onions, stir well and season to taste. Simmer for approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with grated cheese and cubed toast.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1 cup nuts.
Form into ball; chill overnight.
Roll in remaining nuts next day.

title: pizza buns
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add pepper, mushrooms, tomato sauce and spices.
Heat thoroughly.
Arrange buns on baking sheet. Spread mixture evenly over buns.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies (blender works well).
Set aside.
Mix cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar in small bowl (set aside).
Mix milk and pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip in a large bowl.
Blend in the cream cheese mixture.
Layer crushed Oreos and mixture, alternating layers.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Boil first three ingredients for 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Add 2/3 jar of peanut butter.
Stir in cornflakes.
Drop on wax paper.

title: courtney's caramel brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt caramels and 1/3 cup of milk in microwave, stirring constantly.
Mix cake mix, 1/3 cup milk and butter until it holds together.
Stir in nuts.
Press half of cake mixture into well-greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake for 6 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate chips over mixture, then spread melted caramels evenly over chocolate chips.
Crumble remaining cake mixture on top.
Bake 17 to 20 minutes.
Cool and chill for 30 minutes.

title: baked ham slices
directions: Have butcher slice whole ham into 3/4-inch slices.
Layer desired amount of ham slices in baking dish.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top of slices to be baked.
Sprinkle small amount of dry ground mustard on top of brown sugar (about 1/2 to 1 teaspoon).
Place pineapple slices on top of ham slices and pour pineapple juice over top of ham.
This may marinate in refrigerator overnight, or you may bake immediately (extra good if marinated).
Cover with aluminum foil and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake an additional 10 or 15 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add butter, sour cream and both corns.
Add cornbread muffin mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center is clean.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute bacon.
Add onion and other vegetables, except cabbage. Add chicken stock, rice and seasoning.
Cook 30 minutes.

title: cheese cake tarts
directions: Add eggs to cream cheese, one at a time.
Add lemon juice, sugar and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Put paper liners in muffin tins.
Put a vanilla wafer in each liner.
Fill each 2/3 cup full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.
Cool and top with pie filling.
Can be frozen with topping. Allow about 15 minutes defrost time.

title: veg-all chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into pie crust shell and brush with egg.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well and pack firmly in loaf pan.
Top with 1/4 cup ketchup.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Makes 8 servings.

title: holiday morning french toast
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in a 13 x 9 baking dish.
Add apples and cranberries; toss to coat well. Spread apple mixture evenly over the bottom of the baking dish. Arrange bread slices on top.

title: beefaroni
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Brown beef; add chili powder.
Add tomatoes, sugar, garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Add beans and simmer.
Cook 1 cup macaroni and add to sauce.

title: monkey bread
directions: Roll biscuits in mix of cinnamon and 3/4 cup sugar.
Place in greased Bundt pan.
Bring rest of ingredients to boil; pour over biscuits.
Bake at 325° about 40 minutes.

title: swiss plum pie
directions: Quarter the plums. Arrange on pie crust.
Mix eggs, sour cream, sugar, Cream of Wheat and vanilla.
Pour over plums.
Bake in a 375° oven for 60 to 70 minutes or crust is brown and filling set.

title: red bean soup
directions: Boil all ingredients with or without soup bone or bacon (for added flavor).
Add seasonings.
Serve with croutons.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bob boyardee's famous cream of potato soup(slow cooker recipe)
directions: Combine water and flour in a jar and shake until mixed well. In 5-quart slow cooker, combine all ingredients, except sour cream, cheese and evaporated milk.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.
During last hour of cooking, add evaporated milk, sour cream and cheese.
When final ingredients are melted, it's ready to eat.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Have meats ground together twice.
Soak bread in cream 5 minutes.
Cook onion in 1 tablespoons butter until tender.
Mix meats, crumb mixture, onion, egg, parsley and seasonings.
Beat until fluffy, 5 minutes with mixer, then 8 minutes by hand.
Form in 1 1/2-inch balls.
Brown in 2 tablespoons butter, shaking skillet to keep round.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Boil peeled and cut-up potatoes for 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain and mash.
Slowly add remaining ingredients and beat with mixer until fluffy.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup servings).
Per serving:
87 cal, 0.1 g fat.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: Soften ice cream (about 15 minutes).
Mix crumbled Oreos with 1 stick butter and press into bottom of 10-inch spring-form pan. Freeze 15 minutes.
Spread ice cream over crust and return to freezer.
In a small pan, combine butter, sugar, chocolate and Pet milk.
Boil 3 minutes.
Cool and pour over ice cream layer; freeze.
Smooth Cool Whip over top of this; freeze.
Garnish with more cookies or melted Hershey bar drizzled over the top.
Thaw a few minutes; unmold and serve.

title: amaretto pecan pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cover edges of crust with foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: fortune cakes
directions: Write your own fortunes on strips of paper. (You will be very lucky. Hmm, work harder. Take a trip.
You win a free trip to the Moon. You may eat 1 more cupcake, etc.)

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add eggs one at a time, then milk and flour alternating. Add flavorings.
Let the mixture beat a few minutes after all ingredients have been added.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Reserve broth.
Debone chicken and return to broth.
Chop onion and bell pepper.
Add to chicken and broth.
Add okra and tomatoes.
Brown enough flour in oil to thicken broth.
Brown flour until almost burned (dark brown).
Add to other ingredients and simmer 1 hour or longer.

title: spinach salad
directions: In 13 x 9-inch cake pan, mix spinach, celery, onions, cheese, mayonnaise and egg white.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, top with egg yolks and crumble bacon.

title: banana split salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Fold in strawberries with juices, pineapple, bananas and 1/2 cup nuts.
Pour into 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish and jell.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done. Cut in half lengthwise and scoop out inside. With mixer, whip potatoes and add sour cream. Then add egg, chives and salt to taste. Let cool and last, add cheese. Fill halves with potato mixture and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or put in plastic freezer bags and freeze for later use. (These freeze beautifully!)

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients 3 times.
Add vanilla and milk to creamed mixture, beating until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in mixture.
Pour in greased and floured pan or wax lined pan.
Makes 3 (9-inch) cakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked chicken and brown rice with broccoli
directions: Place rice, soup and milk into a Dutch oven and mix.
Add broccoli; mix again.
Place chicken on top and season.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: cool hot dogs
directions: Will also need toothpicks.

title: squash and creamed corn casserole
directions: Cook onion in oil until tender, but not browned.
Add sour cream and salt and stir well.
Mix corn and sugar together and add to onion and sour cream.

title: never fail stew
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir and cook on high for 5 hours or until vegetables and meat are tender.
Can also be cooked in oven at 275° for 5 hours.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix ingredients together, except sauce.
Make into balls. Place in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Cover with the Ragu sauce.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: bubby's chicken soup
directions: Wash chicken thoroughly.
Combine chicken, giblets, water and onions in a large pot.
Skim top when it comes to a boil.
Add celery, parsley, carrots, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour or until chicken is done (loose on bone).
Can be served over cooked rice or soup noodles.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer all the ingredients in the order they are listed.
Do not stir.
Refrigerate.
Make a day before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Put 1 cup dressing mix in bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix other ingredients and put on dressing mix.
Top with remaining dressing mix.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Place chopped broccoli, sherry, water, garlic salt and cayenne in deep pot.
Bring to boil and cook until tender, approximately 1/2 hour.
Drain off most of the remaining liquid.
Add butter and finely chopped onion.
Cook for 10 minutes, until onion is tender. Add milk and Cheez Whiz and bring to a low boil.
Sprinkle in cornstarch to thicken.
Serve with 1 tablespoon shredded Mozzarella cheese sprinkled on each bowl.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Beat eggs in small mixer bowl.
Blend in sugar and melted butter.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to butter mixture. Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into lightly greased 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until almost set (pie will not test done).
Cool.
Cut into wedges.
Serve with ice cream and hot fudge.
Makes 8 servings.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread dough on a greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with topping and bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Mix and press crumbs, sugar and butter into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with chips, nuts and coconut.
Pour milk over all and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly brown on the edges.

title: cordon bleu chicken
directions: Fill halved breasts with slice of ham and slice of cheese. Roll chicken breasts up.
Place in a 1-quart baking dish.
Grate up remainder of cheese.
Spread over breasts with the mushroom soup. Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve over rice. (Can be made ahead and frozen.)

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions. Let cool and split layers. Mix together sugar, 1/2 package frozen coconut and sour cream. Save out 1 cup of this mixture; set aside. Spread mixture between layers. Mix the 1 cup of mixture you saved with 1 regular size Cool Whip. Frost cake. Sprinkle remaining coconut on top of cake.

title: chow's chicken long rice
directions: Saute
chicken	in
oil.
Add water and crushed ginger; cook until
tender.
Add
mushrooms,
bamboo shoots and water chestnuts.	Season	with
salt
and shoyu.	Add soaked and cut long rice; cook for 10 minutes.
Garnish with green onion.

title: quick spoon rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls in greased muffin pans.
Do not let rise in pans.
Pop into a 400° preheated oven.
Bake 15 or 20 minutes or until brown.
Makes 48.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in margarine and oil over low heat.
Mix popcorn, M&M's and nuts together.
Pour melted marshmallow mixture over popcorn, nuts and M&M's.
Stir thoroughly.
Press into greased tube or Bundt pan.
Refrigerate.
Remove from pan and slice.

title: potato wedges
directions: Scrub potatoes; do not peel.
Cut each into 4 wedges.
Soak in cold water to cover for several minutes; dry.
Mix flour, cheese, salt, pepper, chili powder, onion salt and parsley flakes in shallow bowl.
Dip potato wedges in melted butter; coat with flour mixture.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender and brown.
May microwave, covered, for 7 minutes, stirring once.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: hot dog bun sticks
directions: Brush each piece of hot dog bun with butter mixture.
Bake on cookie sheet at 250° for 1 hour or until lightly brown and crisp. Keeps well in a closed container.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add egg and onion. Mix well.
Add boiling water to make a stiff batter.
Make about 1-inch balls and cook in hot oil until golden brown.
Turn in oil as needed.
Drain on paper towel.

title: 4 can soup
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain grease.
Add all canned goods (liquid and all).
Heat and serve, stirring occasionally.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Mix brown sugar into egg white.
Dip each pecan half into mix. Place on greased cookie sheet, being sure that no pieces touch. Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Turn oven off and let the puffs stay until oven cools.

title: cranberry and pineapple relish
directions: Rinse cranberries in cold water and drain well.
Put through find blade of food chopper, saving all juice.
Add undrained pineapple and sugar to chopped cranberries and juice; stir well. Allow to stand at room temperature, stirring a few times, until sugar is dissolved, about 20 minutes.
Refrigerate and serve chilled.
Relish will keep for several weeks.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: corn pone
directions: Mix oil, milk, egg, salt and sugar. Add flour, corn meal and baking powder. Pour into a greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Eat hot or cold.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour and cinnamon.
Beat eggs until light.
Stir in sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla flavoring.
Add dry ingredients and then the nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: homemade spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef.
Saute onion and bell pepper with meat. Drain fat.
Add tomato paste and tomatoes; salt and pepper.
Let simmer.

title: quick tater tot bake
directions: In a skillet, brown the meat and onion.
Drain any fat. Season with salt and pepper. Place in a greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Top with potatoes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together well and put in unbaked shell.
Cover top with pecan halves.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until center is set.

title: lemon and vanilla pudding roll
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar gradually, continuing to beat until light and fluffy.
Add water and vanilla. Add sifted dry ingredients and blend until smooth.
Pour into greased, waxed paper-lined 15-inch jellyroll pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Turn out immediately onto a tea towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Remove waxed paper.
Trim any rough edges.
Roll cake up in cloth and place on rack to cool. Mix contents of package with sugar.
Substitute 1 whole egg for 2 yolks as indicated and prepare as directed; cool.
Unroll cake and spread on cooled filling.
Roll up again and chill until ready to serve.

title: gather round pound cake
directions: Melt together in double boiler the butterscotch, instant coffee granules and water.
Cool.
Combine flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Cream the butter or oleo with the sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in butterscotch mixture.
Add flour mix alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating at medium speed.
Bake in greased, floured Bundt pan at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan, then turn out on rack to cool.
Dust with powdered sugar or frost, if desired.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Heat milk in double boiler.
Mix flour and brown sugar; stir into hot milk. Add egg yolks and stir in.
Add melted butter and stir. Add vanilla and stir.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites and spread on top of pie.
Brown.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and combine with Eagle Brand milk; add rind and juice.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then add sugar gradually and continue beating until very stiff.
Fold egg whites into yolks and pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze for at least 6 hours. Serve with low-fat Cool Whip.

title: applesauce raisin cookie
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add flour, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder and cloves.
Mix well.
Add eggs, applesauce, nutmeats and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir meat and onion in butter until meat is brown and onion is tender. Stir in flour, salt, garlic, pepper and mushrooms; cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Stir in soup.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Reduce heat. Simmer 10 minutes. Stir in sour cream.
Heat through. Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
Stir in poppy seed and butter. Serve meat mixture over noodles.

title: chinese meat loaf dinner
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and form a meat loaf.
Arrange the carrots, celery and pineapple around the meat loaf.
Pour the juice over the vegetables and pour the sweet and sour sauce over the loaf.
Cook, uncovered, at 350°, turning vegetables once for 1 hour.
Serve with rice, if desired.

title: southwestern pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Drain and rinse.
Combine pasta with 1 3/4 cups of Southwestern dressing mix; toss and chill.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Combine soups, chilies, spices, Tabasco sauce and broth in large pan and heat until warm.
Cover baking dish with 2 cups of chips.
Spread 1/2 chicken over chips; add 1/2 sauce and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Combine sugar and apples and let stand.
Beat eggs with oil and vanilla.
Sift all dry ingredients and combine with eggs and oil mixture.
Add apple and sugar mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test; when knife inserted in middle comes out clean, cake is done.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Blend eggs and sugar together.
Add flour with soda, salt and then fruit cocktail.
Beat well.
Pour into long cake pan.

title: best ever cole slaw dressing(this is really great!)
directions: Beat ingredients together until very creamy.
Store in a covered pint jar in refrigerator.
Keeps very well.

title: ms. willie morris' jam cake
directions: Cream the
sugar and shortening. Add eggs and mix well. Add buttermilk	and
jam.
Add	to
sifted ingredients and mix well. Add fruit
and
nuts
last.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes. Makes two 10-inch layers.

title: layered chicken salad
directions: Layer 1 1/2 cups chicken and lettuce in 3-quart bowl.
Combine rice, peas and parsley.
Spoon evenly over lettuce.
Layer tomatoes, cucumber, chopped red pepper, green pepper and remaining 1 1/2 cups chicken.
Spoon dressing evenly over top of salad, sealing to edge of bowl.
Top with red pepper rings; cover and chill 8 hours.
Toss before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: taco casserole
directions: Spread chips in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with ground beef and diced onions.
Mix 1/3 cup milk with Cheddar cheese soup.
Pour over ground beef.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spread rice in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add milk and soup. Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour glazed onions
directions: Bring water to boil in large saucepan.
Add onions and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat, drain in colander and rinse with cold water.
Trim off stem and root ends, then slip off skins.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Sift the flour with baking powder and salt. Add sugar, egg, butter and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 cup walnuts. Turn into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until top is lightly browned and springs back when touched lightly.
Remove from oven.
Immediately arrange marshmallows, remaining walnuts and chocolate pieces over top.
Return pan to oven for 2 minutes or until chocolate is softened.
Remove from oven, then swirl chocolate over marshmallows and walnuts.
Cool until chocolate is set.
Cut into 15 (1 3/4 x 3-inch) bars.

title: tropical fruit delight
directions: Blend crumbs and butter. Saving 2 tablespoons of mixture for topping, press remainder over bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish in an even layer. Chill.

title: squash dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt, which have been sifted together, with milk alternately; add vanilla.
Roll and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
You can also drop these on a greased cookie sheet; flatten out with small glass with sugar on it.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and add envelope of taco seasoning.
Cook according to package instructions.
Drain on paper towels and refrigerate to get cold.
Add all other ingredients, but don't add chips until just before serving as they will get soggy.

title: farmer's fare
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Crumble and set aside.
Brown potatoes and onion in bacon drippings.
Drain off excess fat.
Add beaten eggs, salt and pepper.
Cook slowly, stirring until eggs are almost done. Sprinkle cheese over top. Cover with lid and warm to melt cheese. Serve hot with toast and jelly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pistachio surprise
directions: Set aside 6 cookies.
Count out 30 cookies and crush.
Melt oleo and add to crushed cookies.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill while mixing second layer.
In mixing bowl, add cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Beat with mixer until well blended.
Place over first layer.
Mix puddings with milk.
Beat 2 minutes with mixer.
Pour over second layer.
Add rest of Cool Whip.
Crush additional 6 cookies for garnish.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Heat beans and drain; pour into casserole dish and stir in soup.
Top with onion rings and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: vanilla drop cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking pan. Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes. Cookies spread out quite thin. If you like them thicker, decrease the amount of liquid to 2 or 3 tablespoons.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Cook until tender, the cranberries, water and soda.
Add sugar, flour and dates.
Cook until clear, then add 1/2 c. nuts (I use walnuts) and 1/2 tsp. vanilla.	Pour into baked pie shell. Cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients in saucepan.
Add beaten egg yolks and cream.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Add margarine and vanilla.
While mixture cools slightly, make meringue.
Put chocolate mixture into baked crust; top with meringue.
Bake in oven at 350° until meringue is slightly brown.

title: fruit bowl salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let sit for at least one hour in refrigerator.

title: gail's pink salad
directions: Mix together Cool Whip, jello and cottage cheese. Add fruit cocktail. Pour in shallow dish and chill.

title: hilda's breakfast apples
directions: Combine sugar, water, cloves, cinnamon and lemon peel.
Pare apples; core and cut in eighths.
Add to syrup and cook slowly 5 to 8 minutes or until apples are almost tender.
Remove cloves and cinnamon stick and serve warm.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat for 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Let cake cool in pan. Cake will settle during cooling.
Remove and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: risen biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve the yeast in 1 tablespoon warm water.
Put all liquids in dry ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Turn out on floured board.
Roll thin.
cut round.
Stack one on another.
Brush with melted butter on top and between layers.
Let rise about 2 hours before baking. Bake 12 to 14 minutes in a 400° oven.
Watch closely.

title: oxtail rice soup
directions: Cook oxtails and salt in enough water to cover well for 2 hours or until soft.
Drain broth off meat.
Start rice in cold water; add onion and celery.
When rice is almost done, add the broth and continue cooking until tender.
Grate a little carrot for color and add the meat from the oxtails.
Season with a little beef soup base to taste.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Peel and thinly slice 10 potatoes.
Place potatoes in a 14-inch Dutch oven with the rest of the ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 50 minutes with
14 coals on top and 12 coals on the bottom.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Combine ingredients and chill until set in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs, well beaten. Add flour, salt, vanilla, syrup and pecans.
Turn into a 9-inch unbaked pie crust and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 to 50 minutes longer.

title: frances' hash
directions: Boil pork until done.
In separate pot, boil chicken.
Pour off broth.
When cold, take off fat.
Dice onions and boil them in chicken broth.
Cut up potatoes real small and cook them in onion broth.
Put pork and chicken through a grinder.
Mix meat with chicken, onion and potato broth.
Add tomato puree.
Add pork broth as needed.
Cook for a couple of hours.
Keep adding broth as needed.
Stir real often to prevent sticking.
Season to taste.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, milk, butter, syrup and salt in saucepan.
Stir over moderate heat until dissolved.
Boil until it reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and allow to stand until lukewarm, about 1 hour.

title: apricot salad
directions: In saucepan, heat to boiling the jello and crushed pineapple. Let cool, then add Cool Whip, buttermilk and nuts.
Put in 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch Pyrex dish and chill.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes on hand grater.
Add egg, flour and water.
Mix thoroughly.
Plop spoonful of mixture into melted Crisco (on medium high).
Shape flat like a pancake.
Fry until golden brown.

title: golden glow salad
directions: Add water to reserved pineapple juice to make 1 cup.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add juice and vinegar; chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in pineapple, carrots and nuts and chill until firm.
Serves 4 to 6.
If desired, serve with mayonnaise.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat all ingredients together thoroughly.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: glazed carrot coins
directions: Combine water, salt and carrots in a 1-quart casserole dish. Cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Microwave 15 minutes on High, or until carrots are tender.
Stir in butter, sugar and lemon rind. Cover.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes, or until hot and glazed. Serves 6.

title: fat free oven french fries
directions: Cut each potato lengthwise into eight wedges, dip into egg white and dredge in Parmesan cheese.
Place fries on baking sheet coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients (except chicken wings) in large roasting pan or marinator.
Wash chicken wings and cut into 2 pieces.
Add to ingredients in pan, coating all sides.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight, if possible, turning several times. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: aunt monya's lasagna
directions: Brown ground chuck with salt, pepper and garlic.
Drain off fat and add Prego sauce; mix thoroughly.
Set aside.

title: seven can bean soup
directions: Cook and drain ground beef.
Put in a large 6-quart pot and add each can listed.
Cook together, then simmer to keep warm.

title: never fail peanut brittle
directions: Butter a large shallow baking pan or platter.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Parboil potatoes until fork tender.
Peel and shred.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes.
Stir in cheese.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender. Bone and chop chicken. Reserve 2 cups broth. Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine reserved broth, soup and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Pour over chicken. Combine flour, margarine and buttermilk in bowl. Mix well. Spoon over casserole.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Sift dry ingredients together; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal. Quickly stir in milk. Knead dough lightly. Roll into 1/2-inch thickness on lightly floured board. Cut in 2-inch rounds. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 12 to 16.

title: pear oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter with brown sugar until smooth.
Beat in remaining ingredients, until just combined.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine nectars and juices.
Chill to serve. Pour over ice. Add ginger ale last.
Makes enough to serve 30 to 35.

title: basil garden salad
directions: Toss the lettuce, onions, tomato, mushrooms and basil in a large salad bowl. Combine remaining ingredients in a jar with tight-fitting lid; shake well. Pour over the salad and toss. Serve immediately. Without salt and sugar, has 3 grams carbohydrate.

title: philly fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill.

title: shrimp newburg
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir constantly.
Add milk, gradually, until thickened.
Add a little of hot milk mix to eggs; stir.
Return egg mix to pan.
Stir and cook for 2 minutes.
Add shrimp and sherry.

title: hot hominy casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo. Add remaining ingredients, stir well. Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes in covered dish. Remove from oven and stir well before serving. (You may reserve juice from hominy to add in case it gets too dry while cooking.)

title: english butter toffee
directions: Lightly butter a large cookie sheet.
Sprinkle chopped almonds evenly in it and set aside.

title: cocoa cheesecake
directions: Prepare Graham Crust; set aside.
Beat cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar, cocoa and 1 teaspoon vanilla in a large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; blend well.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool 15 minutes.
Combine sour cream, 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla; stir until smooth.
Spread evenly over baked filling. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Cool; chill several hours or overnight.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Heat oil in thick iron pot.
Add shrimp and cook only until they turn pink.
Add tomato sauce, can of water, onion, garlic and seasoning to taste.
Add onion tops and parsley.
Cook very slowly, covered, for 45 to 50 minutes.
Add a tablespoon of flour mixed with a small amount of cold water to gravy before serving. Serve over hot cooked rice.
Approximately 6 servings.

title: banana fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in a wax paper lined pan, about 1/4-inch thick.
Freeze.
Cut into squares.
Equals 1 milk and once a week fruit.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken breast until tender.
Bone and grind in food processor.
Add pineapple, Cheddar cheese, celery and mayonnaise until moist.

title: sausage cassoulet a la steuben
directions: Heat butter in large skillet and saute sausages.
Remove from skillet and drain, reserving 1 tablespoon fat.
Saute onion and garlic in fat until soft.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix in sausages.
Simmer 15 minutes or longer.

title: shrimp dip for chips
directions: Thin cream cheese with a little salad dressing and French dressing.
Add garlic salt and onion salt.
Add shrimp.
I use electric mixer to mix all.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients (except paprika).
Put in a shallow ovenproof dish (better if mixture is shallow in dish).
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: shish kabobs
directions: Put meat in a bowl (after you have cut it up) with meat tenderizer.
Swish around and baste with butter.
Alternate meat, peppers, onion and mushrooms on skewers.
Baste with butter as you are cooking them.

title: spiced apple party mix
directions: In medium bowl, combine cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add raisins and apples; toss to coat with spices.
Add walnuts; toss.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: quiche lorraine 2
directions: Mix eggs, cream, grated cheese and seasonings.
Saute onion and ham in butter; add bacon and diced cheese and spread evenly in bottom of pastry shell.
Pour egg mixture over ham mixture and fill to the rim of shell.
Bake at 400° for approximately 45 minutes or until set.
Serves 8.

title: ham biscuit delight
directions: Split each pan of rolls.
Cover the bottoms of the rolls with ham and cheese.
Place the tops back on the rolls.
Set aside.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes and boil until done (7 to 8 minutes). Drain and cool potatoes.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.

title: pineapple angel food cake
directions: Make cake according to package directions adding pineapple and juice. Bake in bundt pan. Bake until done.

title: lemon muffins
directions: Mix together and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mom's applesauce cake
directions: Put all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Mix and add enough flour to make stiff.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 inch pan.
Bake 350 degrees for 50 - 60 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas.
Put soda in sour cream; add to mixture.
Add flour and salt.
Add vanilla and nuts; mix.
Pour in loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes. May be divided into smaller loaf pans.
Freezes well.

title: montana ribs
directions: Mix peppers, salt, mustard, sugar, vinegar and water.
Add lemon and onion.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add catsup, Worcestershire sauce and liquid smoke.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Put ribs in shallow baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 450°.
Drain fat; pour sauce over ribs.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 to 60 minutes, basting with sauce.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together 1/2 cup Crisco and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift 2 cups cake flour 3 times and add to creamed mixture.
Add salt and cocoa.
Mix well.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla, buttermilk and food coloring.
Beat well.

title: cashew milk
directions: Blend the cashew meal and hot water.
Add salt, vanilla, honey and 3 cups of water.
Blend until smooth.
Chill and serve.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix honey and peanut butter in a bowl.
Add powdered milk and stir until combined.
With hands, roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on wax paper and store in refrigerator.
Great snacks anytime.

title: egg rolls
directions: Prepare beefy rice according to package directions.
Cool slightly, then fold in water chestnuts and onions.
Place rounded 1/4 cupful hamburger rice filling in egg roll wrapper.
Fold and seal with slightly beaten egg.

title: banana split cake
directions: In large casserole layer ingredients in order given. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: stylish bacon and egg sandwich
directions: Place tomato slice on toast; follow with bacon and then egg, cut side down.
Cover with cheese sauce and garnish with parsley sprigs.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: onion meatballs
directions: Mix meat, bread crumbs, milk and egg. Make 1-inch meat balls. In bottom of casserole dish, spread thinly chopped onion. Place meat balls on top of onion. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown. Then add vegetables, Worcestershire sauce and tomato sauce. Cover and bake until tender vegetables, 425° for 35 minutes. Then uncover. Top with cheese and brown.

title: a satisfied stud
directions: Blend Love, Loyalty, Hope and Tenderness.
Add Faith as needed.
Sprinkle abundantly with Laughter.
Bake it with sunshine.
Serve daily with a pinch of Nagging and you will have a satisfied stud.
Spouses that understand donating services.

title: skinny dip
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables such as celery, cauliflower, cucumbers, green peppers, etc.

title: baked stuffed mushrooms
directions: Fry and chop sausage.
Let drain thoroughly.
Cream the cream cheese while sausage is draining.
Mix.
Stuff mushroom tops. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: magic pumpkin pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean. Cool and refrigerate at least 1 hour. You may substitute 1 3/4 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice for the other spices.

title: simple sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine ingredients and spread on top of breasts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
An easy way to "sweet and sour" something.

title: pepperoni-cabbage casserole
directions: Shred cabbage.
Dice onion and green peppers.
Add garlic powder to taste.
Add pepperoni.
Mix all these together.
Put in baking dish.
Slice Velveeta cheese and spread over top.
Add just enough water so it will not stick.
Bake, until soft, at 350°, approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: swirled mint christmas cookies
directions: Combine flour and baking powder.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter or margarine until softened.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy. Add egg, vanilla and peppermint extract and beat well.
Beat flour mixture and beat until well mixed.
Divide the dough into thirds. Tint one red, one green and leave one plain.
Cover each and chill about 1 hour.

Roll each of the dough into 1/2-inch diameter ropes. Using 1 rope of each color, twist together to swirl the colors. Slice the twisted ropes into 1/2 or 1/4-inch pieces, depending on how big you want the cookies without blending the colors too much to keep them distinct.
Shape each slice into a ball.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet about 2-inches apart and flatten to 1/4-inch thickness with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in a 375° oven until done (allow 8 to 10 minutes for larger cookies or 6 to 8 minutes for smaller ones).
Remove and cool.
Makes about 72 large or 144 small cookies.

title: hamburger heaven
directions: Heat oven to 350 to 400°.
Brown meat.
Add remaining ingredients in layers in order given. Add seasonings.
Rinse out tomato can with 1/4 cup water and pour over all.
Cover when steaming.
Turn to 250° or low and cook for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese olive balls
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients well.
Roll dough around olives. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Yield:
Makes 25 olives.

title: easiest chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil broth and soup.
Add chicken and stir well.
Drop tortilla squares into boiling broth, a few at a time.
Reduce heat and cook until dumplings are fluffy.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine all ingredients and boil for 15 minutes.
Place in pint jars with lids and process in boiling water for 15 minutes. Makes 5 to 6 pints.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Beat egg, vinegar and water. Mix flour, salt and Crisco with fork. Add liquids to form dough. Roll out. Freeze what you don't use for later.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Then, in a pot, add the next 3 ingredients.
Let this come to a boil and then pour over kraut and mix well together.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Then serve.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet 2 inches apart. Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: egg rolls
directions: Chop pork chops into very small pieces.
Put all vegetables, except bean sprouts, into food processor and mince into small pieces.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together the sugar and Crisco.
Add beaten eggs.
Add all other ingredients except nuts and beat until well blended. Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased bread pans.
Bake slowly for about 50 minutes at 275° or 300°.

title: lord baltimore cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.

Add to creamed mixture and beat until very smooth, almost waxy in appearance. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in lemon extract.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely.
Spread Lord Baltimore Filling between layers and on top of cake.
Yield:
One 3 layer cake.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Put eggs, oil and chopped zucchini into blender and beat.
Add to the other ingredients.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325° in greased Bundt cake pan.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook (heat) lima beans. Drain and set aside.
Cook bacon. Reserve 2 tablespoons fat.
Crumble bacon. Saute onion and pepper in oil. Stir all together. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: mama's chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 11-inch pan.
Add rice.
Place chicken over rice.
Pour onion soup, salt and pepper over.
Add water.
Cover; bake 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes to brown.

title: vodka sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add Vodka and pepper.
Simmer for 2 minutes, then add whole tomatoes (blended) and heavy cream.
Simmer for 15 minutes uncovered.
Add cheese and pour over 1 pound rigatoni, cooked.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and 2 1/2 cups milk.
Add sour cream, condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Pour over sliced bananas and wafers.

title: corn dog
directions: Will also need 6 skewers.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Cream the oleo and cheese until soft. Stir in flour and chill. Shape into 20 (1-inch) balls.
Place in ungreased small muffin tins and shape.

title: chrysanthemum salad(serves 6)
directions: Pull petals from flowers.
Combine vinegar with honey, tarragon and lemon juice in small bowl.
Marinate petals in mixture for 30 minutes.
Drain petals and reserve marinade.
Mix petals with lettuce, watercress and olives in large bowl.

title: mulled apple cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven or large pot on stove top.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove and discard spices.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Add other ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, covered.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Cook macaroni 10 minutes.
Drain. Mix all ingredients, except cheese, together thoroughly.
Put into casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: maple frosting
directions: Place syrup, sugar and egg white in top of double boiler over hot water.
Beat until mixture stands in peaks.
Remove from heat and beat until cool.
This frosting is especially nice on a chocolate cake.

title: pudding and pie delight
directions: Mix melted margarine, flour and chopped nuts and pat out thin in pan.
Bake at 325° about 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool this mixture. Cream together powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Mix chocolate pudding according to package.
Beat until solid. Pour over cream cheese mixture. Spread Cool Whip over chocolate pudding.
Sprinkle top with nuts.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain.
Chop onion and saute in margarine in
frying
pan.	Add cream of chicken soup and 8 ounces sour cream.
Mix well and add stuffing mix.

title: brick chili
directions: Cook suet and beef together until done. Add tomatoes and spices. Add oats to boiling ingredients 1/2 cup at a time. Cook 2 or 3 minutes, stirring deep and long. Pour into bread pans. Let cool and cut into 1 pound blocks. When cool, wrap and freeze.

title: correlli's poulet supreme
directions: Simmer boneless chicken breasts in water with bay leaf, white wine and 2 to 3 cubes chicken bouillon.
Remove when cooked and cool.
Layer (buttered) baking dish with asparagus.
Top with cooled chicken.
Mix soup, 1/4 cup white wine, 1 teaspoon Krazy Mixed-Up salt, garlic powder and mushrooms.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° until golden brown (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Top with Cheddar and bake until melted.

title: winter pear marmalade
directions: Mix pears in blender.
Add sugar and gelatin.
Pour into saucepan.
Bring to a boil; stirring constantly.
Cook 5 minutes. Pour into sterilized jars and seal with paraffin.
Store in refrigerator.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven until cookies are brown around edge but centers are not done, 8 to 9 minutes.
Makes 96 cookies.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put cooked broccoli on bottom, then cut up chicken.
Then mix soup, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Put this on top with cheese and croutons.
Cook for 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Boil all ingredients together.
Pack eggs in jar; remove all water.
Pour the mixture over eggs.
Seal and put in refrigerator. Will keep several weeks.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Heat 2 cups milk.
Put sugar, flour, cornstarch, eggs and salt in blender with 1 cup milk.
Slowly add to heated milk until it thickens.
Remove from stove; add butter and vanilla, let cool. Put half peanut butter crumbs into pie shell.
Add pudding.
Top with Cool Whip and remaining crumbs.

title: ruby-red raspberry sauce
directions: Place strainer over small saucepan (do not use a fine strainer).
Push raspberries through strainer with a wooden spoon to extract as much juice as possible; discard seed.
Add jam to juice in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. Dissolve arrowroot or cornstarch in liqueur in small cup.
Whisk into sauce.
Cook over moderate heat, whisking or stirring constantly, until sauce comes to a boil and thickens.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
(Can be kept for 1 week, covered, in refrigerator.)

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place the first 3 ingredients in a food processor and pulse 2 to 3 times.
Add margarine pieces and pulse 10 times or until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
With the processor on, slowly add ice water through food chute, processing just until combined (do not form a ball).

title: mccluskey chili
directions: Brown hamburg.
Drain fat.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer uncovered and stir occasionally for 1 hour.

title: fluffy banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding with milk according to instructions on box. Beat in Cool Whip.
Add marshmallows.
In bowl, place one layer of wafers, one layer of bananas, sliced round, and one layer of pudding mixture.
End layers with pudding on top.
Sprinkle top with wafer crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Boil until thick and clear; let cool.
Fill baked pie shell with whole strawberries.
Pour cooked berries in glaze over whole berries.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla, salt and zucchini.
Add all dry ingredients; mix until dry ingredients are moistened. Pour into well-greased loaf pan that has been lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until done.

title: pork chops with mushroom gravy
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper.
Spray frying pan with Pam. Brown chops (not too brown) on medium heat.
Drain chops on paper towel.
If too much grease is in pan, drain.

title: mac el's christmas breakfast
directions: Crumble bread.
Mix bread and cheese.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Beat eggs and milk together; stir in salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Spread ham across top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add vinegar and water; boil for 5 minutes.
Add beets to hot sauce and let stand at least 30 minutes.
Add butter, if desired.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Add meat, eggs, onions, and seasonings.
Mix well.
Place in loaf pan and cover with sauce. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: garden pizza
directions: Mix the yeast with water.
Add the flour and salt.
Knead. Cover and let rest while you assemble filling.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Layer in casserole the zucchini, tomatoes and onions.
Season each layer with garlic salt.
Makes at least 2 or 3 layers.
Top with cheese and bacon. Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 375°.

title: teresa's stew
directions: Cut meat into bite size pieces.
Trim off all fat.
Put in pan with onion and spices and cover with water and bring to a boil. Add all other ingredients and simmer several hour.

title: brownies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and remaining dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and pecans; mix well.
Bake at 375° approximately 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar in large bowl until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs.
Mix mashed bananas, milk and vanilla.
Mix flour, salt and baking soda; blend in with banana mixture.
Stir in nuts. Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out of pan.
Let it cool completely.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: cherry pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour cherry pie filling into pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of pie filling. Melt margarine and pour over cake mix.
Bake for 45 minutes and sprinkle chopped nuts on top of cake mix.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt and sugar.
Add buttermilk, oil, eggs and cereal.
Mix well.
Store in refrigerator.
(Do not stir again.)
Bake in greased muffin tins at 375° for about 20 minutes. Keeps in refrigerator 6 weeks.

title: sweet and sour cabbage salad
directions: Toss cabbage, onions and peppers together in a large bowl. In a saucepan, mix together vinegar, sugar and spices.
Bring to a boil.
Add salad oil and mix well.
Pour over cabbage mixture to coat thoroughly.
Can be kept in refrigerator for at least a week.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order given with your hands in a large dishpan.
Use a larger tablespoon or ice cream scoop.
Drop and flatten.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° (only 6 or 8 fit on a sheet).
Cool a minute before removing from baking sheet.

title: chocolate marshmallow haystacks
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and
milk,
mixing
until well blended.
Gradually add sugar.
Stir in melted chocolate, salt and
vanilla; fold in marshmallows.
Drop
rounded	teaspoonful of mixture into shredded coconut
or chopped walnuts. Toss until well covered.
Place on waxed
paper
lined
cookie sheet;
chill until set.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chef's salad
directions: In large bowl, tear lettuce and romaine into bite-sizes.
Save a few strips of meat and cheese.
Toss rest of meat and cheese, onions, celery and anchovies with lettuce.
Blend mayonnaise and French dressing.
Pour over salad and toss.
Garnish with reserved meat and cheese strips, olives, egg slices and tomato wedges. Makes approximately 4 servings.

title: corn scallop
directions: Mix in bowl in order given; bake in buttered dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: carolina pound cake
directions: Cream together the butter and cream cheese.
Beat in sugar with mixer on low.
Sift into another bowl the flour, salt, baking powder and nutmeg.
Beat two of the eggs into cream cheese mixture alternately with 1/3 of dry ingredients.
Continue same until all eggs and dried ingredients are used.
Beat thoroughly, adding vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into waxed paper lined tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain (approximately 10 minutes).
Put broccoli in 3-quart casserole dish.
Layer chicken over it.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and cheese and spread over chicken.
Mix margarine, crackers and pecans and layer over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in chicken broth until tender.
Put in blender and blend until almost smooth.
Return to stove, add shredded Swiss cheese and milk.
Thicken with 2 tablespoons cornstarch mixed in 1/4 cup water.
Do not boil.
If the soup is still not thick enough, add a little instant mashed potato until desired consistency.

title: stuffed cabbage(golabki)
directions: Remove core from cabbage; scald in hot boiling water.
Take out and remove leaves.
Boil rice until done.
Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Combine onion, meat, salt, pepper, egg and rice and mix well.
Spread each leaf with meat mixture about 1/2-inch thick; fold the two opposite sides of the leave and roll, starting with one of the opened ends.

title: calico beans
directions: Bake at 325 degrees in 3-quart casserole for 2-1/2 hours. (Can do in crock pot, also.)

title: lemon tea muffins
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Beat butter and sugar together, add egg yolks.
Stir in lemon.
Mix dry with wet ingredients.
Beat egg whites.
Fold in slowly.
Mix brown sugar, nuts and nutmeg. Sprinkle on top of muffins.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes for mini, 15 to 20 minutes for regular.

title: chewies
directions: Mix well with fork or spoon until blended.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: In a large bowl, make in order of recipe (layered). Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, toss.
Makes enough for a large group.
You may want to cut the recipe in half.

title: chicken (and dressing) casserole
directions: Cut up cooked chicken; add mushroom soup and milk.
Mix well and place in a baking dish.
Saute butter, onion and celery until tender and add corn bread and broth to vegetables.
Pour mixture over top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 6 ingredients into prepared cake mix.
Fold into mix the poppy seed.
Pour into a Bundt or angel food cake pan already oiled and floured.
Bake for 1 hour. Remove from oven and turn cake onto serving dish.
Let cool about 10 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: yellow corn bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat egg slightly; add milk and salad oil.
Stir lightly.
Pour into 10-inch square pan.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 12 pieces. (Cubed bacon can be put on top of batter.)

title: milk chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients, flour, salt and cocoa, and add alternately with sour milk.
Add vanilla.
Mix vinegar with soda and add last.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch greased pan at 350° until pick comes out clean.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine 1 stick of butter, melted, with the graham cracker crumbs.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: light carrot cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; set aside.
Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons juice for Cream Cheese Frosting.
Combine brown sugar and oil.
Add egg whites, beating well.
Stir in pineapple, carrot, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; stir well.
Pour batter into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Spread Cream Cheese Frosting over cake.
Cut cake into squares.
Yield: 18 servings (181 calories per serving).

title: glazed wings
directions: Cut wings in half at joint, discarding tip.
Broil 12 minutes, turning once, until crispy.
Combine jam, oil and horseradish. Brush wings with glaze and broil 2 minutes each side until golden brown.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly.
Spoon off excess fat.
Add next 5 ingredients.
