Simmer 30 minutes, uncovered, stirring occasionally. Cook noodles in a large amount of boiling, salted water until tender; drain and rinse.

title: lamb dijon
directions: Have butcher prepare lamb; remove any excess fat.
Combine mustard, ginger, rosemary, soy sauce, garlic and oil in small saucepan.
Heat and whisk until mustard is fairly well blended with other ingredients.
Pour mixture over meat.
Marinate all day or at least 2 hours, turning 2 or 3 times.
Broil or barbecue about 6 inches from heat or hot coals 30 to 40 minutes on each side.
Meat should be pink inside.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: wine-marinated mushrooms and olives
directions: In a bowl, mix mushrooms, olives, onions and parsley.
In another bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth and thick.
Pour mixture over mushrooms.
Stir to coat well. Cover and marinate overnight or for several days.
Serve as an hors d'oeurve, with roast meats or in a salad.

title: homemade peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir flour, salt and baking soda.
Set aside.
Mix well margarine and peanut butter.
Add both kinds of sugars and mix well.
Add eggs and beat well.

title: rainbow jello salad
directions: Prepare each package of Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water. Divide in half.
Add 3 tablespoons of water to one-half.
Pour in a large bowl (clear bowl looks better).
Refrigerate to set.
To other half, add 4 ounces of sour cream and blend.
Layer on first half.
Refrigerate.
After set, add first half of another flavor, then second half with sour cream.
Repeat for all six flavors (12 layers).

title: mama's sweet and sour beets
directions: Drain off half of liquid from beets and pour beets into bowl. Add
apple
cider
vinegar,
sugar
and black pepper to taste. Let stand about 1 hour to absorb juices.

title: crab dip
directions: Marinate crabmeat in lemon juice for 30 minutes.
Mix other ingredients.
Can melt cream cheese in microwave.
When mixed, blend gradually into crabmeat.
Do not shred crabmeat, keep lumpy. Use crackers and veggies for dip.

title: pickled sausage kielbasa
directions: Cut kielbasa in 2 1/2-inch chunks to fill a quart or gallon jar.
Heat sausage in boiling water to cover 3 minutes.
Drain. Pack hot in jar.
Heat white vinegar with pepper pods in.
Pour over sausages.
Cover with tight plastic cover.
Put in fridge for 24 hours.

title: cabbage salad dressing
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a simmer and cool to room temperature.
Pour over head of shredded cabbage and let stand 24 hours.
Add onion and carrot, if desired.

title: butter pecan fudge
directions: Coat nuts with the 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Spread in pie pan.
Place in 350° oven for 15 minutes, stirring frequently until lightly toasted.
Combine sugar, sour cream, chocolate, syrup, salt and cream of tartar in heavy pan.
Stir over low heat until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth.
Cook to soft ball stage. Remove from heat and add butter.
Don't stir.
Let cool to lukewarm and add vanilla.
Beat until mixture loses its shine.
Stir in pecans and spread in buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cut into squares. Store in refrigerator.

title: juicy rib steaks
directions: Quickly rinse steaks.
Pat dry.
Rub 1 teaspoon cornstarch on each steak.
Rinse and slice leek.

title: four layer delight
directions: Cream all the ingredients, then pat and spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 300° for about 20 minutes. Cool.

title: russian tea
directions: Let tea be light amber color. Cover lemon and orange rinds with water. Add two cups of sugar and let boil a few minutes. Pour 1 cup boiling water over 4 Tbsp. whole cloves. Strain fruit juices and mix all together. Just before serving heat, but do not boil. Serves 16.

title: grandma's chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour in a large bowl and set aside.
Mix water, oil, margarine and cocoa in a saucepan, bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Pour over sugar and flour mixture.
Stir well, then add soda, salt, buttermilk and eggs.
Mix all ingredients well and pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Place all ingredients into heavy pan.
After it comes to a boil, cook 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat until thick enough to spread on cake.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Beat sugar, butter and egg until creamy.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: You will also need a cookie sheet and wax paper.

title: low calorie french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut each potato lengthwise into 8 wedges.
Brush cut sides with beaten egg whites, then sprinkle with salt, pepper, Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Place wedges, skin side down, on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown, puffed and tender when pierced with a fork.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Heat sugar and cocoa over low fire for 5 minutes (these are dry ingredients).
Add 1 can evaporated milk and oleo.
Bring to boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.

title: fifteen minute cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cocoa and milk; boil for 1 minute. Stir in oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Put on waxed paper.

title: golden squash fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oil, in large bowl.
Mix well. Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: bean casserole
directions: Bake in a large bowl at 300° for 2 hours.
Leave lid off.

title: best ever cole slaw
directions: Chop or shred the cabbage, green pepper and onion.
Sprinkle with 1/3 to 1/2 cup sugar.
Combine the remaining ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture while hot. Cover, cool and refrigerate for several hours or overnight. Serves 8.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: california onion dip
directions: Mix well.
Chill and serve with chips or vegetables.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350° while preparing cookie dough.
Beat egg whites until very, very stiff.
Gradually add salt, cream of tartar and sugar.
When egg whites are like satin, fold in nuts or chips. Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Put cookies in oven and immediately turn oven off; leave cookies in oven overnight.
Do not open oven.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat, onion and bell pepper together until done.
Drain off excess grease.
In separate mixing bowl, mix rice, corn, mushroom soup, garlic salt and water.
Allow to stand. Combine meat mixture and other mixture together.
Bake in glass baking dish at 350° until golden brown.

title: brethren cheddar bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Cut butter into dry ingredients until crumbly, about the texture of uncooked oatmeal. Stir in cheese and dill. Combine eggs and milk. Add to dry, stirring just enough to moisten uniformly. Divide among 4 well-greased pans and bake in hot (400°) oven 35 to 40 minutes, until loaves are nicely browned and sound hollow when thumped. Slice approximately 1/2-inch thick. Freezes well. Makes 4 loaves, each 7 x 3 x 2-inches.

title: midnight malt
directions: Combine first four ingredients in container of electric blender. Cover and process until smooth.
Pour into glasses. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Serve immediately.
Makes 2 cups.

title: walking taco dip
directions: In a casserole dish, spread evenly (layering each item on top of the previous) beginning with the first ingredient on the list. Refrigerate to let the flavors meld and serve with tortilla or corn chips.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Mix cake according to package.
Add 3 tablespoons creme de menthe.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into greased baking pan. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve with warm milk or fried apples.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and spread mixture into a buttered oblong dish.

title: zucchini with almonds
directions: In 1 1/2-quart microwave dish, cook the onion, water and salt, covered, on 100% (High) power for 2 minutes.
Stir in the zucchini. Cook, covered, on High for 3 to 5 minutes or until zucchini is crisp and tender, stirring once.
Drain.
Stir in almonds, butter, marjoram, lemon juice and pepper.
Cook, covered, on High for 30 to 60 seconds more or until mixture is heated through.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: fudge dessert
directions: Place the first 5 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Crumble with pancake turner as baking.
Take half of the crumbs out and reserve.
Cover with vanilla ice cream. Top with fudge ice cream topping.
Sprinkle with other half of crumbs and freeze.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and flour.
Add egg yolks and milk.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter balls
directions: In a large bowl mix the powdered sugar, butter, vanilla extract and peanut butter with spoon until creamy. Then in a small bowl put both bags of chocolate chips and melt in microwave for 2 minutes until melted. Then take the mix and roll into small balls. After you roll mix into small balls dip them into bowl of chocolate until covered. Then place on a cookie sheet. Then place cookie sheet in freezer for 1 hour. After the chocolate balls have hardened place them in bowl and place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: corn cornbread casserole
directions: Prepare cornbread as directed on box.
After cooling, crumble cornbread very fine.
Add soup, corn, onion and pimentos and stir thoroughly.
Spread into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Pour melted butter on top and sprinkle grated cheese to cover. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Peel and core the apples and cut into slices.
Arrange in pie shell.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Mix flour, sugar and butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle as a topping over the apples.
Bake @ 450 for 10 minutes and at 350 for 40 minutes.

title: nut goodies
directions: Melt together almond bark and chocolate chips.
Add peanuts and marshmallows.
Drop with spoon onto wax paper.
Store in tight container.

title: pool room slaw
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Bring to heavy boil and then simmer 15 minutes, stir occasionally.
Pack in hot jars and seal. Very delicious on hot dogs or soup beans.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add tomatoes, soup and beans.
Bring to a boil.
Add cabbage, chili powder, salt and pepper to taste. Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and soft butter well.
Cook in microwave for 9 1/2 to 10 1/2 minutes on High.
Stir twice during cooking time. Make sure sugar is well dissolved, then add marshmallow cream, nuts, vanilla and chips.
Mix well, then spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easy microwave lasagna
directions: Combine sauce, tomatoes and water in a bowl.
Combine Ricotta, 1/2 cup Mozzarella, egg and garlic in another bowl.
Assemble lasagna as follows:
Using at least an 8 x 11 1/2 x 2-inch glass pan sprayed with "Pam" place 1/3 of the sauce in the bottom, then 3 noodles, 1/2 the Ricotta mixture, 1/2 the spinach or sausage and 1/3 of the Mozzarella.

title: mincemeat squares
directions: Combine all ingredients, except mincemeat. Pat 1/2 mixture in greased 13 x 9 pan to within 1/2-inch of edge. Spread with mincemeat. On a piece of waxed paper, pat out remaining half of mixture. Carefully place on top of mincemeat. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Drizzle with an orange glaze (orange juice and confectioners 10x sugar to desired consistency) and cut into squares.

title: rum cake
directions: Butter bundt pan and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Mix together all of the ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Pour sauce over cake while hot.

title: good cheese ball
directions: Mix all with a little red Mogen David wine and form ball.

title: hamburger beans
directions: In large bowl, combine cooked hamburger, onion and beans.
Add spices and seasonings; mix well.
Pour into casserole dishes (usually takes two).
Top with bacon slices. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until beans are bubbly and bacon is done.

title: buttered marshmallow squash
directions: Cut solid portions of squash into 1/2-inch round cuts; peel. From the large end, peel and remove seeds; cut as desired.
Cut rounds into fourths.
Add 1/2 cup water; cool slowly until tender Drain off water; add sugar, butter and nutmeg.
Mash or beat well. Pour into baking dish.
Cover with marshmallows.
Bake in oven until brown and glazy looking.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: deer stew
directions: Pressure deer meat with onion.
Add remaining ingredients. Boil until done.

title: fresh tomato juice
directions: Wash tomatoes; remove cores and cut into quarters.
Put in stainless steel kettle with onion, basil, peppercorns and salt. Simmer over low heat, stirring often and mashing tomatoes to soften to a juicy mush.
Put the mixture through a food mill.
If you want a thinner juice, put the milled puree through a fine strainer.
Add more salt to taste.
Chill.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion until hamburger is almost done.
Put in tomatoes and tomato soup and water.
Put beans in 10 minutes before serving just enough to heat them.
You can put chili powder in while cooking or use at the table.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Save liquid. Pour milk over bread crumbs and let stand for 5 minutes.
Add salmon, liquid, minced onions, eggs, salt and pepper.
Spoon into a greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: easy blueberry cobbler
directions: Place blueberries in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine flour, sugar and egg.
Stir until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Spread over blueberries.
Drizzle melted butter over topping.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.
Yield:
about 6 servings.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, water and vanilla, then beat well.
Add flour, baking powder and soda which have been combined and oatmeal.
Mix all together.
Add butterscotch morsels and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together very well. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: caesar salad
directions: Mix first seven ingredients together.
Cut lettuce into bite size pieces.
Mix together and toss with grated Parmesan cheese and croutons.

title: pecan pie
directions: Dissolve sugar, syrup, butter and salt over low heat.
Beat egg until foamy.
Add all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: eclair
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients well.
Layer with crackers, start with pudding mixture.
Top with icing.
Refrigerate.

title: sixty minute hot rolls
directions: Heat milk.
Sprinkle yeast over top of milk and allow to dissolve.
Add shortening, egg, sugar, salt and flour and mix well.
Cover and let rise 15 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until rolls are brown.
Makes 3 dozen rolls.

title: bacon dressing
directions: Cook bacon.
Add other ingredients.
Stir over low heat until thickens.
Pour over lettuce.

title: white frosting
directions: Beat 5 minutes the Crisco.
Add egg whites and beat 2 more minutes.
Add vanilla and sugar.
Beat to spread.

title: cider salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot cider liquid with salt.
Add cold ginger ale.
Chill until slightly firm; add fruit and nuts.
Make a day before to assure firmness.
Mold in 1-quart mold.
Serves 16.

title: easy pizza dough(this makes two 12-inch crusts.)
directions: In medium bowl, combine 1 cup flour, yeast and salt.
Add water and oil.
Mix on low speed of mixer about 2 minutes. Gradually stir in remaining flour to make firm.
On floured surface, knead 10 to 12 times.
Cover.
Let rise 15 minutes. Divide and shape.
Bake according to pizza recipe.

title: taco dip
directions: Bottom Layer:
In plate, put bean dip.
Mix seasoning mix with sour cream and mayonnaise.
Spoon over bean layer.
Top with shredded cheese (Cheddar and/or Mozzarella), black olives, diced tomatoes and onions.
Arrange nacho chips around platter and serve.

title: geneva's coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a glass bowl.
Put in microwave for 15 minutes.
Remove.
Stir.
Remove every 2 minutes and stir until thick.
Place in pie shell.
Cover with prepared egg white icing. Sprinkle with coconut.
Place in oven at 450° until brown.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes; dice into a large bowl. Add celery, sliced hard-boiled eggs and onion. Beat eggs; add sugar, spices, vinegar and water. Mix well. Pour mixture into hot bacon grease; stir and cook until mixture thickens. Pour over potatoes. Add bacon; stir.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and heat 1/2 stick oleo, potatoes, milk, eggs, vanilla, sugar (white) and salt.
Pour into a greased 2-quart dish.
Mix brown sugar, flour and pecans into 1 stick of melted oleo; pour over potato mixture.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: corn and shrimp soup
directions: Heat butter and add flour; make medium brown roux.
Add onion and saute.
Add remaining ingredients except green onions and parsley; let simmer 1 hour.
Add water for desired consistency. Add green onions and parsley.
Simmer 15 minutes and serve.

title: peas and spinach casserole
directions: Cook the peas and spinach according to directions and drain well.
Then add the soup and Cheez Whiz.
Heat thoroughly in oven. May be made ahead and reheated.
Fine bread crumbs may be sprinkled over top.

title: chicken licking good
directions: Put rice in bottom of casserole.
Put chicken on top in single layer.
Cook onion soup according to directions.
Pour over chicken; add milk to cream of chicken soup and heat.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in oblong pan at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: mock chicken fried steak
directions: Combine egg into ground beef, then work in enough crumbs to absorb moisture.
Sprinkle with salt and onion powder; make 1/4 cup balls and roll out on a board sprinkled with crumbs.
Fry in pan with a small amount of oil.
There have been times when I pureed onions and added them.
Once rolled these freeze well for the future.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into teaspoon size balls; place on cookie sheet.
Bake until golden, about 8 to 10 minutes, in 350° oven.

title: taco salad bowl
directions: Heat oil in 10-inch skillet for 2 minutes.
Fry tortillas 1 at a time in hot oil for 30 seconds, turning once with tongs.
Cool slightly.
Shape over taco salad shell molds on baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until crisp.
Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Stir in chili powder.
Layer lettuce, tomatoes, ground beef and cheese in salad shells.
Top with sour cream.
May serve with picante sauce, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: working mother's fast chicken or turkey a la king
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Add mushroom soup, milk, broth and vegetables.
Add chicken or turkey (cut up into bite size pieces last).
Thicken with a little cornstarch and water.
Serve with or over rice or noodles or put into pie shells and bake according to directions on box.
If you like more vegetables or want to stretch the meal, add more, but be sure to rinse off the vegetables well. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: hot crab meat dip
directions: Combine cheese and spices.
Fold in crab meat (including juice).
Add almonds.
Bake in glass pie plate for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve with fancy crackers.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and cream cheese in water.
Add cranberry relish and walnuts.
Partially set Jell-O mixture in refrigerator. Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator until set.
Keep refrigerated.

title: squash delight casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain; add oleo and mash.
Mix sugar, egg, mayonnaise, nuts, pepper, onion, salt and cheese and add to squash.
Pour mixture into buttered casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and more cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake until it is bubbling and brown (375° for about 30 minutes).
Serves 8.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix salt, baking powder and flour.
Add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Add flavoring and mix well.

title: oatmeal scotchies pan cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In large bowl combine butter, sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla extract; beat until light and fluffy.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oats and Nestle butterscotch morsels.
Spread dough into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.* Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into 35 (2-inch) squares.

title: lynda's potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook potatoes, salt, onion and enough water to cover.
Boil just until tender.

title: cereal muffins
directions: Place 3 cereals in bowl and pour boiling water over it; set aside.
Cream shortening, sugar and add eggs.
Combine with cereal mixture.
Add flour, soda, salt and baking powder with buttermilk.

title: holiday cider
directions: Slice orange into wedges.
Stud with cloves.
Combine cider and red hots in Dutch oven and cook over medium heat until candy is dissolved.
Add orange and cinnamon sticks; simmer over low heat until serving time.

title: coffee cookies
directions: Cream sugar with shortening and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture gradually.
Stir in nuts and raisins; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes; cool.
May be frosted with mocha icing, if desired.
Yield:
5 dozen.

title: elegant mushroom soup(serving size: 4)
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in margarine in a Dutch oven until onions are tender.
Stir in flour.
Dissolve bouillon in water. Gradually add bouillon and milk to mushrooms.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes or just until thoroughly heated.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until threads.
Add the raw peanuts; stir this quite often until it turns golden brown.
When this is done, add the margarine, soda and salt.
Mix this real quick; pour onto buttered pan or foil.

title: steak strips and mushrooms
directions: Cut steaks into 1/2 x 2-inch strips.
Use frying pan or heavy skillet; heat 2 tablespoons of butter; add meat.
Saute over high heat 3 to 4 minutes, turning, until cooked to your liking.
Place on warm platter.
Add 2 tablespoons of butter to pan with onions and mushrooms.
Saute 3 to 4 minutes over high heat.
Place on platter with meat.
Add wine and broth to pan; bring to a boil over high heat.
Scrape brownings into sauce; add salt and pepper to taste.
Add lemon juice and any juices from platter.
Boil over high heat until juices glaze.
Whisk in butter.
Return contents of platter.
Cook over high heat; continue mixing until completely hot.
Add chives and serve.
Serves 4.

title: grandma norton's molasses cookies
directions: Combine sugar, salt, Crisco, egg and molasses.
Beat until creamy.
In a small mixing bowl, combine flour, soda and spices. Add to sugar mixture; stir well.

title: dutch cinnamon waffles(zimmet waffles)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in the eggs, 1 at a time, and add cinnamon.
Work in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Form into small balls.
Place several in a hot waffle iron, suitably spaced.
Press down top and bake.

title: icing
directions: Add milk to flour gradually.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Cream butter and Crisco; add sugar, cooled mixture and vanilla.
Run mixer at high speed for 5 minutes. Looks like whipped cream.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls(gotqbki)
directions: Remove core from cabbage.
Place whole head in a large kettle filled with boiling salted water.
Cover; cook 3 minutes or until softened enough to pull off individual leaves.
Repeat to remove all leaves (about 30).
Cut thick center stem from each leaf.
Chop remaining cabbage.
Saute onion in oil.
Add meat, rice, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Place a heaping tablespoonful of meat mixture on each cabbage leaf.
Tuck sides over filling while rolling leaf around filling.
Secure with wooden picks.
Place half the chopped cabbage on bottom of a large Dutch oven.
Fill with layers of the cabbage rolls.
Cover with remaining chopped cabbage. Combine tomato soup with water; mix until smooth.
Pour over cabbage rolls.
Cover and bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.
Serve with sauce.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add chicken livers; cook 10 minutes until done.
Blend with brandy, sherry, Worcestershire sauce, basil and spices.
Put hard-boiled eggs through mill or sieve. Add butter to blender.
Stir until melted.
Add ground parsley and eggs; mix.
Refrigerate in serving containers.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If too thick, add a little water.
Spoon out with a teaspoon in hot oil, enough to cover hush puppies.

title: salad from kansas city
directions: Toss pineapple with marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Add toasted nuts on top.
Delicious with meat or a meal.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and blend well after adding each one.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: lou's famous cheesecake
directions: Step One:
Prepare jello with 1/2 cup hot water and 1/2 cup cold water.
Put in refrigerator to cool.

title: mexican taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add taco mix and picante sauce. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in beaten egg. Sprinkle frozen pie crust with 1/2 cup of cheese.
Top with chilies, then add beef mixture over chilies.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° on cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with lettuce and sour cream.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pudding mix with pineapples then add Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Chill for 1 hour if desired.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Preheat the oven to 450°.
Combine the flour, baking powder and salt in a large bowl, then add the sausage, cheese and butter. Blend well with a wooden spoon or with your hands.
Roll the mixture into 1 inch balls; it should yield about 36 pieces.
Place the balls about 1/2 inch apart on a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking sheet and flatten them slightly with the heel of your hand.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown at the bottom.

title: o.j. drink(orange juice)
directions: Blend all together.
Put in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine ingredients with electric mixer and beat for 1 minute.
Scrape bowl down and beat for 1 more minute.
Pour into greased Bundt or tube pan.
Bake for 40 minutes or until cake springs back when touched in center.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Into crushed crackers, add nuts, fruits, dates, raisins and cherries; coat thoroughly and set aside.
In large pan, mix butter, honey, salt, spices, flavoring and cream.
Mix well.
Add graham crackers and fruits; mix well to bond together.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: In medium saucepan, melt oleo.
Saute almonds.
Stir in onion mushroom soup.
Mix blended with flour and milk.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, stirring constantly until sauce is slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.

title: artichoke and mushroom salad
directions: Slice artichokes and mushrooms according to preference. Marinate overnight in Italian dressing. Serves 2 to 4. Don't know if can freeze. Must do ahead.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Stir stuffing mix and water in a medium bowl.
Remove stems from mushrooms; chop stems.
Cook and stir mushroom caps in 3 tablespoons hot margarine in large skillet until lightly brown. Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Cook and stir stems and peppers in skillet until tender.
Stir into prepared stuffing.
Spoon into mushroom caps; drizzle tops with remaining 2 tablespoons butter. Broil 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: old-fashioned apple butter
directions: Wash, drain and slice apples.
Cook in cider until soft. Press through sifter or food mill.
Boil until thick enough to heap on a spoon.
Add sugar and spices.
Boil until thick.
Pour into hot jars.
Process for 15 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: oven fried chicken chimichangas
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Wrap tortillas in damp paper towel.
Microwave on High for 15 seconds.
Brush both sides with vegetable oil.
Place a scant 1/2 cup of chicken mixture just below center of each tortilla.
Fold in left and right sides. Fold up bottom edge and top edge into a rectangle.
Secure with a toothpick.
Place on a Pam sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, until crisp and lightly browned.
Serve with shredded lettuce, salsa and sour cream (no fat; is good).
Serves four.

title: taco bake
directions: Fry hamburger; drain excess fat.
Add tomato sauce, kidney beans, enchilada sauce and black olives.
Simmer about 10 minutes. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Take a casserole dish and layer crumbled tortilla chips first, then meat sauce, then shredded cheese.
Repeat, ending with meat sauce and shredded cheese.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes on 350°.
Take out of oven; take remaining whole chips and line the edge of dish and spoon on sour cream. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Partially freeze meat.
Thinly slice across the grain into bite-size strips. Combine 1 tablespoon of flour and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Coat meat with flour mixture.

title: quick and easy fudge
directions: Line an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with buttered foil.
Combine sugar and milk in large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Boil stirring constantly 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat in chocolate chips and marshmallows until melted and mixture thickens.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into pan and cool until firm.
Store in tightly covered container.
May be frozen for a few weeks.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Drain beans; put in casserole dish.
Stir in soup, salt and pepper to taste.
Put onions on top.
Bake at 375° for about 35 minutes.

title: chocolate
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
This mixture should not be too light or too dark.
If it's too dark, add a little sugar.
If it's too light, add a little cocoa.
Add water.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Serve over buttered biscuits.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together first, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch iron skillet at 450° until brown and tests done with toothpick.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Mix oatmeal, flour and sugar.
Place half of mixture in an 8 x 8-inch greased baking dish.
Cover with cranberry sauce.
Spread rest of oatmeal over sauce.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve topped with vanilla ice cream.

title: luscious lemon meringue pie
directions: Make and bake a pie shell.
Mix cold water, salt and cornstarch.
Combine hot water and sugar in top of double boiler and bring to a boil over direct heat.
Add cornstarch mixture and cook until thickened.
Place over boiling water and cook until thick and smooth (15 minutes), stirring constantly.

title: chicken and biscuit pie
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine stew, chicken soup, onion and rosemary.

Stir in peas and mushrooms, carefully adding chicken. Heat slowly, stirring occasionally, until mixture boils. Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Arrange biscuits on top of hot chicken mixture. Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: shell salad
directions: Cook and drain shells.
Add chopped green pepper and diced onion.
Mix tomato soup, sugar, oil and vinegar together.
Pour over shells and refrigerate overnight.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken, peel off skin and take off the bone.
Mix soup, tomatoes, bell pepper, onion, garlic powder, chili powder and 1/2 cup of cheese.

title: deviled ham eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half and remove yolks.
Mash yolks and deviled ham together in small bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Stuff whites.
Garnish with parsley.

title: cheese bread
directions: Combine biscuit mix, cheese and poppy seed.
Add milk and eggs, stirring just enough to blend.
Beat 1 minute.
Turn into well-greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle with additional poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Serve warm.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix sugars and oleo.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix all dry ingredients with nuts.
Add to sugar mixture.
Make into long rolls and wrap each roll in waxed paper.
Refrigerate overnight. Slice in thin slices.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
These rolls can be kept in refrigerator indefinitely and baked as needed.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Break Hershey bars, then place them plus the chocolate chips, vanilla, marshmallow cream and butter in a 6 to 8-quart container. Place sugar and milk in a 4 to 6-quart saucepan; bring to a boil and cook 6 minutes. Pour mixture of sugar and milk over remaining ingredients; blend until smooth and creamy. After blended, add nuts. Mix, then drop balls of mixture on waxed paper with tablespoon.
Refrigerate about 6 hours. Makes about 6 pounds.

title: white lightning texas chili
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Cover with water and soak overnight (or at least 8 hours).
Drain the beans and place in a large pot.
Add 3 cans of broth and the next 7 ingredients.
Bring this mixture to a boil, then reduce heat to a simmer and cover.
Simmer for 2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add the fourth can of broth, the chicken and the next 3 ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour. Layer the bottom of a large casserole dish with the tortillas. Cover with the chili.
Add the salsa, sour cream and cheese as desired.

title: macaroon crunch pie
directions: Sprinkle 6 tablespoons coconut in bottom of baked shell. Cover with soft sherbet.
Place in freezer while preparing remainder.
In mixing bowl, beat whipping cream with powdered sugar until thickened; reserve 1 cup for topping.
Fold crushed cookies and pecans into remaining whipping cream.
Spoon over sherbet, sealing to edge.
Garnish with 2 tablespoons coconut. Freeze 6 hours or until served.
A two tiered treat of tangy sherbet and crispy macaroon cream.
Make it early and freeze.

title: pizza monster
directions: Spread pizza sauce on Italian bread. Place pepperoni slices on sauce.
Sprinkle cheese.
Use scissors to cut pepperoni or other ingredients to create a monster face for your pizza monster. Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 450° for
8 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a deep pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Combine cottage cheese, egg, spinach and dressing.
Spread 1/2 cup sauce on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Layer 3 noodles, spinach filling and sauce.
Repeat layering twice.
Top with Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes more, or until firm.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients; form into bite size balls.
Place on cookie sheet; bake for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: rice and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy chicken and pasta
directions: Brown and cut up chicken. Add frozen vegetables pasta blend, soup and water. Cover and simmer until done.

title: quick and colorful spinach medley
directions: Saute red pepper in butter 1 minute.
Stir in onions and nutmeg; cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in spinach; heat through. Season to taste with salt and pepper if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake, uncovered, 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: brisket
directions: Sprinkle brisket with celery salt, garlic salt, lemon pepper and onion salt. Center in a heavy piece of oil.
Sprinkle with liquid smoke and fold sides of foil to form a pocket.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: moroccan chicken
directions: Raisins and onions add a bit of sweetness to this mix of flavors and textures.

title: butter pastry
directions: Place steel blade in work bowl.
Add the flour, chunks of cold butter and salt.
Process with on/off turns until most of mixture resembles cornmeal, but a few larger size pieces remain.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate. After chilled, shape into ball. Top with parsley and chopped pecans. Serve with crackers.

title: corn bread
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Blend next 3 ingredients.
Add milk.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turkey salad
directions: Mix and serve as salad or sandwich.

title: apple swirls
directions: Roll out pie crust. Place sliced apples on dough. Roll up like jelly roll.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch slices.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Boil for 3 minutes oleo, water, sugar, cinnamon and salt. Pour over apple rolls and bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 250° and bake 45 minutes.

title: blue fish
directions: Place fillets skin down on lightly greased pan.
Brush 1/2 of melted butter and lemon juice on the fillets.
Sprinkle bread crumbs evenly on fillets.
Sprinkle seasonings on top of the fillets to suit your taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then baste with remaining butter and lemon juice.
Bake until flaky and golden brown.

title: easy oven beef stew
directions: Mix together in casserole dish.
Place in oven at 275° for 5 hours.

title: chocolate dream bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In large bowl, combine cake mix and oats. Mix well. Add butter and beat mixture on low speed until it clumps together and all dry mix is moistened. Press half of this mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Pour condensed milk evenly over batter. Sprinkle chocolate chips, coconut and pecans evenly over milk. Crumble remaining mixture over and bake for 20 minutes. Let cool well before cutting into bars.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add shortening.
Mix until coarse then add milk.
Mix until dough follows fork around bowl.
Knead 1/2 minute.
Cut into biscuits.
Bake on ungreased pan 8 to 10 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour two 8-inch round cake pans.
Into large bowl, measure all ingredients; with mixer at low speed, beat until well mixed constantly scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Beat at high speed 5 minutes occasionally scraping bowl. Pour batter into pans and bake 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool layers in pans on wire racks 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool on racks.
Makes 2 layers.

title: tuna macaroni casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Separate eggs, saving whites for meringue.
Beat egg yolks. Add sugar and cornstarch.
Mix with a little milk.
Then pour in rest of milk.
Cook over double boiler until thickened, stirring all the time.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Pour into baked pie shells.

title: beef scramble
directions: Cook macaroni by package directions; drain.
While macaroni cooks, brown beef and onion.
Stir in macaroni and remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Serve.

title: sugar-free ice cream(for 6-quart freezer)
directions: Beat eggs, milk and sweetener together and pour into freezer. Add 4 mashed bananas or other fruit, or make it plain.
Beat pudding mix and milk until it begins to thicken.
Pour into freezer.
Add milk to fill freezer.
Freeze.

title: hot virginia dip
directions: Saute pecans in margarine and set aside.
Mix all other ingredients and pour into a casserole dish and top with pecans. Chill until serving time, then bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: grandma sodek's jelly roll
directions: Mix eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar slowly until blended.
Add vanilla; add flour mixture, a small amount at a time. Last put in hot water.
Pour mixture onto greased and floured or wax paper lined jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Be careful not to overbake.
Invert on damp towel, putting jelly or filling on cake.
Roll up and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: grilled chicken teriyaki
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken, in a bowl.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Add chicken and coat to marinate.
Refrigerate, turning occasionally, at least 3 hours (preferably overnight). Grill chicken over medium heat for 40 minutes, turning until chicken is crisp outside and tender inside.

title: grape meatballs
directions: Mix hamburg, bread crumbs, onions, milk, egg, parsley, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Roll into meatballs.
Fry in shortening until done.
In crock-pot mix chili and grape jelly. Mix well, then add cooked meatballs.

title: scotch oatmeal shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine oats, sugar, flour and salt.
With pastry blender, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal. Stir in vanilla; mix well.
With hands, press mixture evenly into prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden.
Cool slightly.
Cut into bars while still warm.
Let cool completely in pan before removing.
Makes 32.

title: mexican magic
directions: Saute beef and onion.
Heat sauce of remaining ingredients except Doritos.
Line bottom of casserole with Doritos.
Layer sauce and grated Cheddar cheese.

title: red beet eggs
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid.
Place beets in quart jar. Measure reserved liquid if necessary.
Add enough water to measure 1 cup.
In saucepan, combine beet liquid, vinegar, sugar and salt; bring to boil, stirring.
Pour over beets, then refrigerate, tightly covered, 24 hours.
Next day, remove beets; put eggs in jar.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Also refrigerate beets.
Cover and ready to serve.

title: cinnamon cucumber rings
directions: Cover cuke rings and lime with water; soak for 24 hours.
Drain and wash with cold water 3 times.
Mix 1 cup white vinegar, alum and food coloring.
Cover with water; simmer 1 hour and then pour off.
Mix 2 cups white vinegar, sugar, 2 cups water and cinnamon sticks.
Heat and pour over cukes.
Let stand 24 hours.
Bring cukes and syrup to a boil.
Cool and pack in jars.
Can also use small package of cinnamon hearts.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cut citron and soak in grape juice overnight.
Drain.
Cream sugar and butter.
Beat eggs and add with part of flour, saving part to mix with fruit.
Add grated coconut and fruit.
Beat well. Put into pans and bake for 3 to 4 hours.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches and juice in 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add half of sugar and half of margarine to peaches.
Put into 350° oven and heat until mixture begins to bubble, about 10 minutes.
Open crescent rolls and spread on peaches.
Sprinkle remaining sugar and margarine on top of dough.
Bake 25 minutes until top is browned.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and gradually add sugar while beating.
Add chocolate bits and nuts.
Drop onto a greased cookie sheet one teaspoon at a time.
Place in a preheated 350° oven, then turn off heat and leave in oven overnight.

title: cheese loaf
directions: Slice bread diagonally, crisscrossing as you go.
Do not slice through the bottom.
Mix cheese, mushrooms and onion.
Fill bread with cheese mixture, pulling slices apart and stuffing cheese in between.
Mix seasonings with butter and drizzle all over stuffed bread.
Wrap entire loaf in aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Unwrap and enjoy!
This is also good for children, using Cheddar cheese, omitting seasonings and then serving with pizza sauce to dip with.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; pour off excess grease.
Place hamburger in an 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle the cheese and Pizza Quick sauce over meat.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great for an overnight slumber party.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Heat oil in saucepan.
Cook garlic for 2 minutes in oil over medium heat.
Add clam juice, wine and red pepper.
Stir well and simmer, uncovered, for about 20 minutes or until liquid is reduced by 1/3.
Cook linguine according to directions.
Drain.
Place back in pot.
Toss with butter.
Add white clam sauce mixture to linguine and toss.
This recipe can be doubled.

title: salad dressing
directions: Beat eggs lightly and add rest of ingredients.
Stir constantly over medium heat, until mixture boils.
Cool.
Add 4 tablespoons of any good commercial mayonnaise and mix.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Combine and drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown meat; mix all ingredients and place in a casserole dish. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until rice is tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: open-faced burgers
directions: Combine all burger ingredients.
Cover 1/2 of bun with mixture.
Place buns on cookie sheet.
Broil in oven until brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl.
After deboning chicken, add it to soup mixture.
Squeeze butter (small amount) into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add a thin layer of biscuits and pour soup mixture over biscuits.
Add a layer of biscuits and top with a small amount of butter.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes in preheated oven (350°) or until crust is brown.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Sift
dry ingredients, except sugar.
Add raisins, nuts and fruit.
Combine
sugar,
carrots, potatoes and shortening with the
dry
mixture;	mix
thoroughly.
Pour	into 1-pound well-greased coffee cans 3/4 full.	Steam for 2 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend peanut butter, cream cheese and confectioners sugar. Add Cool Whip and blend completely.
Turn into crust.
Let set in refrigerator for 2 hours and serve.
This pie is delicious.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Fill uncooked crust with sliced apples; pile high.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over sliced apples and chips of butter.
Cover with crust and freeze overnight.
Bake the next day.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cut up cabbage.
Cook until just tender; drain.
Mix white sauce with cabbage.
Put into buttered oven dish.
Sprinkle with butter and browned bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread and add ingredients.
Mix with the Miracle Whip.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate, preferably 24 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in greased 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch dish.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: 5 minute salmon tidbits
directions: Drain salmon; set aside juice.
Put salmon in a mixing bowl. Using a fork, break salmon.
Add egg and mix real good.
When gummy, add sifted flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Mixture is real thick. Do not add salt; pepper is okay.

title: aunt marsha's mint patties
directions: Combine
sugar,
water	and extract in a double boiler; add desired color.
Put over simmering water for 3 minutes or until creamy and	pours from spoon.
Drop nickel sized patties onto waxed paper.
When	they dry, you may decorate with icing if you wish.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk; then add peanuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix chicken, chiles and salt.
Combine enchilada sauce and evaporated milk.
Fry tortillas in hot oil for a few seconds on each side until limp.
Dip each tortilla in enchilada sauce mixture; fill with 1/4 cup chicken mixture.
Roll up and place seam side down in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 15 minutes, until bubbly.

title: impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth, 30 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Cool at least 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 1 pie.

title: cheese straws
directions: Let ingredients get to room temperature.
Mix by hand; roll into logs.
Chill in refrigerator.
Slice very thin; place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: top of stove rice pudding
directions: Cook rice, water and salt rapidly for 5 minutes, stirring, then lower heat to low.
Cover and continue slow cooking for 12 minutes.
Set off burner for 5 minutes, then add 2 cups milk to heat on medium.
(Beat egg whites and sugar; set aside.)
To rice and milk, add egg yolks and sugar, stirring and remove from heat. Add flavorings and egg whites with the sugar, folding in gently. Top with a sprinkle of cinnamon.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Defrost hash browns.
Mix all ingredients except corn flakes and pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover with corn flakes.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: Secure large elephant; kill, clean and cut into small cubes (this will take about 2 months).
Put in large kettle and simmer over kerosene heat at 465° for 14 weeks.
Make gravy to cover.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix meat, bread, salt, pepper and milk.
Form into balls. Place in pan in one layer.
Mix remaining ingredients together; pour over meat balls.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: paste(kids stuff)
directions: Mix flour and water until they are thick and creamy.
Will keep longer in refrigerator.

title: cajun cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage, bell pepper and onion together in 1 1/2 cups of water for 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 1 hour.

title: lemon chicken saute
directions: Roll chicken in flour to coat.
Spray 10-inch skillet with Pam.
Add butter and melt.
Add chicken.
Cook over medium heat until chicken is lightly browned (5 to 7 minutes).
Turn chicken over, continue cooking until lightly browned (5 to 7 minutes). Remove chicken; set aside.
Stir in teriyaki or soy sauce, lemon juice and garlic.
Return chicken to pan; simmer 3 minutes.
Turn chicken over, continue cooking until fork-tender (2 to 3 minutes). Serve over rice.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Mix all together well except cheese.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put cheese on top.
Mix 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1/2 cup melted butter and sprinkle this on top.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Add broccoli to jello, salt and boiling water.
Add onion. Add cottage cheese, mayonnaise and mustard.
Chill for several hours.

title: blueberry swirl
directions: Blend butter, flour and pecans.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lite banana split pie
directions: Add Sweet 'N Low to strawberries; set aside.
Layer each ingredient as listed, in order, in pie crust.
Chill about 2 hours before serving.
Serves 8. 3.8 grams fat, 195 calories.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour over pasta and mix well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry hamburg and add taco mix.
Stir and cool.
Layer in a large bowl the hamburg mixture, cut up lettuce, diced tomatoes, diced onion, cheese and taco chips.
Sprinkle dressing on top and toss all ingredients together to distribute well.
Serve.

title: strawberry-rhubarb bars
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, salt, 1/2 cup softened margarine, eggs and milk and line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spray sides of pan with Pam, otherwise jello will stick to sides. Spread rhubarb over bottom crust and sprinkle evenly with jello.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone.
Cut in bite size pieces. Mix with sour cream, soups and mushrooms.
Sprinkle with Ritz crackers.
Melt butter and pour over crackers.
Place in a 300° oven until crackers are golden brown.

title: summer berry pie
directions: Mix berries in a large bowl.
Pour into pie shell.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Gradually stir in water until smooth, stirring constantly.
Cook on medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour over berries in pastry shell.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Spread whipped topping over pie before serving.
Garnish with additional berries.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lemon chicken marsala
directions: Cut chicken into strips; coat with flour.
Heat oil and butter in large skillet.
Saute chicken quickly and remove from skillet. Saute mushrooms.
Add Marsala and cook 2 minutes.
Add chicken broth and juice of 1 lemon, slowly.
Mix cornstarch with water and stir in.
Add basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes; return chicken to sauce.
Slice remaining lemon into 8 rounds; place on chicken.
Sprinkle with parsley and cook on low heat for 10 minutes.
Serve with noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Saut or boil until tender; drain.
Mix it all together. Form mixture to fit inside of a 9 x 13 pan without touching the side of the pan. Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut sugar cookie dough into 1/4 to 1/2-inch slices (thin). Press on 12 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: ripe tomato pickle
directions: Put tomatoes, onions and peppers on stove.
Cook until tender. Add balance of ingredients.
Cook for about 45 minutes to 1 hour over low heat.
Watch for sticking.
Put in jars and seal.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together all ingredients and dip into hot oil or grease until brown.

title: banana crush(serves 60)
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Add juices.
Peel and mash bananas in blender.
Stir in juices.
Pour into freezer boxes.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: black forest brownie torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans. Prepare brownie mix according to package directions for cake-like version. Stir chocolate chips into batter. Divide batter evenly between prepared pans. Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes in pans. Loosen edges; remove from pans to wire racks. Cool completely.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix and pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: angie's cherry cheesecakes
directions: You will need mini cupcake papers.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine hot water, salt, shortening and sugar in large bowl. Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast, softened in lukewarm water.
Add egg and half of flour; beat well.
Stir in more flour, enough to make a dough easily handled.
Grease top of dough, cover and store in refrigerator.
Keeps 4 to 5 days.

title: sherry dressing for fresh fruit salad
directions: Beat egg and sugar.
Add butter, juice, salt and sherry.
Whip cream and add last.

title: sugarless orange cookies
directions: Blend egg and
margarine
in
mixer
bowl.
Add
orange juice and orange rind; mix
well.
Add mixture of dry ingredients; beat until smooth.
Stir in pecans and raisins.	Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2
inches
apart onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20
minutes
or
until brown.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: beaver center biscuits
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in shortening. Beat egg and add milk and egg to flour mix.
Roll out and cut with round cutter.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: ann's two pie crust
directions: Measure 2 cups flour into bowl.
To 1/2 cup salad oil add cold water.
Add oil and water to flour all at one time.
Stir as little as possible.
Roll out on two 12-inch lengths wax paper. For one crust, cut ingredients in half.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook the chicken in 4 cups water until tender.
Debone chicken when cooled.
With 2 cups of the chicken broth, add 2 cups of plain water.
Add deboned chicken, carrots, celery, salt, sugar, pepper and bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add the egg noodles and cook until tender.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix lobster delights, mushrooms, bell pepper, olive oil and Italian seasoning. Serve on lettuce with a good squeeze of fresh lemon juice. Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: home of the brave chili
directions: Brown meat in oil in Dutch oven.
Chop jalapenos and bell pepper. Mix with meat, onions and garlic.
Husk tomatillos.
Wash and chop.
Add to mix with tomato sauce, beef broth, cilantro, paprika, salt and cracked pepper.
Boil then reduce.
Heat and simmer for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
4-5 servings.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Melt butter and mix crumbs.
Beat Dream Whip, milk, cream cheese and sugar.
In deep square pan, layer crumbs mixture, 1/2 Dream Whip and pie filling.
Add rest of Dream Whip.
Top with crumbs.

title: debbie johnston's quick and easy homemade bread
directions: Mix warm water and dry yeast until dissolved.
Stir in sugar, oil and salt.
Add flour gradually, until desired consistency. You do not have to knead the dough.
Divide into 3 parts and put in greased bread pans.
Let rise once and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cowboy coffee cake
directions: Combine flour, salt, sugar and shortening.
Mix until crumbly. Reserve 1/2 cup mixture.
To remaining crumbs, add baking powder, soda and spices.
Mix thoroughly.
Add milk and eggs.
Mix well. Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top of cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: white chili
directions: If using dry beans, soak beans for 24 hours.
In a crock pot combine beans, 5 1/4 c. broth, garlic, onion, and seasonings. Simmer covered at least 5 hours until beans are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in chilies and chicken and remaining broth. Add jalapenos.
Cover, simmer 1 hour.
ENJOY!!

title: incredible cake
directions: Mix together brown sugar and cocoa; add water and marshmallows. Spread in 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan (at this point it looks awful). Make cake mix according to directions on the box; pour evenly over mixture in pan.
(Be sure and pour as evenly as possible because you can't spread it at all after it is poured.)
Spread nuts over cake mix and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares; remove from pan with a spatula and turn so that pudding is on top.

title: spicy hot black-eyed peas
directions: Cook bacon slices in large skillet over medium flame until crisp.
Remove bacon; crumble and set aside.
Stir all remaining ingredients except parsley into bacon drippings in skillet; bring to a boil over medium-high flame.
Reduce flame to low and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon mixture into serving dish; sprinkle bacon and parsley over top.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: perfect dumplings
directions: Mix all together.
Drop into boiling water or stew and cover. Cook 10 minutes before lifting cover.
Continue cooking until tops of dumplings are not shiny.
Serve.

title: crunchy chicken
directions: In a greased casserole or dish, place chicken breasts.
Mix soup and liquid together and pour over chicken.
Place cheese over this and sprinkle with croutons.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Uncover and brown cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breast; cool and shred or cube, set aside. Mix tomatoes, soups and sour cream in bowl. Take tortilla and cut length wise. In a 9 x 13 glass dish, spread a layer of soup mixture, then a layer of tortilla strips, a layer of chicken and then a layer of cheese.
Continue until all ingredients are used, ending with chicken and cheese. You should have some soup mixture left after using all the other ingredients. Pour it over last layer of chicken and cheese.
Cover with foil and place in a 350° oven for 50 minutes. Remove foil and bake for another 10 minutes. Serve hot, alone, or with other mexican food (rice and beans) or a tossed salad.

title: mint dessert
directions: Crush the cookies until fine.
Melt the marshmallows in the milk.
Add Creme de Menthe and peppermint into marshmallow mixture.
Fold marshmallow mixture into the whipped cream.

title: crab quiche
directions: Sprinkle cheese into pie shell.
Beat eggs with milk and seasonings.
Pour over cheese.
Sprinkle crab meat and mushrooms over pie.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until firm (inserted knife should come out clean).
Cut into wedges.

title: no guilt brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Break up chocolate.
Over very low heat, melt chocolate; cool slightly.
In a food processor, puree all ingredients except chocolate and powdered sugar until smooth.
Add melted chocolate.
Blend well.
Pour into a lightly buttered 8-inch square pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until just set. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16 servings.
Serving size:
1 piece.
Preparation time:
45 minutes.

title: rum and pine nut tartlets
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease 12-cup muffin pan.
Brush 1 sheet of phyllo with butter.
Top with second sheet of phyllo and brush with butter.
Fold in half crosswise.
Fold in half again.
Brush with butter and cut into fourths.
Place 1 portion in each prepared cup, forming a shell.
Bake until light golden, 5 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Thaw strawberries and reserve 1/2 cup juice for filling.
Mix soda, flour, cinnamon, sugar and salt.
Add strawberries, oil and eggs.
Mix by hand until thoroughly mixed.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans after spraying with Pam.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Slice white potatoes with skins on, about 1/2-inch thick.
You can peel if desired.
Mix Italian dressing with melted butter and pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 300° until done, or cook 30 minutes in microwave.

title: favorite tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cool water and drain well.
In large bowl, combine tortellini, sweet pepper, broccoli, carrot and olives.
For dressing, in a small bowl, stir together mayonnaise, pesto sauce, milk, cheese, oil, vinegar, pepper and garlic.
Pour over tortellini.
Toss lightly until well mixed.
Cover and chill for at least 5 hours.
Serve in a spinach lined bowl.

title: chocolate yummy pie
directions: Mix and press into a baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to boil and simmer 20 minutes. Seal in hot jars.

title: pork chops and stuffing
directions: In skillet, brown pork chops on both sides.
Then place in shallow baking dish.
Mix bread crumbs, onion, butter, 1/4 cup water, celery and pepper.
Place over pork chops.
Blend soup with 1/3 cup water and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until pork is tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: blackberry fritters
directions: Fill deep fryer with oil to at least 6-inches.
Heat oil to 375°.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Stir in eggs and milk.
Blend and fold in berries.
Drop by spoonful into hot oil and cook, turning once, 2 or 3 minutes or until golden.
Drain on paper towel and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve warm.

title: soda cracker delight
directions: Beat the egg whites and cream of tartar.
Add the sugar and the ???.
Fold in the crushed soda crackers.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° until light brown.
Top with fruit pie filling.
Good with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Heat and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to a boil.
Then cook to soft ball stage (238°), stirring only if necessary.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until mixed well, then let set until it cools to 110° without stirring.
Beat until mixture begins to hold its shape. Pour into buttered dish.
Cut when cool.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: hunter's chicken
directions: In large skillet, saute bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon; drain fat.
Saute onions in oil until tender; remove.
In small skillet, brown chicken, adding more oil if necessary.
Drain excess fat.
Combine bacon, onions, tomatoes, 57 sauce and pepper; pour over chicken.
Cover; simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is tender, basting occasionally.
Remove chicken.
Skim excess fat from sauce.
If thicker sauce is desired, gradually stir in mixture of equal parts flour and water, simmer until thick.
Serve chicken and sauce with rice or noodles.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Put sage to taste.
Bake until onions are done.

title: omelette a la joel(student favorite)
directions: Other appropriate ingredients may be added, as desired.

title: molasses berry cake
directions: Mix in order.
Bake in two 9-inch round pans at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: creamy lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a medium bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in condensed milk, ReaLemon and food coloring. Pour into prepared pastry shell.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: orange french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix together first seven ingredients. Pour into large shallow dish.
Cut bread diagonally into 1-inch slices.
Soak bread 1 minute on each side.
Brown the slices in butter over medium-low heat in a large skillet.
When all are browned, place on cookie sheet (in single layer) and bake 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; sift powdered sugar over toast.
Serve with heated maple syrup.
Crisp, not soggy, perfect for a large group since it's all ready at the same time.

title: oven-fried fish
directions: Place margarine in a baking dish and place in preheated 375° oven.
Watch carefully while melting margarine.
Dip fish in beaten egg, then in meal.
Coat well.
Place each piece in butter, turning to coat evenly.
Season to taste.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: crusty grecian bread
directions: In large bowl combine 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Add water and oil.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remainder flour to form a stiff dough.
Knead until no longer sticky, about 5 minutes. Place in greased bowl and turn to grease top.
Cover let rise until double in size.
Shape into loaves.
Combine egg white and water. Brush over top, sprinkle with sesame seed.
Make 3-4 diagonal slashes 1/2 inch deep across the top.
Bake at 375 degrees for 40-45 minutes until light brown.

title: almond nuggets
directions: Add dry ingredients; gradually mix until dough is smooth and well blended.
Shape into small balls using 1 teaspoon dough for each cookie.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and flatten slightly.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Roll warm cookies in confectioners sugar.

title: strawberry sugar-free dessert
directions: Heat water; add jello.
Mix.
Place strawberries in dish; cover with nuts.
Add orange juice to jello mix and stir.
Pour jello over berries and nuts.
Let set.
When firm, make pudding according to directions and pour over chilled jello.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: sausage and creamed potatoes
directions: Cut sausage and onion together and fry until slightly brown. Add water to cover and add the cut up potatoes.
Salt to taste and cook until soft.
Make a paste of the flour and milk.
Add to mixture and cook until thickened.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach; strip leaves from stems, discarding any tough or discolored leaves.
(Wash spinach first in warm water for 2 minutes; lift out leaves and rinse twice in cold water.)
Place drained spinach leaves in glass salad bowl; add onion, eggs, bacon and salt and pepper to taste.
Toss with dressing just before serving.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: french bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast on 1/4 cup warm water.
Let stand a few minutes, then stir until dissolved.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over the shortening, salt and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add 3/4 cup cold water and cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and gradually beat in enough flour to form a stiff dough.

title: creamy salmon dip
directions: Combine tartar sauce and water.
Add sour cream and blend well.
Drain salmon.
Remove any black skin and pieces of bone. Flake salmon and add to sour cream mixture.
Combine thoroughly. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 2 cups.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix and form into balls.

title: caramel apple walnut squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine flour, oats, sugar, soda and salt.
Cut in butter until crumbly, reserving 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture.
Press remainder on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Add walnuts to reserved crumb mixture.

title: saucy chicken breasts
directions: Melt the butter in a large skillet. Add chicken and brown on both sides.
Remove chicken.
Add chopped onion, green pepper and mushrooms to skillet.
Saute until tender.
Return chicken to skillet.
Combine soup mix, 1 1/4 cups water and Worcestershire sauce in a small bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Combine cornstarch and 3 tablespoons water. Add to sauce.
Return to boil for 1 minute. Serve sauce over chicken.

title: carefree tuna bake
directions: In saucepan, blend soup, water and liquid from peas.
Stir in tuna, peas and seasonings.
Bring to quick boil, stirring occasionally.
Add rice and pour into casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: gaminee's christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Then add 1 cup flour to which has been added the spices.
Add vanilla and butter flavor extract.
Cut the dates, cherries and pineapple.
Mix with the chopped pecans and walnuts in a large bowl.
Mix the remaining 2 cups of flour with fruit and nut mixture.
Mix well.
Blend the egg and sugar mixture with fruit and nut mixture.
Drop by teaspoonful onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: grandma white's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Either put pecans in batter or sprinkle on top of pies.
Makes two pies.
Bake until brown and firm, 30 or 40 minutes, 15 minutes at 350° then reduce to 300° until done.

title: fireside vegetable soup
directions: Melt butter into 2 to 3-quart saucepan.
Add leeks and garlic and saute 5 minutes.
Add broth, tomatoes and carrots; simmer 5 minutes.
Add zucchini, mushrooms, beans and peas; simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in mustard, then season with salt and pepper.
Ladle into ovenproof soup bowls.
Top each with a square of bread.
Cover with 2 tablespoons cheese.
Broil 4 inches beneath heat source about 3 minutes until cheese melts and browns lightly.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: poppy seed crackers
directions: Combine flour and butter with a pastry blender until crumbly. Add poppy seed, tossing with a fork to blend.
Add water, a teaspoon at a time, mixing lightly with a fork until dough forms. Shape into a ball and refrigerate until stiff enough to handle. Preheat oven to 425°.
Roll dough out to 1/8-inch thickness; cut into 3-inch squares and bake 4 to 5 minutes.
Serve with cheese spread.

title: cheese knots(children)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Use small saucepan and melt butter over low heat. Mix together Chex crumbs, cheese and butter.

title: mashed potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, eggs, celery, onions, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix salad dressing, sugar and vinegar; stir into potato mixture.
Chill thoroughly, garnish with green onions.
Makes 12 servings.

title: sweet-sour baked beans
directions: Place onions (cut in rings) in skillet; add sugar, mustard, garlic powder, salt and vinegar.
Cook 20 minutes, covered.
Add onion mix to beans; add bacon (fried crisp, crumbled and drained). Pour into 3-quart casserole.
(Drain all beans except New England-style.)
Bake in moderate oven, 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 12 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Mix all but flour.
After mixed well, add flour.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Pour in pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: tina's pizza casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook meat, onion and sausage; drain. Combine meat and onion with tomato sauce, Cheddar cheese soup and seasonings.
Stir in cooked macaroni.
Pour in casserole dish. Top with Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw and drain chopped spinach.
Blot with paper towels until most of moisture is out of spinach.
Beat eggs with mixer.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Shape into large or small balls. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until light brown edges show.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat together the egg substitute, sugar, salt, vanilla and milk.
Remove 2/3 cup of the mixture and set aside.
Pour remaining mixture into the baked pastry shell.
Bake, uncovered, for 3 minutes.
Stir carefully to move the cooked portion from the edge of the pie to the center.
Cook again, uncovered, for 7 to 8 minutes or until the center of the pie is almost set.
Stir gently again, if necessary, halfway during the cooking period.
Sprinkle the top of the pie with nutmeg and let cool before serving.
Pour reserved custard mixture into two custard cups.
Cook for three to four minutes, or just until the mixture begins to boil.
Cool before serving.

title: mom's lima bean stew
directions: Soak lima beans overnight or 2 days.
Grate carrots and slice celery.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Add water to cover beans.
Cook all day.
Add water when needed.

title: mexican dip
directions: Melt first three ingredients.
Brown ground beef and sausage. Drain.
Mix in dip.
Enjoy!

title: peach cobbler 3
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over melted butter.
Top with peaches.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: coffee orange fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
In large mixer bowl, combine cake mix, sour cream, oil, water, eggs, pudding mix, liqueur, orange peel and cinnamon.
Beat with electric mixer on low to blend.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until tested pick comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Dust with powdered sugar if desired.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Crush defrosted strawberries.
Mix undiluted fruit juices and water.
Chill.
Add ginger ale and crushed strawberries just before serving.
Pour over ice cubes in punch bowl.

title: cornbread stuffing
directions: Saute onions and celery.
In large bowl combine all ingredients.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes.

title: corn and asparagus bake
directions: Drain corn, reserving liquid.
Melt butter or margarine; quickly stir in flour.
When blended, gradually stir in milk and 1/2 cup corn liquid.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add cheese, egg, parsley and celery salt; stir until well blended and mixture thickens.
Add almonds.
Remove from heat.
Layer corn, asparagus and sauce in a baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 6. Contains 215 calories per serving.
Source of Vitamins A, B and C. Preparation time:
10 minutes.
Cooking time: 30 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown onion and celery in shortening.
Add meat and brown. Add parsley, mustard, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer; stir occasionally.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream first three ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Place by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle generously with sugar before baking.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.
I usually chill the dough for several hours before baking.

title: peanut butter potato chip cookies
directions: In bowl, cream first 5 ingredients.
Add flour.
Stir until soft dough. Stir in chips and potato chips.
Drop by spoonfuls 1 inch apart onto greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool.
Store in container.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; form into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet; press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: german potato salad(hot potato salad)
directions: Boil potatoes in their jackets.
When soft, peel and dice. Add celery, diced hard-cooked eggs and onion.
Fry bacon in skillet until crisp and brown.
Beat 2 eggs; add sugar, spices, vinegar and water.
Mix well.
Pour egg mixture into the hot bacon fat and stir until mixture thickens (about 10 minutes).
Pour over potato mixture and mix lightly.
Let stand for awhile.
This can be eaten hot or cold.
Very, very good!

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg in a large bowl.
In another bowl, beat eggs, milk and oil.
Add bananas and stir; mix until smooth.
Add nuts.
Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients.
Mix only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven until done, about 1 hour.
Cool in pan about 5 minutes. Remove from pan and finish cooling on rack.
Makes one loaf.

title: layered green salad
directions: In a long Pyrex dish, layer in order given lettuce through green peas.
Spread mayonnaise on top.
Mix together sugar, salt and black pepper; sprinkle over mayonnaise.
Next, sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over mayonnaise.
Last, top with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Spread chops with mustard; dip into seasoned flour.
Brown in fat.
Place in casserole and cover with soup.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: duck
directions: Put medium onion inside duck.
Cook in roaster with a little water for 1 hour.
Throw away onion and water and start all over again.
Rub salt and pepper inside and outside.
Rub butter inside and out; put in roaster again.
Cook 1 1/2 hours (about), basting often to keep from drying out.
Put wine or vinegar in water.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together;
refrigerate.
Serve with any kind of chips or a hollowed out round loaf of bread, using extra bread for dipping.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients together and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes, until hot. Serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Blend butter, sugars, vanilla and water.
Beat in egg.
Add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate bits and nuts.
