Drop by well-rounded half teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour in tube pan at 350°.

title: corn and crab chowder
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter.
Add pepper.
Blend all remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer slowly for 30 minutes.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal, walnuts and peanut butter together.
Combine milk, sugar, cocoa, butter and vanilla in a saucepan.
Boil 2 minutes.
Pour over oatmeal mixture and drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper until cooled.

title: curried shrimp
directions: Blend cream of chicken soup with milk.
Add curry powder and shrimp.
Heat thoroughly and serve over cooked rice tossed with chopped parsley and butter.

title: super eggplant casserole
directions: Cut up eggplant into 1-inch square pieces.
Parboil about 5 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Add onion, meat and tomatoes and saute about 5 minutes or until tender.
Add meat mixture plus cooked rice and seasonings to eggplant and mix well.
Spoon mixture into buttered casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until the cheese is melted and eggplant is tender.

title: quick surprise rolls
directions: Mix milk and yeast to dissolve.
Add mashed potatoes, sugar and salt.
Add soft shortening and add just until easy to handle the 2 to 2 1/2 cups flour.
Knead well.
Shape into any desired shapes.
Let rise until double in bulk (45 to 60 minutes).
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crockpot simple pork chops
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in shallow dish, dredge pork chops and set aside. Pour oil into large skillet, place over medium heat until hot. Cook chops in oil until brown. Combine remaining flour mixture and chicken broth in slow cooker. Place browned chops in slow cooker and cook on HIGH for 2-2 1/2 hours or until tender. Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: no bake chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, milk and cocoa together in a 2-quart pan; bring to a boil.
Add rolled minute oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop on waxed paper the size of a tennis ball.
Let harden to set.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: grilled applebee's style chicken
directions: Follow directions on envelope.
Double oil and water if you use more that 4 lbs. of chicken.
Grill thigh quarters, starting with skin side down, 20 to 25 minutes on each side over a medium warm Charcoal grill.
If you use a different variety of chicken, cook less time.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until crumbly.
Press half into greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Top with apples.
Cook remaining ingredients until thick and clear.
Pour over apples; top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crock-pot vegetables
directions: Grease crock-pot.
Brown onion in butter.
Add milk, soup and cheese.
Heat through.
Layer vegetables in crock-pot.
Pour cheese mixture over.
Cook on low for 4 to 5 hours or 2 to 3 hours.
Last hour, cook with lid off and sprinkle on crumbs.

title: grandma's sand cookies
directions: Set oven to 300°.
Cream butter, sugar and vinegar in mixer. Stir together baking soda and flour and add to sugar mixture. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 30 minutes until light and golden.
Makes approximately 40 cookies.

title: easy nut bread
directions: Riboflavin or Vitamin B-2, maintains skin and eye tissue.
It is essential for the utilization of oxygen within the body and enzyme function.
A diet rich in dark, green vegetables, whole grain, pasta, mushrooms, milk, eggs, meat and fish will supply the riboflavin your body needs.

title: penny carrot salad
directions: Blend soup, salad oil, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, prepared mustard and salt.
Heat until warm.
No need to boil.
Pour mixture over carrots, onion and green peppers.
Let it brew for 24 hours in refrigerator to set taste in.
Keeps very well.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Add chili and cheese; mix well.
Heat until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through, stirring frequently.
Spoon into chafing dish.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: marinade for grilling
directions: Mix together and pour over meat.
Allow at least 2 hours to marinate.
Dispose of marinade after placing meat on the grill.

title: carrot salad
directions: Scrape the carrots.
Place on ice for 1 hour.
Grate coarsely. Mix in remaining ingredients.

title: confetti macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain well. Combine macaroni, Spam, Velveeta, pepper and onion in a large bowl.
Mix salad dressing, milk and vinegar.
Pour dressing over macaroni and toss well.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake uncovered 45 minutes at 350° stirring occasionally.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix all ingredients, except beef, onion and cheese.
Put half of batter on bottom of baking dish.
Add beef, onion and cheese over batter.
Pour other half of batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spoonburgers
directions: Brown meat in hot fat; add onion.
Cook until golden brown. Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer on low heat 30 minutes.
Spoon onto buns.
(You may melt cheese on top!)

title: lemon berry cooler
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container; cover.
Blend on high speed until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2 (1 cup) servings.

title: microwaved cinnamon toasted pecans
directions: Melt butter and pour over pecans.
Mix sugar and spices and mix with buttered pecans.
Spread on paper plate.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes.

title: microwave divinity
directions: And a little leaven of prayer

title: pennsylvania milk punch
directions: Mix ingredients in blender or with spoon until frothy.
Serves 6 (3/4 cup).

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper, celery and the bay leaves in butter for 10 minutes, being careful not to burn them.
Add flour; stir until fully blended, 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt, sugar, garlic powder, cayenne and lemon pepper.
Simmer gently for 15 minutes. Add shrimp; continue to simmer until shrimp are thoroughly heated. Serve on a bed of hot rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ruthie mae's garlic chicken
directions: Place prepared chicken in single layer in long Pyrex dish. Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle garlic, flour and water over chicken. Dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven until chicken is brown and bubbly.
Turn once.
Baste with pan drippings.
Cook until chicken is tender.
Good over rice.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in baking dish and cover with broth.
Add soups. Add can of Veg-All.
Mix flour, milk and melted butter together and pour this mixture over the chicken/broth/soup mixture.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes, until crust is brown and bubbly.

title: black or white peanut clusters
directions: Place chocolate morsels or white chocolate in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe dish.
Cook on 100% power (High) for 1 or 2 minutes or until melted.
Add peanut butter and shortening.
Cook on High 1 or 2 minutes or until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Blend well. Stir in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a cookie sheet lined with waxed paper.
Chill until set.
Store in refrigerator. Makes about 2 dozen clusters.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook garlic and onions until soft; add meat.
Mix paste, water and seasonings; stir into the meat.
Simmer for 35 to 40 minutes or until sauce thickens.

title: potato bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
To scalded milk, add shortening, sugar, salt and mashed potatoes.
Stir until cold and add yeast cake.
Add enough flour for stiff dough.
Roll dough in flour.
Place in greased bowl and cover.
Rise.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: pavlova(australian dessert)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar gradually; continue to beat until sugar is all mixed in.
Place aluminum foil on a baking sheet.
Pour mixture onto center of foil and form a circle (8-inch).
Indent center slightly.
Lower temperature of oven to 250°.
Place in oven and bake 1 hour. Remove from oven; cool.
Fill with sliced fruits.

title: rolled round steak
directions: Saute onions, celery, green pepper and garlic in bacon fat. Add salt, pepper, paprika, thyme, poultry seasoning, water or tomato sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add bread crumbs.
Sprinkle round steak with seasoning and salt.
Cut steak 1/2-inch thick. Cover with dressing.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Mix 1/3 cup soup, 1/4 cup water and onion.
Dip chicken in soup mixture; roll in stuffing.
Place in shallow baking dish and drizzle with butter.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Combine remaining soup and water.
Heat; stir.
Serve over chicken.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potatoes and carrots au gratin
directions: Heat
oven to 375°.
Combine potatoes, carrots and onion in buttered
quart	baking dish.
Blend soup, milk, salt and pepper
and pour over vegetables.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour.
Uncover, sprinkle
with
cheese
and bake an additional 15 minutes. Yield: 8 servings.

title: play dough
directions: Cook over medium heat until it boils around spoon.
Knead for a couple of minutes.
Put in a plastic bag and seal.

title: rye bread snacks
directions: Mix cheese, olives, onion and mayonnaise together.
Put on the rye bread.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: cheese cake dreams
directions: Use an 8-inch square pan.

title: joey's favorite strawberry dessert
directions: Mix together; pour into 2 graham cracker or baked pie shells. Refrigerate.

title: smoked pork tenderloin with molasses barbecue sauce(recipe from "eating well" magazine)
directions: The earthy sweetness of molasses goes exceptionally well with pork.

It's recommended that the pork be smoked over pecan shells or hickory chips and finished on the grill to crisp the exterior. This is delicious served hot or at room temperature, accompanied by Mango Salsa (recipe follows.).

title: depression cake
directions: Boil together for 2 minutes the first 7 ingredients.
Cool and add flour and soda.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan 20 to 30 minutes at 350° or make cupcakes.
Best with chocolate icing.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add sugar and pudding.
Beat thoroughly.
Stir in topping, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into freezer can and add milk to full line.
Freeze according to instructions with freezer.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix melted oleo, flour and pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: cheese buds
directions: With mixer, blend cheese and butter.
Sift flour and pepper. Gradually work into creamed mixture with spoon.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 1-inch rounds.
Brush with egg white; top with pecan half.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet in hot oven (425°) for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs lightly in large bowl. Stir in oil, grated & well drained zucchini, sugar & vanilla. Sift flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon & salt onto waxed paper. Stir in egg mixture until well blended, stir in raisins & nuts. Put into 2 well-greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until center springs back when touched with fingertip. Cool in pans on racks for 10 min. remove from pans and cool completely.

title: snack crackers
directions: Whisk together first 5 ingredients. Pour over crackers, stirring to coat. Place on baking sheet and bake at 275° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar together. Add eggs one at a time and beat well. Mix dry ingredients and add to above mixture and mix well. Add chopped apple and nuts and mix well. Cook in bundt or tube pan for 50 minutes at 325. Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: vegetable goulash
directions: Combine vegetables, tomato sauce and a mixture of remaining ingredients in a large saucepan; stir to blend.
Cover and bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Turn into a warm serving dish and serve hot.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter.
With a wire whisk, stir in flour.
Add milk or half and half; stir until mixture is smooth and starts to thicken.
Add chicken broth and cheese; reduce heat and stir constantly until cheese melts.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, macaroni and pimentos.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch or 3-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: creole red devil's food cake (never fail)
directions: Pour coffee over cocoa and cook until thick; let cool.
Mix flour, baking soda and cloves together.
Cream Crisco and sugar. Beat egg yolks and add to cocoa-coffee mixture.
Add milk, flour, baking soda and cloves.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in loaf cake and/or rectangular pan in preheated oven at 375° until it pulls away from sides of the pan or until it springs back when lightly touched on top.
When cool, top with white icing.

title: kale soup
directions: Bake steak until dry at 375° until well well done.
(Bake steak in open roasting pan so that you can make your soup stock in the same pan.)

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix brownie mix according to package. Bake, then let cool. Mix pudding in different bowl following directions. Let set until firm, then put this on top of brownies. Crush all 4 candy bard, sprinkle on top of pudding. Then add layer of Cool Whip.

title: seashell crab salad
directions: Cook shells according to package.
Drain and cool.
Combine shells, crab meat and vegetables.
In another bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Mix and toss with shell mixture.
Chill.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Then add milk, water, melted margarine and vanilla.
Pour into 2 deep dish pie crusts.
Cook at 350° until firm.
Add nutmeg, if desired.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add vinegar and water and boil for 5 minutes.
Add beets.
Serve.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Mix cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg. Stir nuts in egg white to coat. Add other ingredients and stir well. Spread on cookie sheet (foil lined). Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Stir a few times while baking.

title: turtle cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Make cake according to package directions.
Pour half of cake batter into prepared pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels, milk and butter in top of double boiler.
Pour over baked cake.
Top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour remaining cake batter over chips and nuts.
Bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in 9 x 13 pan. Spread Hormel chili on top of cheese. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Put in 350° oven or microwave until cheese melts.
Serve with white corn chips.

title: tortillas
directions: Combine flours and salt together.
Add oil and gradually add water and mix (may not need all water).
Makes soft dough but not sticky.
Divide into 12 to 15 equal balls of dough.
Roll or press to thin tortilla.
Brown on grill or skillet on both sides.
(Cook like you cook a pancake, no oil.)

title: strawberry cream freeze
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar together and fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into foil lined muffin tins and freeze until firm, about 2 hours.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken bean stew
directions: Cut chicken; brown slightly in oil.
In another pan, saute onion in butter.
Add broth and chicken and cook for 10 minutes. Then add potato soup.
Simmer until chicken is tender.
When done, remove chicken and place in Pyrex dish.
Set aside.

title: rice and noodle dish
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water.
Wash and drain.
Braise onion in oil.
Boil eggs and slice.
Blend all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Place in oiled pan and sprinkle bread crumbs or potato chips on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: italian scalloped potatoes
directions: In a Corning Ware dish, layer the first 7 ingredients.
Add the water, and top with the bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours or until potatoes are soft.
Remove from oven and let sit for 15 minutes.
Serve with your favorite side dish.

title: freezer strawberry jam
directions: Add water to Sure-Jell as directed.
Mix sugar with strawberries and let set for at least 15 minutes.
Fill jars to 3/4 to the top and place in freezer.

title: easy salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: grits and cheese casserole
directions: In a 3-quart casserole place water, grits and salt.
Microwave at High 10 to 12 minutes, uncovered, stirring after five minutes. Add butter and cheese to grits.
Mix well.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes, until butter and cheese are melted.
Stir well.
In a 1-cup measure, beat eggs and fill with milk to the 1-cup line. Add garlic powder and Tabasco.
Quickly stir into grits.
Pour mixture into a well-greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Dot top with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Microwave on High 17 to 19 minutes, rotating dish one-half turn after 9 minutes, until set.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute chuck and onions.
Place layer of rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Next, layer of ground chuck on top of rice. Slice carrots and place on top of meat.
Shred up cabbage and fill dish.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on top of cabbage.
Pour beef broth and water over cabbage.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in covered casserole dish.

title: salsa
directions: Mix together all ingredients, simmer one hour. Add 1 C vinegar. Cook until thickens to desired consistency. Fill sterilized canning jars, seal.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients until fine crumbs (reserve 1 cup crumbs for top).
Add water with baking soda dissolved in it and molasses.
Beat until smooth.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate walnut roll
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line jelly roll pan with parchment or waxed paper.
Grease liberally and dust with flour.
Beat the egg whites until very stiff.
Gradually add sugar, a spoonful at a time, beating until thick and glossy.
Whisk the egg yolks.
Add to the whites, then carefully fold in flour, baking powder and ground walnuts.
Turn mixture into the prepared pan and level top.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes.
When baked, turn out onto a sheet of waxed paper sprinkled with a little sugar.
Roll from the short end like a jelly roll, keeping the paper inside.
Cool.

title: chile cheese casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl; stir well.
Set aside.

title: mock enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Add chili and soup (do not add water).
Place a layer of corn chips in a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add a layer of meat and sauce and then a layer of cheese.
Repeat until gone.
Set aside for 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: flounder a l'orange
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine salt, pepper, orange juice, rind and oil in a bowl.
Place fish in oiled, shallow baking pan. Pour orange juice mixture on top.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and serve at once.

title: "i can't wait for puerto rico" french toast
directions: Crush corn flakes.
Dip bread in eggnog, allowing to soak.
Put bread on plate of corn flakes and flip to cover other side. Lightly brown in margarine on both sides.

title: hot water corn bread
directions: Combine flour, meat, salt and baking powder.
Gradually pour into corn meal mixture until thick consistency.
Wet hands with cold water.
Take small amount of corn meal mixture.
Shape into patties.
Have cooking oil hot.
Drop patties into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.

title: cabbage and beef casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion until brown.
Stir in rice.
Place shredded cabbage in a greased baking dish.
Add beef mixture over the cabbage.
Mix soup, water, sugar and vinegar.
Pour on top. Cover with a lid and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ripe cucumber sweet pickles
directions: Cook in large kettle until soft.
Spoon into clean jars.
No processing required.

title: turkey salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on toasted bread for sandwiches.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all together well.
Makes own crust.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: deviled clams
directions: Scrub clam shells thoroughly.
Put hinge side down in covered Dutch oven with small amount of water over a low heat.
Clams are cooked when shells have opened.
Using tongs, remove shells to a large platter.
With the point of a knife, detach connecting muscle tissue along with clams from shells.
Remove dark material from the stomach.
Grind clams and hard-boiled eggs.
Mix with onion, celery, cream and raw egg.
Refrigerate until set.
Fill clam shell halves.
Add buttered bread crumbs last.
Arrange on a cookie sheet or in a shallow pan.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: sunshine jello
directions: Prepare jello with boiling water.
Mix.
Mix in pineapple and carrots.
Chill for 3 hours.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Combine strawberries and the 2 tablespoons sugar.
Cover and let stand in the refrigerator at least 1 hour.
In a mixing bowl, stir together flour, the 1 tablespoon sugar, baking powder and baking soda.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine egg and buttermilk.
Add to flour mixture all at once, stirring until combined.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix well, cut out and bake at 375°.
Makes 18 biscuits.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate; remove from heat and add peanuts. Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper. Place in refrigerator 12 hours.
Keep in cool place until eaten. Makes 3 dozen.

title: pepper steak and rice
directions: Mix steak, onion, bell pepper and flour together.
Brown in skillet until tender.
Cook rice.
Serve steak mixture over rice.

title: date coconut balls
directions: Boil dates, eggs and butter 5 minutes, stirring and mashing dates as fine as possible.
Remove from heat and stir in Rice Krispies.
Cool and roll in small balls.
Roll balls in shredded coconut.

title: tomato basil torte
directions: Poke pie crust with a fork and bake for 5 minutes. Mix together mayonnaise, dried basil, oregano, garlic and pepper; spread on pie crust. Add tomato slices and cheese blend. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until cheese is slightly browned.

title: new potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Reserve juice to soak bananas in to prevent darkening. Combine all ingredients.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix sugar an flour and add to the beaten eggs. Add canned milk and 3 tablespoons of other milk.
Beat until well blended.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens slightly. Remove from heat and add vanilla and peaches.
Place the mixture in a 1 1/2-gallon freezer container and fill to 2/3 full with remaining milk.
Mix well.
Freeze.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain a little juice off of pineapple.
Mix jello and pineapple.
Heat to dissolve the jello.
Cool.
Mix cheese and Cool Whip.
Add pineapple mixture.

title: oreo sundae
directions: Crush 22 Oreos; mix with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with the mixture (spray pan with Pam).
Slice 1/2 gallon vanilla ice cream on top of lining.
Cover with chopped pecans.
Cover with Saran Wrap and freeze.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: To boiling water, add the oatmeal and let stand for 25 minutes until cool.
Cream sugars and shortening and add eggs and oatmeal. Sift dry ingredients and add to other mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: jacob's favorite slush
directions: Blend together and freeze. Thaw a little before serving.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat.
Brown onion and celery in shortening.
Add to meat.
Add potatoes, tomatoes and chopped carrots.
Place in pastry-lined dish and stripe top with 1/2-inch wide pastry strips. Bake 30 minutes in a 425° oven.

title: raspberry lemon muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Combine the eggs, cream, oil and lemon extract.
Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fold in raspberries.
Spoon into 18 greased or paper lined muffin cups. Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: country corn bread
directions: Put cornmeal into bowl and scald with 2 cups boiling water, mixing as you pour.
Add sugar, eggs, salt, flour, milk and baking powder.
Mix with electric mixer until blended well.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, condensed milk, pineapple, lemon juice, pecans and sugar together.
Place in pie shells.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours before serving.

title: macaroni pie
directions: Boil macaroni until soft.
Pour 3 yolks in pan along with the milk and stir until it comes to a boil.
Place macaroni in casserole dish.
Spread cheese, season with salt and pepper. Place in butter and pour sauce over mixture and reheat.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: springtime salad
directions: Put the apples, celery and cucumbers in a bowl and sprinkle with lemon juice, distributing evenly over all pieces to prevent browning.
Sprinkle with sugar and salt; mix well.
Cover and chill until serving time.
Fold in the sour cream or mayonnaise.
Line salad bowl with crisp greens and arrange salad over it.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix the ingredients well and shape into a ball.
Roll in nuts. This may also be shaped into 2 or 3 smaller balls, then rolled in the nuts in the event that a large size portion was not needed. May be frozen.

title: tuna turnover
directions: Mix tuna with Barbecue Sauce (see recipe following).
Roll one slice whole wheat bread thin.
Place tuna on bread and fold over to form triangle.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream together oil, sugar and flour.
Add eggs, baking soda, cinnamon, carrots and walnuts.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan in a 300° oven for 60 minutes.

title: magic paint bag
directions: You also need large Ziploc plastic bag and masking tape or cloth tape.

title: hot fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate over low heat.
Meanwhile, beat eggs and add syrup, salt, sugar and vanilla.
Add chocolate mixture and mix well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 35 to 40 minutes.
It will be very shaky and must cool to set.
Reheat and serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: linguini with clam sauce
directions: Cook and drain the linguini.
In large frying pan, saute garlic in oil and butter (slightly), just so oil mixture is flavored (but do not brown garlic).
Add clam juice and allow to simmer for 5 minutes.
Add the clams and allow to simmer for an additional 5 minutes.
Add pasta, parsley and pepper, tossing lightly to combine all ingredients.
Add the cheese, toss lightly to combine all ingredients.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes, to allow pasta to absorb all the flavors and heat everything.
Serve with extra cheese.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken and let cool.
Take all bones out and pull apart the meat into bite-size pieces.
Put in a large casserole dish. Pour soup over chicken and mix.
Prepare box of stuffing as directed on box.
Mix stuffing mixture with chicken and soup. Pour 1 can of broth over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: cherry sponge cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, beat well after each one.
Add flour and fold in well. Pour batter into tart pan.
Make squares in the batter with a toothpick.
In each square put a spoonful of your favorite filling and bake.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes (depending on oven).
Test with toothpick.
When cool, dust with powdered sugar.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in vanilla.
Add cream gradually until right consistency for cake.

title: chow mein casserole(my kids love this one!)
directions: Brown the ground beef or turkey and onions; drain.
Add into the pan the remaining ingredients, except the chow mein noodles. Mix together well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered, then for 30 more minutes, uncovered.
Sprinkle with chow mein noodles; set back in oven for 5 minutes.

title: spam spread
directions: Put the first 5 ingredients through a meat grinder.
Add a little salt, pepper and celery.
Stir in 2 or 3 tablespoons of Miracle Whip to moisten.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar all together.
Blend in eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients. Chill several hours.
Roll into balls and into powdered sugar. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fluffy buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a medium bowl with a wire whisk.
Cut in butter with a pastry cutter or 2 knives until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Add buttermilk all at once and stir briefly with a fork until the mixture just comes together.
Dollop biscuits onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes, brush tops with melted butter. Continue to bake for 3 to 5 minutes longer or until golden brown. Yield: 20 biscuits.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid with about a quart of water and sugar.
Add pineapple and orange juice (large cans).
Stir.
Add 7-Up and thawed orange juice.
Can also add 32 ounces of Sunny Delight. You may want to add more sugar.
Makes about 2 gallons.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and pumpkin. Sift dry ingredients and add it to pumpkin mixture.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Sprinkle pan with confectioners sugar.

title: lemon dream frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients in a small bowl at medium speed.
Scrape bowl often.
Mixture should be light and fluffy.
Spread on your choice of items.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake crust in oven until brown on 350°.
Mix together sugar, water and cornstarch in a boiler and cook until clear.
Add 4 tablespoons of strawberry Jell-O.
Cut strawberries and put into browned crust.
Pour liquid mixture over it.
Chill and put whipped cream on top, if desired.

title: best chicken salad ever
directions: Toast the almonds to light brown.

Combine 2 tablespoons juice from the pineapple with the mayonnaise, mustard, curry powder and salt. Set aside. Cut chicken into small slivers and mix with remaining ingredients (except pineapple). Add flavored mayonnaise and blend well.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
If desired, serve on lettuce leaf, garnished with pineapple and green grapes. Serves 4.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Combine 4 tablespoons sugar and 4 teaspoons cinnamon (set aside).

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix flour, pepper and cheese; cut in butter using pastry cutter.
Mix with hand until it becomes stiff dough.
Mix in 2 cups Rice Krispies.
Chill overnight; work with small amount of dough, about size of baseball.
Roll to 1/4 inch or less.
Press pecan on top of each biscuit.
Bake at 300° about 15 or 20 minutes; watch carefully!

title: dr. zan's texas barbecue beans
directions: Soak the beans overnight in water.
Do not, under any circumstances, no matter how dire, substitute canned beans!
Place in saucepan with cooking water to cover.
Add the salt, bacon, black pepper, chili powder, onion, and bay leaf.
Simmer, covered, for 2 hours, then add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer, stirring occasionally and gently, for 2 more hours at least, or until beans are tender and juice is thickened.
Cook uncovered if juice is thin; cook covered if not.
Adjust salt just before serving.
Serve hot with Texas barbecued beef.*

title: raisin cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll thawed
dough
on
floured
surface to 14 x 8-inch rectangle.
Reserve 2 tablespoons butter for later use.
Brush remaining
butter
over
dough.
Combine
cinnamon
and sugar; sprinkle over
dough
along with raisins, nuts and lemon peel. Start from
14-inch
side, roll up jelly roll style.
Cut into 12 rolls.
Arrange
in 9-inch greased pie plate or baking pan. Allow to rise in refrigerator overnight.
Brush with remaining butter and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Allow to cool 10 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Soak cornbread and biscuits or white loaf bread in stock from giblets, milk or water.
Cook in deep skillet over medium gas flame (300° to 325° dial setting on controlled burner) until golden the onions and chopped celery in 1/3 cup hot fat.
Combine bread and onion mixture with eggs, salt, pepper, poultry seasoning (if desired) and sage (if desired).
Add stock from giblets, milk or water to thoroughly moisten.
Mix well.
Stuff bird.
If dressing is baked separately, bake in shallow uncovered baking pan in moderate gas oven (325°) for 1 hour.
Makes 12 cups.
If very light, fluffy dressing is desired, add 1 teaspoon baking powder.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix together sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Add scalded milk gradually and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add beaten eggs.
Cook and stir constantly until thick again.
Add chocolate and blend.
Cool.
Add vanilla and fold in whipped cream if freezing in your kitchen freezer.

title: old time pancakes
directions: Stir
together
flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar.
In deep medium-size bowl, beat egg until thickened and lemon
color.
Add
buttermilk and butter; beat to blend. Add flour mixture; stir only until it is moistened.

title: steak by kirby
directions: Put A.1. on it.
Cook on grill.
If it burns that's alright, I'll eat it anyway.

title: sauteed zucchini
directions: Heat olive oil in skillet.
Add zucchini and saute over high heat for 3 minutes.
Stir in basil and remaining ingredients. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Makes 2 servings.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Stir until smooth and blended over double boiler.
Add wine gradually, then crabmeat.
Serve hot with unsalted crackers.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix brown sugar, margarine and peanut butter until crumbly. Press into a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan (ungreased).
Flatten with a rolling pin.
Put wax paper over mixture and roll.

title: pecan delights
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir into egg mixture.
Add pecans; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: shrimp de chink
directions: Prepare equal amount of vegetable ingredients and slowly boil in the water from the chestnut can.
Also boil (in a separate pot) all the stalks, leaves, peelings and anything else left over from the ingredients to gain a more flavorable broth.
Then pour only the broth into the ingredients that are slowly boiling.

title: pumpkin spice cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In medium bowl combine flour, soda, salt and pumpkin pie spice.
In large bowl, blend sugars with an electric mixer at medium speed.
Add butter and beat to form a grainy paste.
Scrape sides of bowl, then add egg, pumpkin and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Drop by rounded tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheets, 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake 22-24 minutes until slightly brown around edges. Immediately transfer cookies with a spatula to a cool surface. Yield 3 dozen cookies.

title: caramel corn
directions: In 2 1/2 quart pan, put brown sugar, corn syrup, margarine, cream of tartar and salt.
Boil over medium heat, stirring.
Boil rapidly for 5 minutes.
Take off heat, stir in soda quickly.
Pour over popcorn.
Bake at 200 degrees on cookie sheets for 1 hour. Stir 2 to 3 times during baking.
Turn onto wax paper to cool.
